ainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"margin-right: 0;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Role\n! scope=\"col\"| Performer(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Tooltip|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Naam Hai Tera\"\n| 2005\n| {{mdash}}\n| [[Himesh Reshammiya]]\n| ''Aap Kaa Surroor''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref name=\"video\" /><br /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.saavn.com/p/song/hindi/Aap-Kaa-Surroor/Naam-Hai-Tera/FzxeSBlhdGw |title=Naam Hai Tera |publisher=[[Saavn]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201020910/http://www.saavn.com/p/song/hindi/Aap-Kaa-Surroor/Naam-Hai-Tera/FzxeSBlhdGw |archive-date=1 February 2016 |access-date=16 January 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Mile Sur Mera Tumhara|Phir Mile Sur Mera Tumhara]]\"\n| 2010\n| Herself\n| Various\n| {{mdash}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/amitabh-launches-new-version-of-mile-sur-mera-tumhara/article1-501675.aspx |title=Amitabh launches new version of Mile sur mera tumhara |date=25 January 2010 |work=Hindustan Times |access-date=7 June 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150708033525/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/amitabh-launches-new-version-of-mile-sur-mera-tumhara/article1-501675.aspx |archive-date=8 July 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Bolydude Ganeshan\"\n| 2012\n| {{mdash}}\n| [[Ganesh Hegde]]\n| ''Let's Party''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Ganesh-Hegde-makes-Pune-dance/articleshow/11893870.cms |title=Ganesh Hegde makes Pune dance |last=Birajdar |first=Laxmi |date=15 February 2012 |work=The Times of India |access-date=25 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127034051/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/pune/Ganesh-Hegde-makes-Pune-dance/articleshow/11893870.cms |archive-date=27 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone]]\n\n== Footnotes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|id=2138653|name=Deepika Padukone}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/index/id/1856 Deepika Padukone] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n\n{{featured list}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Padukone, Deepika filmography}}\n[[Category:Indian filmographies]]\n[[Category:Actress filmographies]]\n", "name_user": "Not to mention", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deepika_Padukone_filmography"}
{"title_page": "Deepika Padukone", "text_new": "{{pp-semi-protected|small=yes}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Deepika Padukone\n| image              = Deepika Padukone at Chhapaak premiere.jpg\n| alt                = Deepika Padukone is seen smiling at the camera\n| caption            = Padukone at the premiere of Chhapaak in 2020.\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age |df=yes|1986|1|5}}\n| birth_place        = [[Copenhagen]], Denmark\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actress|film producer}}\n| yearsactive        = 2005\u2013present\n| father             = [[Prakash Padukone]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Ranveer Singh]]|2018}}\n| works              = [[Deepika Padukone filmography|Full list]]\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone|Full list]]\n| website            = {{URL|deepikapadukone.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Deepika Padukone''' ({{IPA-hns|d\u032ai\u02d0p\u026aka\u02d0 p\u0259\u0256\u028ako\u02d0\u0273e\u02d0|pron}} or {{IPA-hns|pa\u02d0\u0256\u028ako\u02d0\u0273|}}; born 5 January 1986) is an Indian film actress and producer. One of the highest-paid actresses in India, [[List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone|her accolades]] include three [[Filmfare Awards]]. She features in listings of the nation's most popular personalities, and ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' named her one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]] in 2018.\n\nPadukone, the daughter of the badminton player [[Prakash Padukone]], was born in [[Copenhagen]] and raised in [[Bangalore]]. As a teenager, she played badminton in national level championships but left her career in the sport to become a fashion model. She soon received offers for film roles and made her acting debut in 2006 as the title character of the [[Kannada film]] ''[[Aishwarya (film)|Aishwarya]]''. Padukone then played a dual role opposite [[Shah Rukh Khan]] in her first Bollywood release, the romance ''[[Om Shanti Om]]'' (2007), which won her the [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]]. Padukone received praise for her starring role in the romance ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' (2009), but this was followed by a brief setback. \n\nThe romantic comedy ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' (2012) marked a turning point in her career, and she gained further success with starring roles in the romantic comedies ''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]'' and ''[[Chennai Express]]'' (both 2013), the heist comedy ''[[Happy New Year (2014 film)|Happy New Year]]'' (2014), [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s period dramas ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015) and ''[[Padmaavat]]'' (2018), and the [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] action film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' (2017). She also received critical acclaim for playing a character based on [[Juliet]] in Bhansali's tragic romance ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' (2013) and a headstrong architect in the comedy-drama ''[[Piku]]'' (2015), winning two [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Filmfare Awards for Best Actress]]. She formed her own company Ka Productions in 2018, under which she produced ''[[Chhapaak]]'' (2020), in which she also starred as an [[acid attack]] survivor. \n\nPadukone is the chairperson of the [[Mumbai Academy of the Moving Image]] and is the founder of [[the Live Love Laugh Foundation]], which creates awareness on mental health in India. Vocal about issues such as [[feminism]] and depression, she also participates in stage shows, has written columns for a newspaper, designed her own line of clothing for women, and is a prominent celebrity endorser for brands and products. Padukone is married to her frequent co-star [[Ranveer Singh]].\n\n== Early life and modelling career ==\nPadukone was born on 5 January 1986 in [[Copenhagen]], Denmark to [[Konkani Language|Konkani]]-speaking parents.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Celebrity/Deepika-Padukone/894255-Profile.aspx |title=Biography: Deepika Padukone |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=23 July 2012 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141231022055/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Celebrity/Deepika-Padukone/894255-Profile.aspx |archivedate=31 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Baksi |first=Dibyojyoti |title=Shah Rukh Khan made Deepika Padukone learn Tamil |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/shah-rukh-khan-made-deepika-padukone-learn-tamil/story-cdrZkwDuAQGCilR51uF7wI.html |accessdate=18 August 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=13 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304081932/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/shah-rukh-khan-made-deepika-padukone-learn-tamil/story-cdrZkwDuAQGCilR51uF7wI.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> Her father, [[Prakash Padukone]], is a former professional badminton player and her mother, Ujjala, is a travel agent.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-182121908.html |title=She's the model of success |work=[[The Star (South Africa)|The Star]] |date=4 August 2008 |accessdate=29 August 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140610213030/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-182121908.html |archivedate=10 June 2014 |df=dmy-all }}{{subscription required|via=Highbeam}}</ref> Her younger sister, Anisha, is a golfer.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kaura |first=Neha |title=Deepika\u2019s link-ups don\u2019t bother us, says sister |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepikas-link-ups-dont-bother-us-says-sister/articleshow/13994578.cms |accessdate=2 July 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=11 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616173634/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepikas-link-ups-dont-bother-us-says-sister/articleshow/13994578.cms |archivedate=16 June 2012 |df=}}</ref> Her paternal grandfather, Ramesh, was a secretary of the Mysore Badminton Association.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/an-exciting-tournament/article3185184.ece |title=An exciting tournament |newspaper=The Hindu |date=5 January 2006 |accessdate=3 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085559/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/an-exciting-tournament/article3185184.ece |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> The family relocated to [[Bangalore]], India when Padukone was a year old.<ref name=\"toi interview\">{{cite news |last=Gupta |first=Priya |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Ranbir-and-I-are-still-friends-Deepika-Padukone/articleshow/16782698.cms |title=Ranbir and I are still friends: Deepika Padukone |accessdate=29 August 2013 |date=13 October 2012 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014233537/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Ranbir-and-I-are-still-friends-Deepika-Padukone/articleshow/16782698.cms |archivedate=14 October 2012 |df=}}</ref> She was educated at Bangalore's [[Sophia High School]] and completed her pre-university education at [[Mount Carmel College, Bangalore|Mount Carmel College]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Just How educated are our Bollywood heroines?: Deepika Padukone |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm#3 |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130805134000/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm |archivedate=5 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> She subsequently enrolled at the [[Indira Gandhi National Open University]] for a Bachelor of Arts degree in sociology but later quit it due to scheduling conflicts with her modelling career.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Deepika-Padukone-has-not-put-studies-on-back-burner/articleshow/2661901.cms |work=The Times of India |title=Deepika Padukone has not put studies on back-burner |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=30 December 2007 |archivedate=18 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150718235820/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Deepika-Padukone-has-not-put-studies-on-back-burner/articleshow/2661901.cms |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone has said that she was socially awkward as a child and did not have many friends.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> The focus of her life was badminton, which she played competitively from a young age. Describing her daily routine in a 2012 interview, Padukone said, \"I would wake up at five in the morning, go for physical training, go to school, again go for playing badminton, finish my homework, and go to sleep.\"<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> Padukone continued to pursue a career in badminton throughout her school years and played the sport in national level championships. She also played baseball in a few state level tournaments.<ref>{{cite news |last=Banerjee |first=Soumyadipta |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-was-a-state-level-baseball-player-deepika-padukone-1349480 |title=I was a state level baseball player: Deepika Padukone |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=18 February 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222022814/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-was-a-state-level-baseball-player-deepika-padukone-1349480 |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> While concentrating on her education and sporting career, Padukone also worked as a child model, first appearing in a couple of advertising campaigns at the age of eight.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/mp/2004/08/11/stories/2004081101100100.htm |title=The long and short of the ramp |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=11 August 2004 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911085352/https://www.thehindu.com/mp/2004/08/11/stories/2004081101100100.htm |archive-date=11 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[Education in India|tenth grade]], she changed focus and decided to become a fashion model. She later explained, \"I realised that I was playing the game only because it ran in the family. So, I asked my father if I could give up the game and he wasn't upset at all.\"<ref name=\"model\">{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/613309.cms |title=Smash hit on the ramp |work=The Times of India |first=Asha |last=Chowdary |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=13 April 2004 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025015245/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/613309.cms |archivedate=25 October 2012 |df=}}</ref> In 2004, she began a full-time career as a model under the tutelage of [[Prasad Bidapa]].<ref name=\"model\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Malani |first=Gaurav |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-not-a-part-of-race/articleshow/10971364.cms |title=Deepika Padukone not a part of race |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=7 December 2011 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085559/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-not-a-part-of-race/articleshow/10971364.cms |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}<br />{{cite news |last=Saran |first=Rhea |title=Venus Rising? |url=http://www.verveonline.com/30/people/verve/venus/excerpt.shtml |accessdate=7 August 2013 |work=[[Verve (Indian magazine)|Verve]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018010159/http://verveonline.com/30/people/verve/venus/excerpt.shtml |archivedate=18 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\nEarly in her career, Padukone gained recognition with a television commercial for the soap [[Liril]] and modelled for various other brands and products.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gahlaut |first=Kanika |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-in-new-liril-soap-ad/1/196716.html |title=Making a splash |work=[[India Today]] |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=12 April 2004 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBsSbRF?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-in-new-liril-soap-ad/1/196716.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Deepika Padukone: Biography |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity-profile/Deepika-Padukone.htm |publisher=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=7 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906020146/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity-profile/Deepika-Padukone.htm |archivedate=6 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> In 2005, she made her [[runway (fashion)|runway]] debut at the [[Lakme Fashion Week]] for designer [[Suneet Varma]] and won the \"Model of the Year\" award at the [[Kingfisher (beer)|Kingfisher]] Fashion Awards.<ref>{{cite web |last=Menon |first=Sita |url=http://www.rediff.com/getahead/2005/apr/21fwdeep.htm |title=Go white this summer |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=21 April 2005 |publisher=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928093037/http://www.rediff.com/getahead/2005/apr/21fwdeep.htm |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Chowdhury |first=Smita R. |title=Glamour, glitz & grace |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050405/asp/calcutta/story_4572605.asp |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]] |date=5 May 2005 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927205701/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050405/asp/calcutta/story_4572605.asp |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> Padukone's fame increased when she appeared in a highly popular print campaign for the 2006 [[Kingfisher Calendar]];<ref name=\"meet\" /> the designer [[Wendell Rodricks]] commented, \"Since [[Aishwarya Rai]], we haven't had a girl as beautiful and fresh.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://m.indiatoday.in/story/young-achievers-deepika-padukone-ms-dhoni-to-rabbi-shergill/1/181846.html |title=Young achievers: Deepika Padukone to Aditya Mittal, MS Dhoni to Rabbi Shergill |work=India Today |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=20 February 2006 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBwTlZD?url=http://m.indiatoday.in/story/young-achievers-deepika-padukone-ms-dhoni-to-rabbi-shergill/1/181846.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Rodricks had spotted her at a Ganjam jewellery class he was teaching and signed her up with the Matrix agency.<ref>{{cite book |last=Vasudev |first=Shefalee |title=Powder Room |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DzdfsXQEtqoC&pg=PT61 |publisher=Random House India |isbn=978-81-8400-297-3 |page=61 |year=2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231234025/http://books.google.com/books?id=DzdfsXQEtqoC&pg=PT61 |archivedate=31 December 2013 |df=}}</ref> At the age of 21, Padukone relocated to [[Mumbai]] and stayed at her aunt's home.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> That year, she gained wider recognition by featuring in the music video for [[Himesh Reshammiya]]'s song \"Naam Hai Tera\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Iyer |first=Meena |title=Deepika Padukone in awe of beauty pageant winners |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-in-awe-of-beauty-pageant-winners/articleshow/10767352.cms |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=17 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085600/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-in-awe-of-beauty-pageant-winners/articleshow/10767352.cms |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nPadukone soon began to receive offers for film roles.<ref>{{cite web |title=The hottest heroine in Kannada cinema |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/24sld1.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=24 August 2006 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928092027/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/24sld1.htm |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> Believing herself to be too inexperienced as an actor, she instead enrolled for a course at [[Anupam Kher]]'s film academy.<ref>{{cite news |title=On course: Deepika Padukone joins Anupam Kher's Film Academy |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/badminton-star-prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-shifted-to-mumbai/1/193374.html |work=India Today |date=11 July 2005 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwC0HxiV?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/badminton-star-prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-shifted-to-mumbai/1/193374.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Following much media speculation, the director [[Farah Khan]], who had noticed her in Reshammiya's music video, made the decision to cast her for a role in ''[[Happy New Year (2014 film)|Happy New Year]]''.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /><ref name=\"meet\" /> Fashion designer [[Wendell Rodricks]] also takes credit in helping her get the role. Farah Khan was looking for a model to star in her next film, and got in touch with [[Malaika Arora]]. Rodricks, for whom Padukone had been modelling for roughly two years then, recommended her to Arora, a close friend of his, who in turn recommended her to Khan in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/malaika-arora-deepika-padukone-om-shanti-om-wendell-rodricks-1039745-2017-09-07|title=Throwback Thursday: Did you know Malaika Arora helped Deepika Padukone bag her first film Om Shanti Om?|date=Sep 7, 2017|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-05-22}}</ref>\n\n== Acting career ==\n{{See also|Deepika Padukone filmography}}\n\n=== Film breakthrough and career struggles (2006\u20132011) ===\nPadukone announced in 2006 that she would make her film debut with ''[[Aishwarya (film)|Aishwarya]]'', a [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada film]] directed by [[Indrajit Lankesh]].<ref name=\"meet\">{{cite web |last=Vijayasarathy |first=R.G. |title=Meet Deepika Padukone |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/14sd1.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=14 March 2006 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055752/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/14sd1.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> The romantic comedy was a remake of the [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Telugu film]] ''[[Manmadhudu]]'', and she was cast in the title role opposite the actor [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]]. The film proved to be a commercial success.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kumar |first=S.S |title=Ramya in a rush |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/ramya-in-a-rush/article3230859.ece |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=29 September 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085559/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/ramya-in-a-rush/article3230859.ece |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> RG Vijayasarathy of [[Rediff.com]] was appreciative of Padukone's screen presence but added that \"she needs to work on her emotional scenes.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Vijayasarathy |first=R.G. |title=Deepika's Aishwarya is a must watch |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/15aish.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=15 September 2006 |accessdate=3 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055429/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/15aish.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> By the end of 2006, Farah Khan's ''Happy New Year'' was shelved, and Khan had instead cast Padukone for the melodrama ''[[Om Shanti Om]]'' (2007).<ref>{{cite web |title='I was pulling SRK's hair out!' |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/10fchat.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=10 December 2007 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928093128/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/10fchat.htm |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> Set against the backdrop of the [[Bollywood|Hindi film industry]], the film tells the story of a struggling actor in the 1970s who dies soon after witnessing the murder of the woman he loved and is reincarnated to avenge her death. [[Shah Rukh Khan]] starred as the protagonist, and Padukone featured in dual roles of a leading actress of the 1970s, and later, an aspiring actress.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ray |first=Sarit |title=I'm a shy person: Deepika |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-11-02/news-interviews/27986233_1_dream-debut-modelling-deepika-padukone |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=2 November 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194317/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-11-02/news-interviews/27986233_1_dream-debut-modelling-deepika-padukone |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> In preparation for her role, Padukone watched several films of actresses [[Helen (actress)|Helen]] and [[Hema Malini]] to study their body language.<ref>{{cite news |last=Thakur |first=Shweta |title=I saw Hema Malini films for '70s look: Deepika |date=17 November 2007 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-saw-hema-malini-films-for-70s-look-deepika/story-mGPqGR1oyShb3ElcJ7qpDO.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130102931/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-saw-hema-malini-films-for-70s-look-deepika/story-mGPqGR1oyShb3ElcJ7qpDO.html |archivedate=30 January 2016 |df=}}</ref> Her voice was dubbed by the voice artist [[Mona Ghosh Shetty]].<ref name=\"mona dub\">{{cite web |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-01-03/news-interviews/45834895_1_deepika-padukone-dramatic-prowess-and-zest-kochadaiiyaan |title=Why is Deepika's Hindi in Kochadaiiyaan dubbed? |work=The Times of India |date=2 January 2013 |accessdate=3 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105062349/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-01-03/news-interviews/45834895_1_deepika-padukone-dramatic-prowess-and-zest-kochadaiiyaan |archive-date=5 January 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> For one of the songs in the film, \"Dhoom Taana,\u201d Padukone drew upon Indian classical dance, and according to [[Dorling Kindersley]], \"mesmeriz[ed] audiences\" by using ''[[List of mudras (dance)|hasta mudras]]'' (hand gestures).<ref>{{cite book |title=The Book of Dance |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EzKmKyugOjkC&pg=PA113 |date=3 September 2012 |publisher=Dorling Kindersley Limited |isbn=978-1-4093-2237-5 |page=113 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131013030643/http://books.google.com/books?id=EzKmKyugOjkC&pg=PA113 |archivedate=13 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> ''Om Shanti Om'' was a commercial success, and emerged as the [[List of Bollywood films of 2007|highest-grossing film of the year]], with a global revenue of {{INRConvert|1.49|b}}.<ref name=\"top\">{{cite web |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat= |title=Top All Time Worldwide Grossers Updated |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |accessdate=13 October 2013 |date=11 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105215110/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4409&nCat= |archivedate=5 November 2013}}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of the entertainment portal [[Bollywood Hungama]] opined that she had \"all it takes to be a top star\", and she was awarded with the [[Filmfare Best Female Debut Award]] and received her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] nomination.<ref>{{cite web |last=Adarsh |first=Taran |title=Movie Review: Om Shanti Om |date=7 November 2007 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54373 |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=18 December 2007 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBYXxYy?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54373 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"heroine\">{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/top-actresses-of-bollywood-ever/9/7051.html#photo35 |title=Top heroines of Bollywood |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=10 May 2013 |work=India Today |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwC4LXB6?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/top-actresses-of-bollywood-ever/9/7051.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Bollywood Hungama reported that the success of ''Om Shanti Om'' proved a [[breakthrough role|breakthrough]] for her.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Exploring the Box Office journey of Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2013 Part 1 |date=2 August 2013 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBdY9Zu?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Deepika Padukone at an event.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|alt=Deepika Padukone is sitting on a chair and smiling at the camera|Padukone at a promotional event for ''[[Lafangey Parindey]]'' in 2010]]\n\nPadukone next played the role of one of star [[Ranbir Kapoor]]'s love interests in [[Yash Raj Films]]' romantic comedy ''[[Bachna Ae Haseeno]]'' (2008). The film was a financial success,<ref>{{cite web |title=Bachna Ae Haseeno scores at box office |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/18box.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=20 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517150653/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/18box.htm |archivedate=17 May 2015 |df=}}</ref> but [[Namrata Joshi]] of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' wrote that Padukone's performance was disappointing; \"She is mannequin-like and utterly lacks fire and zing.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Joshi |first=Namrata |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?238292 |title=Movie Review: Bachna Ae Haseeno |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=1 September 2008 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927152352/http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?238292 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Her first release of 2009 came alongside [[Akshay Kumar]] in [[Nikhil Advani]]'s [[Kung fu film|kung fu]] comedy ''[[Chandni Chowk To China]]'', in which she portrayed dual roles of Indian-Chinese twin sisters. Produced by [[Warner Bros.]], it had one of the widest international releases given to an Indian film.<ref>{{cite news |last=Anderson |first=Jason |title=Chandni Chowk to China: Kung fusion hustle |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2009/01/16/chandni_chowk_to_china_kung_fusion_hustle.html |work=[[Toronto Star]] |date=16 January 2009 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012104208/http://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2009/01/16/chandni_chowk_to_china_kung_fusion_hustle.html |archivedate=12 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> Padukone learned [[jujutsu]] and performed her own stunts.<ref>{{cite web |title=Deepika's unbelievable stunt! |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2008/nov/26slid1-deepika-unbelievable-stunt.htm?zcc=rl |publisher=Rediff.com |date=26 November 2008 |accessdate=3 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611083353/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2008/nov/26slid1-deepika-unbelievable-stunt.htm?zcc=rl |archivedate=11 June 2014 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lalwani |first=Vickeya |title=Yes, I'm dating Ranbir: Deepika |date=15 March 2008 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-03-15/news-interviews/27772143_1_action-film-deepika-ranbir-yash-raj |work=The Times of India |accessdate=3 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012195823/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-03-15/news-interviews/27772143_1_action-film-deepika-ranbir-yash-raj |archive-date=12 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite the hype, ''Chandni Chowk To China'' was a financial failure, failing to recoup its {{INRConvert|800|m}} budget.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=348&catName=TGlmZXRpbWUgV29ybGR3aWRlIEluIFVTICQ= |title=Top Lifetime Grossers Worldwide (US $) |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=11 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602093609/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU%3D |archivedate=2 June 2013 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Sharma |first=Amit |last2=Verma Ambwani |first2=Meenakshi |title=Chandni Chowk to China crosses Rs 33 cr at local box office |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-01-20/news/27650181_1_domestic-box-office-bollywood-film-kinng |work=[[The Economic Times]] |date=20 January 2009 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305091941/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-01-20/news/27650181_1_domestic-box-office-bollywood-film-kinng |archivedate=5 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> Bollywood Hungama reported that the success of ''Om Shanti Om'' proved a [[breakthrough role|breakthrough]] for Padukone.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Exploring the Box Office journey of Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2013 Part 1 |date=2 August 2013 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBdY9Zu?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Following an [[item number]] (for a song called \"Love Mera Hit Hit\") in the drama ''[[Billu]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.in.msn.com/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=3034274&page=4 |title=Item Number in 'Billoo Barber' |publisher=[[MSN]] |date=6 January 2009 |accessdate=2 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314143005/http://entertainment.in.msn.com/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=3034274&page=4 |archivedate=14 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> she appeared alongside [[Saif Ali Khan]] in the romantic drama ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' from the writer-director [[Imtiaz Ali (director)|Imtiaz Ali]]. The film documented the changing value of relationships among the youth and had Padukone play the part of Meera Pandit, a head-strong [[career woman]]. With a worldwide gross of {{INRConvert|1.2|b}}, ''Love Aaj Kal'' proved to be the [[List of Bollywood films of 2009|third highest-grossing film of 2009]].<ref name=\"top\" /> Aniruddha Guha of ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' said that Padukone \"delivers the best of her four performances so far\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Guha |first=Aniruddha |title=Review: Love Aaj Kal is the perfect date movie |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/review-review-love-aaj-kal-is-the-perfect-date-movie-1278796 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=31 July 2009 |accessdate=16 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106100802/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/review-review-love-aaj-kal-is-the-perfect-date-movie-1278796 |archivedate=6 January 2014 |df=}}</ref> At the [[55th Filmfare Awards]] Padukone received a nomination for Best Actress.<ref name=\"bollywoodhungama1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/725/ |title=Nominations for 55th Idea Filmfare Awards 2009 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=27 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020180943/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/725/ |archivedate=20 October 2014 |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone had five film releases in 2010. Her first role was in the psychological thriller ''[[Karthik Calling Karthik]]'', where Padukone was cast as the supportive girlfriend of a depressed man (played by [[Farhan Akhtar]]). Derek Elley of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' found the film to be \"thinly plotted\" but considered \"the uncomplicated ingenuousness of Padukone\" to be the film's highlight.<ref>{{cite news |last=Elley |first=Derek |title=Review: \"Karthik Calling Karthik\" |url=https://variety.com/2010/film/reviews/karthik-calling-karthik-1117942367/ |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=8 March 2010 |accessdate=16 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130605055907/http://variety.com/2010/film/reviews/karthik-calling-karthik-1117942367/ |archivedate=5 June 2013 |df=}}</ref> Commercially, the film performed poorly.<ref name=\"bo2010\">{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=318&catName=MjAxMA== |title=Box Office 2010 |publisher=Box office India |accessdate=14 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014062657/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=318&catName=MjAxMA%3D%3D |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref> Her most financially profitable film that year was [[Sajid Khan]]'s {{INRConvert|1.15|b}}-grossing comedy film ''[[Housefull (2010 film)|Housefull]]'' in which she featured alongside an [[ensemble cast]] headlined by Akshay Kumar.<ref name=\"top\" /> [[Raja Sen]] described the film as a \"festival of bad acting\" and attributed Padukone's poor performance to her \"plasticky expressions.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Gags that'll make you gag |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-housefull-is-painful/20100430.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012003148/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-housefull-is-painful/20100430.htm |archivedate=12 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> \n\n[[Pradeep Sarkar]]'s drama ''[[Lafangey Parindey]]'' (2010) starred Padukone as a blind girl determined to win a skating competition. In preparation, she observed the interactions of blind people and rehearsed scenes while blindfolded.<ref>{{cite news |title=To play a blind dancer was very challenging: Deepika Padukone |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/to-play-a-blind-dancer-was-very-challenging-deepika-padukone/1/106251.html |accessdate=3 September 2013 |work=India Today |date=22 July 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwC8bHIt?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/to-play-a-blind-dancer-was-very-challenging-deepika-padukone/1/106251.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Writing for ''[[The Hindu]]'', Sudhish Kamath was particularly impressed by the \"considerable restraint\" with which she played her part.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/article600437.ece |title=Lafangey Parindey Movie Review |author=Kamath, Sudhish |work=The Hindu |accessdate=28 April 2011 |date=28 August 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220131856/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/article600437.ece |archivedate=20 December 2013 |df=}}</ref> Her next role was opposite [[Imran Khan (Bollywood actor)|Imran Khan]] in the romantic comedy ''[[Break Ke Baad]]''. [[CNN-IBN]]'s [[Rajeev Masand]] found the film to be \"watchable largely for the performance of its leading lady.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Masand |first=Rajeev |title=Masand: Break Ke Baad is an engaging film |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-break-ke-baad-is-an-engaging-film/135956-8-66.html |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |date=16 December 2010 |accessdate=8 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009233651/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-break-ke-baad-is-an-engaging-film/135956-8-66.html |archivedate=9 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> Padukone's final release of 2010 was [[Ashutosh Gowarikar]]'s [[Historical drama film|period film]] ''[[Khelein Hum Jee Jaan Sey]]'' opposite [[Abhishek Bachchan]]. Based on the book ''[[Do and Die]]'', the film is a retelling of the 1930 [[Chittagong armoury raid]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/first-look-deepika-in-khelein-hum-jee-jaan-sey/20100519.htm |title=First look: Deepika in ''Khelein Hum Jee Jaan Sey'' |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=27 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012033209/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/first-look-deepika-in-khelein-hum-jee-jaan-sey/20100519.htm |archivedate=12 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> Bachchan featured as the revolutionary leader [[Surya Sen]] and Padukone played [[Kalpana Dutta]], his confidante.<ref>{{cite news |last=Mukherjee |first=Roshni |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-02/news-interviews/28264661_1_period-thriller-deepika-padukone-kalpana-dutta |title=Working with Ashu sir is an achievement: Deepika |work=The Times of India |date=2 December 2010 |accessdate=10 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012042232/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-02/news-interviews/28264661_1_period-thriller-deepika-padukone-kalpana-dutta |archive-date=12 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Padukone said that she was unable to research her role as there was very little information on Dutta and relied on Gowarikar's direction.<ref>{{cite web |title=`Khelein Hum` no less glamorous than any of my films: Deepika |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/khelein-hum-no-less-glamorous-than-any-of-my-films-deepika_76567.html |publisher=Zee News |date=29 November 2010 |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003203240/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/khelein-hum-no-less-glamorous-than-any-of-my-films-deepika_76567.html |archivedate=3 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> It did not perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bad times continue at the box office |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/bad-times-continue-at-the-box-office/20101213.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025121346/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/bad-times-continue-at-the-box-office/20101213.htm |archivedate=25 October 2012 |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone began 2011 with an item number in [[Rohan Sippy]]'s ''[[Dum Maaro Dum (film)|Dum Maaro Dum]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-04/news-interviews/28359126_1_deepika-padukone-lyrics-rohan-sippy |title=Deepika's Dum Maro Dum with a twist |work=The Times of India |accessdate=27 April 2011 |date=4 February 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523184302/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-04/news-interviews/28359126_1_deepika-padukone-lyrics-rohan-sippy |archive-date=23 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> She referred to it as \"the wildest song any actress has done;\" the song's sexual content attracted controversy including a court case for indecency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sahgal |first=Geety |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/its-the-wildest-song-any-actress-has-done-deepika/777015/ |title=It's the wildest song any actress has done: Deepika |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=27 April 2011 |date=16 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222155407/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/its-the-wildest-song-any-actress-has-done-deepika/777015/ |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/case-against-dum-maaro-dum-for-indecency-news-national-leswuobjjgf.html |title=Case against 'Dum Maaro Dum' for indecency |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=27 April 2011 |date=18 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110419180348/http://www.sify.com/movies/case-against-dum-maaro-dum-for-indecency-news-national-leswuobjjgf.html |archivedate=19 April 2011 |df=}}</ref> Her next film was [[Prakash Jha]]'s socio-political drama ''[[Aarakshan]]'', which dealt with [[Reservation in India|caste-based reservations in India]]. Trade journalists had high expectations for the film which ultimately flopped at the box office.<ref>{{cite web |title=Will Aarakshan draw in the crowds? |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/will-aarakshan-draw-in-the-crowds/20110801.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203184214/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/will-aarakshan-draw-in-the-crowds/20110801.htm |archivedate=3 February 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=It's raining flops at the box office |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/raining-flops-at-box-office/20110919.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429131112/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/raining-flops-at-box-office/20110919.htm |archivedate=29 April 2012 |df=}}</ref> Critical reaction was largely negative, though [[Pratim D. Gupta]] mentioned Padukone as the most \"refreshing thing\" about it.<ref>{{cite news |title=Aarakshan loses plot after second half |date=12 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/aarakshan-loses-plot-after-second-half/story-MxH4SLWdr8jzU3Jr2lUFUP.html |accessdate=13 August 2012 |work=Hindustan Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203133341/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/aarakshan-loses-plot-after-second-half/story-MxH4SLWdr8jzU3Jr2lUFUP.html |archivedate=3 February 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Gupta, Pratim D. |title=Aarakshan&nbsp;\u2013 Film Review |date=13 August 2011 |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1110813/jsp/entertainment/story_14372488.jsp |accessdate=13 August 2012 |work=The Telegraph |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102175641/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1110813/jsp/entertainment/story_14372488.jsp |archivedate=2 November 2012 |df=}}</ref> Her final appearance that year was in Rohit Dhawan's comedy-drama ''[[Desi Boyz]]'' alongside Akshay Kumar, [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]] and [[Chitrangada Singh]], a role that failed to propel her career forward.<ref>{{cite web |title=Review: Desi Boyz |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-desi-boyz-676 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=12 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130917011435/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-desi-boyz-676 |archivedate=17 September 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Exploring the Box Office journey of Deepika Padukone \u2013 Part III |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5360 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=12 August 2013 |accessdate=12 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814144827/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5360 |archivedate=14 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> The series of poorly received films led critics to perceive that Padukone had \"[lost] her sparkle.\"<ref name=\"making of deepika\">{{cite news |last=Pal |first=Chandrima |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-17/news-interviews/40009313_1_deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-deepika-imtiaz-ali |title=The making of Deepika Padukone |accessdate=27 July 2013 |date=17 June 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627020227/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-17/news-interviews/40009313_1_deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-deepika-imtiaz-ali |archive-date=27 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Establishing as a leading lady (2012\u20132015) ===\nPadukone has said that her starring role in the 2012 [[Homi Adajania]]-directed romantic comedy ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' marked a significant turning point in her career.<ref>{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Harneet |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-ranbir-kapoor-excites-me-as-an-actor-costar/1126038/0 |title=Deepika Padukone: Ranbir Kapoor excites me as an actor, co-star |work=The Indian Express |date=7 June 2013 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152538/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-ranbir-kapoor-excites-me-as-an-actor-costar/1126038/0 |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> Raja Sen of Rediff.com opined that she had successfully proved to be a \"stunning girl who can also act.\"<ref name=\"report card 2012\">{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-hows-these-bollywood-actresses-fared-in-2012/20130102.htm#3 |title=Report Card, 2012: How Kat, Kareena, Deepika performed |accessdate=27 July 2013 |date=2 January 2013 |publisher=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508185019/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-hows-these-bollywood-actresses-fared-in-2012/20130102.htm |archivedate=8 May 2013 |df=}}</ref> Set in London, ''Cocktail'' tells the story of a man's relationship with two temperamentally different women{{mdash}}an impulsive party girl (Veronica, played by Padukone) and a submissive [[girl next door]] (Meera, played by [[Diana Penty]]). During the script narration, the producer Dinesh Vijan offered Padukone the choice of which woman to play; she decided on Veronica to expand her horizons as an actress.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/veronica-is-no-meera-deepika-padukone/story-QfD3KilX3eevBOtuKJkznO.html |title=Veronica is no Meera: Deepika |work=Hindustan Times |date=25 May 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808003227/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/veronica-is-no-meera-deepika-padukone/story-QfD3KilX3eevBOtuKJkznO.html |archivedate=8 August 2016 |df=}}</ref> Portraying the role was a creative and physical challenge for her, and to achieve the physical requirements of her character she exercised extensively and followed a rigorous diet.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/playing-veronica-in-cocktail-was-challenging-deepika-padukone/970790/0 |title=Playing Veronica in 'Cocktail' was challenging: Deepika Padukone |work=The Indian Express |date=5 May 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20130811102927/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/playing-veronica-in-cocktail-was-challenging-deepika-padukone/970790/0 |archivedate=11 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/cocktail-deepika-padukone-daina-penty-saif-ali-khan/1/207582.html |title=Was conscious about my look in Cocktail: Deepika |work=India Today |date=11 May 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCBnq5n?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/cocktail-deepika-padukone-daina-penty-saif-ali-khan/1/207582.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Critics were divided in their opinion of the film, but particularly praised Padukone's performance;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-verdict-cocktail-works-but-in-bits/story-cFNQiVGyPXFUTKmsSUSBEN.html |title=Critics verdict: Cocktail works, but in bits |work=Hindustan Times |date=13 July 2013 |accessdate=7 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304122353/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-verdict-cocktail-works-but-in-bits/story-cFNQiVGyPXFUTKmsSUSBEN.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> Devesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' credited her as the \"soul of the film\" and wrote that she \"excels in every scene, whether as a material girl who enjoys sex, drugs and rock and roll or as the jealousy ridden girl out to destroy herself.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Sharma |first=Devesh |title=Movie Review: Cocktail |url=http://www.filmfare.com/reviews/movie-review-cocktail-840.html |work=[[Filmfare]] |date=13 May 2012 |accessdate=29 June 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwAglv9h?url=http://www.filmfare.com/reviews/movie-review-cocktail-840.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> ''Cocktail'' earned Padukone Best Actress nominations at several award ceremonies, including Filmfare, [[Screen Award|Screen]], and [[IIFA Awards|IIFA]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/1856 |title=Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2014 Awards |accessdate=5 September 2013 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCqDjGs?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/1856 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The film proved to be a box office success as well.<ref>{{cite web |title=Box Office Earnings 10/08/12 \u2013 16/08/12 |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=earnings |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=9 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825191030/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=earnings |archivedate=25 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ranveer-Deepika at Ram Leela screening.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1|alt=Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone smiling for the camera|Padukone and [[Ranveer Singh]] at an event for ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' in 2013. She was awarded her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] for her performance in the film.]]\n\nIn 2013, Padukone had established herself as a leading actress of Hindi cinema by featuring in four of the [[List of Bollywood films of 2013|top-grossing productions of the year]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone races to the top as top actress in Bollywood |last=Tanwar |first=Sarita |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-races-to-the-top-as-top-actress-in-bollywood-1858364 |accessdate=8 July 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220024053/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-races-to-the-top-as-top-actress-in-bollywood-1858364 |archivedate=20 December 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"top2\">{{cite news |last=Goyal |first=Divya |title=Deepika Padukone lucky fourth time with 'Ram-Leela' |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-lucky-fourth-time-with-ramleela/1196368/ |accessdate=4 December 2013 |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=18 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152120/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-lucky-fourth-time-with-ramleela/1196368/ |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> She collaborated with Saif Ali Khan for the fourth time in [[Abbas-Mustan]]'s ''[[Race 2]]'', an ensemble action thriller that served as a sequel to ''[[Race (2008 film)|Race]]'' (2008). The film received predominantly negative reviews,<ref>{{cite news |title=Critics report: Race 2 not worth it |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-report-race-2-not-worth-it/story-QhSKezAX1YGfNcpJEyKCTJ.html |accessdate=9 March 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=25 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304081019/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-report-race-2-not-worth-it/story-QhSKezAX1YGfNcpJEyKCTJ.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> but with a total collection of {{INRConvert|1.62|b}}, it proved to be a commercial success.<ref name=\"worldwide10\">{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |title=Worldwide Top Ten 2013 |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=12 December 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104212753/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |archivedate=4 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"cloud9\">{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone on cloud 9, Chennai Express, Ram-Leela, Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani, Race 2 big hits of 2013 |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/happy-birthday-deepika-padukone-on-cloud-9-chennai-express-ramleela-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-race-2-big-hits-of-2013/1215689?rhheader |accessdate=26 January 2014 |newspaper=The Financial Express |date=5 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201194525/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/happy-birthday-deepika-padukone-on-cloud-9-chennai-express-ramleela-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-race-2-big-hits-of-2013/1215689?rhheader |archivedate=1 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> [[Ayan Mukerji]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]'' was Padukone's next film release. Co-starring opposite Ranbir Kapoor, she was cast as Naina Talwar, a \"shy wallflower,\" which marked a departure from the glamorous characters that she had a reputation for portraying.<ref name=\"party girl\">{{cite news |last=KBR |first=Upala |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-party-girl-deepika-padukone-gets-serious-1819664 |title=Party girl Deepika Padukone gets serious |accessdate=17 August 2013 |date=7 April 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141014003716/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-party-girl-deepika-padukone-gets-serious-1819664 |archivedate=14 October 2014 |df=}}</ref> Raja Sen thought that the film \"lacked a good story\" but added that Padukone \"acts within herself and eschews exaggeration, and the results are impressive&nbsp;... This may be her most self-aware performance so far\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Review: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani disappoints |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-disappoints/20130531.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=31 May 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606072818/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-disappoints/20130531.htm |archivedate=6 June 2013 |df=}}</ref> The pairing of Padukone with her former boyfriend was anticipated,<ref>{{cite news |title=Younger generation should learn from Ranbir & Deepika: Ayan |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-01/news-interviews/39674323_1_ayan-mukerji-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone |author=Risbood, Vaibhavi |work=The Times of India |date=1 June 2013 |accessdate=12 July 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618173542/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-01/news-interviews/39674323_1_ayan-mukerji-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone |archive-date=18 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the film emerged as a major commercial success.<ref name=\"worldwide10\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani is Ranbir Kapoor, Deepika Padukone's biggest hit |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-is-ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-s-biggest-hit/1127672/ |accessdate=1 July 2013 |work=The Indian Express |date=1 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152212/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-is-ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-s-biggest-hit/1127672/ |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> Her next appearance was opposite Shah Rukh Khan in [[Rohit Shetty]]'s action-comedy film ''[[Chennai Express]]'', as a [[Tamil people|Tamil girl]] on the run from her father (a local [[boss (crime)|don]]), which required that she adopt a Tamil accent. Critical opinion on her accent was mixed,<ref>{{cite news |title=Not spoofing South India in Chennai Express: Deepika Padukone |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/not-spoofing-south-india-in-chennai-express-says-deepika-padukone/1/298317.html |accessdate=13 August 2013 |work=India Today |date=6 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCFXjFR?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/not-spoofing-south-india-in-chennai-express-says-deepika-padukone/1/298317.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> but her performance received praise;<ref name=\"high\">{{cite news |last=Uniyal |first=Parmita |title=Deepika Padukone rides on a high graph express |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-gets-critical-acclaim-rides-on-a-high-graph-express/article1-1107578.aspx |accessdate=13 August 2013 |work=Hindustan Times |date=13 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101105157/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-gets-critical-acclaim-rides-on-a-high-graph-express/article1-1107578.aspx |archivedate=1 January 2014 |df=}}</ref> film critic Aseem Chhabra wrote, \"Padukone is delightful in the film{{mdash}}beautiful, smiling, and often a lot more playful and funny than Khan.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Chhabra |first=Aseem |title=Aseem Chhabra's Chennai Express Review: Mindless but entertaining |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/aseem-chhabras-chennai-express-review-mindless-but-entertaining/20130809.htm |publisher=Rediff |date=9 August 2013 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811184158/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/aseem-chhabras-chennai-express-review-mindless-but-entertaining/20130809.htm |archivedate=11 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> ''Chennai Express'' earned  over {{INRConvert|3.95|b}} to emerge as one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]].<ref name=\"box office\">{{cite web |title=Top Worldwide Grossers All Time |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/worldwide-total-gross.php |publisher=Box Office India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180107113404/http://boxofficeindia.com/worldwide-total-gross.php |archivedate=7 January 2018 |accessdate=5 February 2018 |url-status=live |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone next played opposite [[Ranveer Singh]] in ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'', an adaptation of the [[Shakespearean tragedy]] of ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'' from director [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]. Her role was Leela, a [[Gujarati people|Gujarati girl]] based on the character of [[Juliet]].<ref>{{cite news |title=First look Ram Leela: Meet Romeo Ranveer and Juliet Deepika |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |work=India Today |accessdate=16 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCOFmHR?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Initially titled ''Ram-Leela'', the film's title was changed after a court case was registered against Bhansali, Padukone, and Singh for \"offending the religious sentiments\" of the Hindu community by showcasing sex and violence under a title that referred to the life of [[Rama]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Sura |first=Ajay |title=Controversy over 'Ram Leela': HC stays arrest of Bhansali, Ranveer and Deepika |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-11-14/india/44073111_1_ram-leela-ranveer-singh-delhi-high-court |accessdate=16 November 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=14 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131117095053/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-11-14/india/44073111_1_ram-leela-ranveer-singh-delhi-high-court |archive-date=17 November 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' released among protests across several states in India, but was generally well received by critics.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ram-Leela faces protest in several states |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-ram-leela-faces-protest-in-several-states-1919790 |accessdate=16 November 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131118080509/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-ram-leela-faces-protest-in-several-states-1919790 |archivedate=18 November 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Uniyal |first=Parmita |title=Movie review: Bhansali's Ram-leela is his best ever, say critics |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/story-cdj9US9WMi2M58gcg56YNI.html |accessdate=15 November 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304070929/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/story-cdj9US9WMi2M58gcg56YNI.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> Meena Iyer of ''The Times of India'' mentioned Padukone as \"breathtaking\", and writing for ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'', [[Khalid Mohamed]] concluded that \"it's Deepika Padukone whom the film belongs to. Looking drop dead gorgeous and going at her part with a wallop, she's the prime asset of ''Ram-Leela''.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Iyer |first=Meena |title=Ram-Leela |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Ram-Leela/movie-review/25770699.cms |accessdate=15 November 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=14 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115000038/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/ram-leela/movie-review/25770699.cms |archivedate=15 November 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mohamed |first=Khalid |title='Ram-Leela' Review: The good, the bard and the beautiful |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131115/entertainment-movie-reviews/article/ram-leela-review-good-bard-and-beautiful |accessdate=16 November 2013 |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=16 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131116102722/http://deccanchronicle.com/131115/entertainment-movie-reviews/article/ram-leela-review-good-bard-and-beautiful |archivedate=16 November 2013 |df=}}</ref> Her performances in ''Chennai Express'' and ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' won her several awards,<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika is toast of this award season |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/deepika-padukone-is-toast-of-this-award-season/1/343781.html |accessdate=16 February 2014 |work=India Today |date=17 February 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140216064856/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/deepika-padukone-is-toast-of-this-award-season/1/343781.html |archivedate=16 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> including the [[Screen Award for Best Actress]] for both films and the Filmfare Award for Best Actress for the latter.<ref>{{cite web |title=Winners of 20th Annual Life OK Screen Awards |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6026 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=14 January 2014 |accessdate=17 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116181505/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6026 |archivedate=16 January 2014 |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"ff13\">{{cite web |title=Filmfare Awards 2014: Deepika Padukone wins Best Actress award, Farhan Akhtar Best Actor |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-2014-deepika-padukone-wins-best-actress-award-farhan-akhtar-best-actor/447639-8-66.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |date=25 January 2014 |accessdate=25 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125110704/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-2014-deepika-padukone-wins-best-actress-award-farhan-akhtar-best-actor/447639-8-66.html |archivedate=25 January 2014 |df=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Padukone featured opposite [[Rajinikanth]] in the [[Tamil cinema|Tamil film]] ''[[Kochadaiiyaan]]'', a period drama that was shot using [[motion capture]] technology.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/kochadaiiyaan-released-nationwide-rajinikanth-turns-movemaking-pioneer-in-india/1253639 |title='Kochadaiiyaan' released nationwide, Rajinikanth turns moviemaking pioneer in India |work=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]] |date=23 March 2014 |agency=Press Trust of India |accessdate=23 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140523230850/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/kochadaiiyaan-released-nationwide-rajinikanth-turns-movemaking-pioneer-in-india/1253639 |archivedate=23 May 2014 |df=}}</ref> She was paid {{INRConvert|30|m}} for two days worth of work in it.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/deepika-padukone-films-rajinikanth-s-kochadaiiyaan-for-two-days-only_143262.html |title=Deepika Padukone shoots Rajinikanth\u2019s `Kochadaiiyaan` for two days only! |publisher=Zee News |date=23 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926173744/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/deepika-padukone-films-rajinikanth-s-kochadaiiyaan-for-two-days-only_143262.html |archivedate=26 September 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-gets-3-cr-for-2-day-shoot-in-Rajnis-film/articleshow/22508894.cms |title=Deepika gets 3 cr for 2 day shoot in Rajni\u2019s film? |work=The Times of India |date=12 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130912235545/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-gets-3-cr-for-2-day-shoot-in-Rajnis-film/articleshow/22508894.cms |archivedate=12 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> In Homi Adajania's praised satire ''[[Finding Fanny]]'', Padukone played a young widow who takes a road trip with her dysfunctional friends (played by [[Arjun Kapoor]], [[Naseeruddin Shah]], [[Dimple Kapadia]] and [[Pankaj Kapur]]) in search of a woman named Fanny.<ref>{{cite news |last=Mehta |first=Ankita |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/finding-fanny-movie-review-must-watch-film-brilliant-performances-608764 |title='Finding Fanny' Movie Review: Must Watch Film with Brilliant Performances |date=10 September 2014 |work=[[International Business Times]] |accessdate=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140911015405/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/finding-fanny-movie-review-must-watch-film-brilliant-performances-608764 |archivedate=11 September 2014 |df=}}</ref> The film was screened at the [[19th Busan International Film Festival]];<ref>{{cite news |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |title=Finding Fanny selected for Busan Film Festival |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Finding-Fanny-selected-for-Busan-Film-Festival/articleshow/41878021.cms |accessdate=12 September 2014 |work=The Times of India |date=6 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140909044509/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Finding-Fanny-selected-for-Busan-Film-Festival/articleshow/41878021.cms |archivedate=9 September 2014 |df=}}</ref> critic Anuj Kumar of ''[[The Hindu]]'' wrote that Padukone successfully \"takes off the fineries of Bollywood and you can sense the freedom from baggage in her performance\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Kumar |first=Anuj |title=Finding fanny: Lost and found |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/finding-fanny-review/article6404665.ece |work=The Hindu |accessdate=29 November 2014 |date=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205215445/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/finding-fanny-review/article6404665.ece |archivedate=5 December 2014 |df=}}</ref> Later that year, she starred opposite Shah Rukh Khan for the third time in Farah Khan's renewal of ''Happy New Year''. She played a bar dancer who trains a group of underachievers for a dance competition. Sanjukta Sharma of ''[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]'' found her role to be of minimal importance that required her only to be \"a pretty thing to be laughed at and pitied\", but the film became one of her most successful, earning over {{INRConvert|3.4|b}} worldwide.<ref name=\"box office\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Sharma |first=Sanjukta |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/RbQFYNOCmIXFirlKS1t0kI/Film-Review--Happy-New-Year.html |title=Film Review Happy New Year |date=4 September 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2014 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024170656/http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/RbQFYNOCmIXFirlKS1t0kI/Film-Review--Happy-New-Year.html |archivedate=24 October 2014 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Deepika Padukone promoting Bajirao Mastani (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A headshot shot of Deepika Padukone|Padukone at an event for ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' in 2015]]\n\nFollowing an appearance in Homi Adajania's online video on [[Feminism in India|feminism]], entitled ''My Choice'',<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone: Bollywood actress urges women to own their 'choice' over marriage, sex and sexuality |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/deepika-padukone-bollywood-actress-urges-women-to-own-their-choice-over-marriage-sex-and-sexuality-10145843.html |work=[[The Independent]] |date=31 March 2015 |accessdate=1 April 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331183715/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/deepika-padukone-bollywood-actress-urges-women-to-own-their-choice-over-marriage-sex-and-sexuality-10145843.html |archivedate=31 March 2015 |df=}}</ref> Padukone took on the role of a headstrong [[Bengali people|Bengali]] architect who cares for her hypochondriac father (played by Amitabh Bachchan), in [[Shoojit Sircar]]'s comedy-drama ''[[Piku]]'' (2015). She was drawn to the depiction of a realistic father-daughter bond, which she thought was rare in Hindi cinema.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ratnam |first=Dhamini |title=Objectifying me, that is not done: Deepika Padukone |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |work=Mint |date=27 December 2014 |accessdate=25 January 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509232711/http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |archivedate=9 May 2016}}</ref> Reviews for the film were positive;<ref>{{cite web |last=Mehta |first=Ankita |title='Piku' Review Roundup: A Film that's all Heart |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/piku-review-roundup-simple-classy-charming-film-631700 |work=International Business Times |date=7 May 2015 |accessdate=10 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509200624/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/piku-review-roundup-simple-classy-charming-film-631700 |archivedate=9 May 2015 |df=}}</ref> Tanmaya Nanda of ''[[Business Standard]]'' praised the film's feminist tone, and wrote that Padukone proves \"what she is capable of when given something more to do than look pretty and be the crazy-dance girl at parties\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Nanda |first=Tanmaya |title=Film Review: Piku is a delightfully brilliant film |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |work=[[Business Standard]] |date=8 May 2015 |accessdate=9 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509232711/http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |archivedate=9 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> NDTV's Saibal Chatterjee opined that she \"holds ''Piku'' together with a restrained star turn\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |title=Piku Movie Review |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/piku-movie-review-1124 |publisher=NDTV |date=8 May 2015 |accessdate=10 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150510190128/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/piku-movie-review-1124 |archivedate=10 May 2015 |df=}}</ref> With a worldwide gross of over {{INRConvert|1.40|b}}, ''Piku'' emerged as a box office hit, and garnered Padukone several awards, including second Best Actress awards at Filmfare and Screen.<ref name=\"filmfare16\">{{cite news |title=Victory dance for Team 'Bajirao Mastani' at the Filmfare Awards |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Victory-dance-for-Team-Bajirao-Mastani-at-the-Filmfare-Awards/articleshow/50604444.cms |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=The Times of India |date=17 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121183819/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Victory-dance-for-Team-Bajirao-Mastani-at-the-Filmfare-Awards/articleshow/50604444.cms |archivedate=21 January 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ghosh |first=Raya |title=Screen Awards 2016: Complete List of Winners |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/screen-awards-2016-complete-list-of-winners-1263815 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=9 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110051251/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/screen-awards-2016-complete-list-of-winners-1263815 |archivedate=10 January 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n\nLater in 2015, Padukone played the part of a businessperson who helps Ranbir Kapoor's character overcome his conflicts in Imtiaz Ali's romantic drama ''[[Tamasha (2015 film)|Tamasha]]''. Despite poor financial returns, Sukanya Verma of Rediff.com named Padukone's performance as the best by an actress that year, writing that she \"is so potent in ''Tamasha'', it's almost as if you can hear her heartbeat across the screen\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Khuranaa |first=Amann |title=Deepika Padukone reacts to Tamasha's box-office failure |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-reacts-to-Tamashas-box-office-failure/articleshow/50186402.cms |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=The Times of India |date=15 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151218163236/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-reacts-to-Tamashas-box-office-failure/articleshow/50186402.cms |archivedate=18 December 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Verma |first=Sukanya |title=Sukanya Verma's Best Actresses of 2015 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sukanya-vermas-best-actresses-of-2015/20151224.htm |date=24 December 2015 |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=24 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123175703/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sukanya-vermas-best-actresses-of-2015/20151224.htm |archivedate=23 January 2016 |df=}}</ref> In her final release of 2015, Padukone reunited with Sanjay Leela Bhansali and Ranveer Singh in ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'', a historical drama about a tragic extramarital affair. Singh was cast as the [[maratha]] general [[Bajirao I]], while [[Priyanka Chopra]] and Padukone featured as his first and second wife, respectively. To play the warrior-princess [[Mastani]], Padukone learnt sword-fighting, horse-riding, and the martial art form of [[kalaripayattu]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Awaasthi |first=Kavita |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-learn-sword-fighting-for-bajirao-mastani/story-KUjvxij1mi4pBQyOLkzWrM.html |title=Deepika Padukone to learn sword-fighting for Bajirao Mastani |work=Hindutan Times |date=23 January 2015 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222163238/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-learn-sword-fighting-for-bajirao-mastani/story-KUjvxij1mi4pBQyOLkzWrM.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref> With a revenue of over {{INRConvert|3.5|b}}, ''Bajirao Mastani'' proved to be the [[List of Bollywood films of 2015|fourth highest-grossing Bollywood film of the year]].<ref name=\"box office\" /> [[Anupama Chopra]] found Padukone \"riveting\", but [[Subhash K. Jha]] thought that she was \"way too subtle and silken, and not steely enough\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Chopra |first=Anupama |title=Bajirao Mastani review by Anupama Chopra: Soaring, searing, sumptuous |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/bajirao-mastani-review-by-anupama-chopra-soaring-searing-sumptuous/story-gZmskukJnTmbRtcS15D3XK.html |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=Hindustan Times |date=22 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116085552/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/bajirao-mastani-review-by-anupama-chopra-soaring-searing-sumptuous/story-gZmskukJnTmbRtcS15D3XK.html |archivedate=16 January 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Jha |first=Subhash K. |title=Subhash K Jha speaks about Bajirao Mastani |date=19 December 2015 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9439 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=24 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119175354/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9439 |archivedate=19 January 2016 |df=}}</ref> The film was showcased at the [[International Film Festival of India]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/IP_press_release_2016_Final.pdf |title=Indian Panorama Selections for 47th International Film Festival of India, 2016: Press Release|access-date=25 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112080152/http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/IP_press_release_2016_Final.pdf |archivedate=12 November 2016}}</ref> at the [[61st Filmfare Awards]], ''Bajirao Mastani'' was named [[Filmfare Award for Best Film|Best Film]] and Padukone received her second Best Actress nomination in that year.<ref name=\"filmfare16\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Nominations for the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11809.html |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=Filmfare |date=11 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gO32fdDO?url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11809.html |archivedate=30 March 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n\n=== Professional expansion (2017\u2013present) ===\nThe action film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' (2017), in which Padukone played the lead female role of Serena Unger, opposite [[Vin Diesel]], marked her first project in [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Goyal |first=Divya |title=Deepika Padukone Wraps xXx 3 Shoot and in Such Style |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/hollywood/deepika-padukone-wraps-xxx-3-shoot-and-in-such-style-1405905 |publisher=NDTV |date=13 May 2016 |accessdate=14 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513123136/http://movies.ndtv.com/hollywood/deepika-padukone-wraps-xxx-3-shoot-and-in-such-style-1405905 |archivedate=13 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> Critical reception of the film was mixed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/xxx_return_of_xander_cage |title=xXx: Return of Xander Cage (2017) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119223913/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/xxx_return_of_xander_cage |archivedate=19 January 2017 |df=}}</ref> Tirdad Derakhshani of ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'' termed the film a \"repetitious heap of remarkably tedious CGI-enhanced action scenes\" and thought that Padukone's talent was wasted in it.<ref>{{cite news |last=Derakhshani |first=Tirdad |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/Vin-Diesels-xXx.html |title=Vin Diesel\u2019s \u2018xXx: Return of Xander Cage\u2019: Abysmal, unwatchable, embarrassing |work=[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]] |date=20 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170123172631/http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/Vin-Diesels-xXx.html |archive-date=23 January 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> Conversely, Frank Scheck of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' believed that she had successfully \"outclassed\" Diesel to \"practically [steal] the film\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Scheck |first=Frank |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/xxx-return-xander-review-965998 |title='xXx: Return of Xander Cage': Film Review |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=19 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120024920/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/xxx-return-xander-review-965998 |archivedate=20 January 2017 |df=}}</ref> The film earned over US$345 million worldwide, a majority of which came from the Chinese box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=xxx3.htm |title=xXx: Return of Xander Cage |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=8 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329021315/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=xxx3.htm |archivedate=29 March 2017 |df=}}</ref> Padukone received three nominations at the [[Teen Choice Awards]] and followed it with an item number in the romantic drama ''[[Raabta (film)|Raabta]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominees |title=Teen Choice Awards 2017: See the First Wave of Nominations |last=Ceron |first=Ella |work=[[Teen Vogue]] |date=19 June 2017 |accessdate=20 June 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6rLtVsNex?url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominees |archivedate=20 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Shcherbakova |first=Lisa |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7865210/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominations-second-wave |title=Selena Gomez Leads Second Wave of Teen Choice Awards 2017 Nominations |work=Billboard |date=12 July 2017|access-date=14 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170714060829/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7865210/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominations-second-wave |archivedate=14 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Watch: Deepika Padukone takes flexibility to a new level for dance number in 'Raabta' |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-watch-deepika-padukone-takes-flexibility-to-a-new-level-for-dance-number-in-raabta-2218761 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=1 June 2016 |accessdate=2 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602145415/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-watch-deepika-padukone-takes-flexibility-to-a-new-level-for-dance-number-in-raabta-2218761 |archivedate=2 June 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Deepika Padukone at Chhapaak premiere.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Padukone at the premiere of ''[[Chhapaak]]'' (2020), which marked her first production venture]]\n\nIn 2018, Padukone portrayed [[Rani Padmini|Rani Padmavati]], a [[Rajput]] queen who commits ''[[jauhar]]'' (self-immolation) to protect herself from the [[Muslim]] invader [[Alauddin Khalji|Alauddin Khilji]], in the period drama ''[[Padmaavat]]''; it marked her third collaboration with Bhansali and Singh.<ref>{{cite news |title=It's official! Sanjay Leela Bhansali's Padmavati to release in 2017 |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/its-official-sanjay-leela-bhansalis-padmavati-to-release-in-2017_-16000.html |work=Filmfare |date=10 October 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011140218/http://www.filmfare.com/news/its-official-sanjay-leela-bhansalis-padmavati-to-release-in-2017_-16000.html |archivedate=11 October 2016 |df=}}</ref> She was challenged by the need to convey her character's courage through silence and considered it to be the most emotionally exhausting role of her career.<ref name=\"filmfare17\">{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Raghuvendra |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/the-empress-strikes-back-25241.html |title=Deepika Padukone chats with Filmfare about Padmavati, Ranveer Singh & more in her exclusive interview |date=24 November 2017 |work=Filmfare |accessdate=25 January 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125193654/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/the-empress-strikes-back-25241.html |archivedate=25 January 2018}}</ref> She read history books on the era and researched the various historical depictions of Padmavati.<ref name=\"filmfare17\" /> [[Saffron terror|Right-wing Hindu groups]] speculated that the film portrayed a romantic liaison between Padmavati and Khilji; they protested violently and placed a bounty to behead Padukone and Bhansali.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ray |first=Saptarshi |title=Bounty placed on Bollywood actress' head after Hindu-Muslim film outrage |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=17 November 2017 |accessdate=2 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171118052745/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |archivedate=18 November 2017}}</ref> Following a deferment in release, the film was cleared for exhibition after several modifications were made to it.<ref>{{cite news |title=Padmavati release deferred after protests, Sanjay Leela Bhansali film not to come out on Dec 1 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/padmavati-release-postponed-not-to-come-out-on-december-1/story-AAMT5dPtRloBAmSdqR4NRL.html |accessdate=19 November 2017 |work=Hindustan Times |date=19 November 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119113357/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/padmavati-release-postponed-not-to-come-out-on-december-1/story-AAMT5dPtRloBAmSdqR4NRL.html |archivedate=19 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855 |title=Censor Board Wants \"Padmavati\" Renamed \"Padmavat\", 5 Changes To Film |publisher=NDTV |date=30 December 2017 |accessdate=30 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230133652/https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855 |archivedate=30 December 2017}}</ref> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' criticised the film's glorification of ''jauhar'', but credited Padukone for managing to \"eke something out of the stereotype-ridden writing\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Vetticad |first=Anna MM |title=Padmaavat movie review: Bhansali couches regressive, opportunistic messaging in exhausting visual splendour |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/padmaavat-padmavati-padmavat-movie-review-bhansali-couches-regressive-opportunistic-messaging-in-exhausting-visual-splendour-4317153.html |website=[[Firstpost]] |date=24 January 2018 |accessdate=24 January 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124090649/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/padmaavat-padmavati-padmavat-movie-review-bhansali-couches-regressive-opportunistic-messaging-in-exhausting-visual-splendour-4317153.html |archivedate=24 January 2018}}</ref> With an estimated budget of {{INRConvert|2|b}}, ''Padmaavat'' is [[List of most expensive Indian films#Hindi|one of the most expensive Hindi films]], and with earnings of {{INRConvert|5.45|b}}, it is Padukone's highest-grossing release and one of Indian cinema's biggest grossers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469 |title=Padmavati Being Aimed For A February Release |publisher=Box Office India |date=8 December 2017 |accessdate=8 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208231459/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469 |archivedate=8 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881 |title=Worldwide Alltime : Padmaavat 7th \u2013 Baaghi 2 22nd |accessdate=26 April 2018 |date=26 April 2018 |publisher=Box Office India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426213042/https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881 |archive-date=26 April 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> She received another Best Actress nomination at Filmfare.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |title=Nominations for the 64th Vimal Filmfare Awards 2019 |work=Filmfare |date=12 March 2019 |access-date=13 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190316052927/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |archive-date=16 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFollowing the success of ''Padmaavat'', Padukone took some time off work to focus on her home and family.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chaurasia |first=Ankita |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-karan-johar-was-only-joking-when-he-said-ill-make-a-good-producer/articleshow/72985903.cms|title=Deepika Padukone: Karan Johar was only joking when he said I'll make a good producer |work=Mumbai Mirror |date=27 December 2019 |access-date=9 January 2020 }}</ref> In 2018, she formed her own company, named Ka Productions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bhattacharya |first=Roshmilla |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-turns-producer-for-meghna-gulzars-next-directorial/articleshow/66077252.cms |title=Deepika Padukone turns producer for Meghna Gulzar's next directorial |work=Mumbai Mirror |date=5 October 2018 |access-date=5 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005052344/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-turns-producer-for-meghna-gulzars-next-directorial/articleshow/66077252.cms |archive-date=5 October 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Her first production venture came with ''[[Chhapaak]]'' (2020), a drama by [[Meghna Gulzar]], in which she starred as an [[acid attack]] survivor (based on [[Laxmi Agarwal]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/deepikas-next-chhapaak-is-a-story-of-undying-human-spirit/articleshow/68549587.cms|title=Deepika\u2019s next 'Chhapaak' is a story of undying human spirit|newspaper=The Times Of India|date=25 March 2019|accessdate=25 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325025119/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/deepikas-next-chhapaak-is-a-story-of-undying-human-spirit/articleshow/68549587.cms|archive-date=25 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She found it taxing to film in extreme heat wearing prosthetic makeup on her face, and considered it to be the most physically challenging role of her career.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ghosh |first=Devarsi |url=https://scroll.in/reel/948467/deepika-padukone-on-chhapaak-this-was-my-most-physically-challenging-film|title=Deepika Padukone on \u2018Chhapaak\u2019: \u2018This was my most physically challenging film\u2019 |website=[[Scroll.in]] |date=4 January 2020 |access-date=5 January 2020 }}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' credited her for \"not just putting the focus on the ravaged-skin-with a missing ear-and-nostril, but reflecting a mix of pain, anger, resignation, and finally, arriving at some kind of resolution\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Gupta |first=Shubhra |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/chhapaak-movie-review-rating-deepika-padukone-6207416/|title=Chhapaak movie review: Deepika Padukone delivers a solid, realised performance |work=The Indian Express |date=9 January 2020 |access-date=9 January 2020 }}</ref> Teo Bugbee of ''[[The New York Times]]'' added that \"Padukone is by turns inquisitive, watchful and serene but never maudlin\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Bugbee |first=Teo |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/10/movies/chhapaak-review.html|title=Chhapaak Review: Life and Activism After an Acid Attack |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=10 January 2020 |access-date=10 January 2020 }}</ref> It did not perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jha|first=Subhash K.|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/much-lauded-deepika-padukone-starrer-chhapaak-crashes-box-office-trade-experts-analyse/|title=The much lauded Deepika Padukone starrer Chhapaak crashes at the box office, trade experts analyse|website=Bollywood Hungama|date=18 January 2020|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nPadukone's next production venture will be ''[[83 (film)|83]]'', a sports film about India's victory at the [[1983 Cricket World Cup]], starring Ranveer Singh as [[Kapil Dev]], in which she will also take on the role of Dev's wife, Romi.<ref>{{cite web |author=Mishra, Shambhavi |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/deepika-padukone-wants-to-spend-time-with-kapil-dev-s-wife-romi-for-83-prep-details-here/434039 |title=Deepika Padukone wants to spend time with Kapil Dev\u2019s wife Romi for \u201883 prep - details here |website=Times Now |date=10 June 2019 |access-date=10 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610061110/https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/deepika-padukone-wants-to-spend-time-with-kapil-dev-s-wife-romi-for-83-prep-details-here/434039 |archive-date=10 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She has committed to star alongside [[Siddhant Chaturvedi]] and [[Ananya Panday]] in [[Shakun Batra]]'s as-yet untitled romantic drama, and to portray [[Draupadi]] in a retelling of the ''[[Mahabharata]]'' from her character's perspective, which she will also be producing.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-teams-up-with-ananya-panday-sidhant-chaturvedi-for-shakun-batra-s-relationship-drama/story-ruLfnemT6A88Xju7a79kqO.html |title=Deepika Padukone teams up with Ananya Panday, Sidhant Chaturvedi for Shakun Batra\u2019s relationship drama |work=Hindustan Times |date=19 December 2019 |access-date=19 December 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-play-draupadi-in-next-this-perspective-on-mahabharata-will-be-interesting-significant/story-SAaHdtLN7UwlIlUYWruyWN.html |title=Deepika Padukone to play Draupadi in next: \u2018This perspective on Mahabharata will be interesting, significant\u2019 |work=Hindustan Times |date=25 October 2019 |access-date=25 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191025041303/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-play-draupadi-in-next-this-perspective-on-mahabharata-will-be-interesting-significant/story-SAaHdtLN7UwlIlUYWruyWN.html |archive-date=25 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Padukone will also produce and star in a remake of the American comedy film ''[[The Intern (2015 film)|The Intern]]'', co-starring [[Rishi Kapoor]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Ramachandran|first=Naman|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/asia/deepika-padukone-rishi-kapoor-bollywood-remake-the-intern-1203481933/|title=Deepika Padukone and Rishi Kapoor to star in Bollywood Remake of \u2018The Intern\u2019|work=Variety|date=27 January 2020|accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life  ==\n[[File:Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh reception.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Singh and Padukone at their wedding reception in 2018]]\nPadukone shares a close bond with her family, and visits them regularly in her hometown of Bangalore.<ref>{{cite news |author=Muthanna, Anjali |title=Deepika makes time for family in Bangalore |date=25 May 2013 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-25/news-interviews/39520879_1_deepika-padukone-bangalore-girl-yjhd |work=The Times of India |accessdate=25 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194307/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-25/news-interviews/39520879_1_deepika-padukone-bangalore-girl-yjhd |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She lives in [[Prabhadevi]], a neighbourhood in Mumbai, and has admitted to missing the presence of her parents there.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone's South Indian home |date=7 November 2011 |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2505006891.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=4 September 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410000136/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2505006891.html |archivedate=10 April 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Ahmed, Afsana |title=I want to be the first girl Ranbir Kapoor directs: Deepika Padukone |date=23 June 2013 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-want-to-be-the-first-girl-ranbir-kapoor-directs-deepika-padukone/story-YHxXvKq8N4PFSgD1glVKEP.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=4 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203134412/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-want-to-be-the-first-girl-ranbir-kapoor-directs-deepika-padukone/story-YHxXvKq8N4PFSgD1glVKEP.html |archivedate=3 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> A practicing [[Hindu]], Padukone considers religion to be an important aspect of her life and makes frequent visits to [[Hindu temple|temples]] and other religious shrines.<ref>{{cite news |author=Batra, Ankur |title=Deepika Padukone on a religious trip |date=8 September 2011 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-08/news-interviews/30123474_1_deepika-padukone-golden-temple-morning-walkers |work=The Times of India |accessdate=25 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194315/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-08/news-interviews/30123474_1_deepika-padukone-golden-temple-morning-walkers |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nWhile filming ''Bachna Ae Haseeno'' in 2008, Padukone began a romantic relationship with co-star Ranbir Kapoor.<ref>{{cite web |title=I've been dating Deepika for few weeks: Ranbir Kapoor |date=17 March 2008 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-ve-been-dating-deepika-for-a-few-weeks-ranbir-kapoor-news-bollywood-kkftL3hfdja.html |accessdate=17 March 2008 |publisher=[[Sify]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231090325/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-ve-been-dating-deepika-for-a-few-weeks-ranbir-kapoor-news-bollywood-kkftL3hfdja.html |archivedate=31 December 2010 |df=}}</ref> She spoke openly about the relationship and sported a tattoo of his initials on the nape of her neck.<ref>{{cite news |last=Behrawala |first=Krutika |title=Tattoo Tales |date=17 August 2012 |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/tattoo-tales/987803/ |accessdate=4 September 2013 |work=The Indian Express |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208095326/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/tattoo-tales/987803 |archivedate=8 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> She has said that the relationship had a profound effect on her, transforming her into a more confident and social person.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> The Indian media speculated on an engagement, and reported that this had occurred in November 2008, although Padukone had stated that she had no plans to marry within the next five years.<ref>{{cite book |title=Drum |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_OosAQAAIAAJ |year=2008 |publisher=Drum Publications (East Africa) |page=98 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114120425/http://books.google.com/books?id=_OosAQAAIAAJ |archivedate=14 November 2013 |df=}}</ref> The couple broke up a year later;<ref>{{cite news |author=Lalwani, Vickey |title=Deepika-Ranbir call it quits! |date=3 November 2009 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-03/news-interviews/28091798_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-nihar-pandya |work=The Times of India |accessdate=10 December 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025161535/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-03/news-interviews/28091798_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-nihar-pandya |archive-date=25 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> she professed in an interview to feeling betrayed for a long time.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> In a 2010 interview, Padukone accused him of infidelity, and Kapoor later admitted to it.<ref>{{cite news |title=He cheated on me: Deepika |date=28 September 2010 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/he-cheated-on-me-deepika/story-Yb1QlWYJgHy9rIyGhoaWJP.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=4 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117032126/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/he-cheated-on-me-deepika/story-Yb1QlWYJgHy9rIyGhoaWJP.html |archivedate=17 November 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Punoose, Rukhmini |title=Deepika on a dream run |url=http://www.verveonline.com/89/people/deepika.shtml |work=Verve |accessdate=4 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBCdTkQ?url=http://www.verveonline.com/89/people/deepika.shtml |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Yes, I cheated: Ranbir |date=30 September 2011 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-30/news-interviews/30229828_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-relationship |work=The Times of India |accessdate=4 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203192202/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-30/news-interviews/30229828_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-relationship |archive-date=3 December 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> They reconciled their friendship while working on ''Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani''.<ref>{{cite news |title='Ranbir and I have become a lot closer now' \u2013 Deepika Padukone |last=Tandon |first=Raedita |date=28 June 2013 |url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/ranbir-and-i-have-become-a-lot-closer-now-deepika-padukone-3546.html |work=Filmfare |accessdate=4 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwAucO9G?url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/ranbir-and-i-have-become-a-lot-closer-now-deepika-padukone-3546.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\nPadukone subsequently became reticent to discuss her personal life, but in 2017, she fondly spoke of her relationship with her frequent co-star [[Ranveer Singh]], whom she began dating in 2012.<ref name=\"filmfare17\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Choudhary|first=Anuradha|title=Exclusive and explosive: Deepika Padukone\u2019s first interview after marriage |url=https://www.filmfare.com/interviews/exclusive-and-explosive-deepika-padukones-first-interview-after-marriage-31906.html |work=Filmfare |date=28 December 2018 |accessdate=8 January 2020 }}</ref> In November 2018, the couple married in traditional Konkani and Sindhi ceremonies at [[Lake Como]], Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone, Ranveer Singh are married now, wedding ceremony ends in Italy |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-are-married-now-wedding-ceremony-ends-in-italy/story-OrrIJnMvTwI1wSwl7JbWqM.html |work=Hindustan Times |date=14 November 2018 |accessdate=14 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114143025/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-are-married-now-wedding-ceremony-ends-in-italy/story-OrrIJnMvTwI1wSwl7JbWqM.html |archive-date=14 November 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n== Off-screen work ==\n\nIn addition to acting, Padukone has written opinion columns and has been involved with women's health and fitness magazines. She has also supported charitable organisations, and has performed for stage shows. In 2009, she was hired by ''Hindustan Times'' to write weekly columns for their lifestyle section; through these columns she interacted with her fans and passed details of her personal and professional life.<ref>{{cite news |last=Padukone |first=Deepika |title=My nervous excitement |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/my-nervous-excitement/story-cd9szDgxJirCJBRYiRSANO.html |work=Hindustan Times |date=27 July 2009 |accessdate=7 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222115730/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/my-nervous-excitement/story-cd9szDgxJirCJBRYiRSANO.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Padukone |first=Deepika |title=Our love stays: Deepika |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/our-love-stays-deepika/story-g90A33jkUB0aliIisrjLmJ.html |work=Hindustan Times |date=12 October 2009 |accessdate=7 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222091753/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/our-love-stays-deepika/story-g90A33jkUB0aliIisrjLmJ.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref> That year, she participated in the [[World 10K Bangalore]] marathon, which raised {{INRConvert|13.1|m}} in support of 81&nbsp;NGOs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika for charity |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-07-22/people/28169980_1_charity-event-bangaloreans |accessdate=24 June 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=22 July 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928200019/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-07-22/people/28169980_1_charity-event-bangaloreans |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone raises Rs 1.3 crore for several charities |url=http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2009/jul/090709-Bollywood-Bengaluru-Deepika-Padukone-marathon-1-crore-charity.htm |accessdate=24 June 2013 |newspaper=[[Mid Day]] |date=9 July 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911085117/http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2009/jul/090709-Bollywood-Bengaluru-Deepika-Padukone-marathon-1-crore-charity.htm |archive-date=11 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2010, Padukone adopted the [[Maharashtra|Maharashtrian]] village of [[Ambegaon]] as part of NDTV's Greenathon Campaign, to provide the village with a regular supply of electricity.<ref>{{cite news |last=Joshi |first=Tushar |title=Deepika adopts a Ambegaon village |url=http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/mar/100310-Deepika-Padukone-Ambegaon-village-Greenathon-campaign.htm |accessdate=21 April 2013 |newspaper=Mid Day |date=10 March 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911085232/http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/mar/100310-Deepika-Padukone-Ambegaon-village-Greenathon-campaign.htm |archive-date=11 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> She visited Indian ''[[jawans]]'' (troops) in [[Jammu]], for an [[Independence Day (India)|Independence Day]] special episode of NDTV's reality show ''Jai Jawaan''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone in uniform |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/photos/entertainment/rough-n-tough-deepika-padukone-in-uniform/photo-yIFQ9OLxuFGsGEJk7bEiUI.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=24 June 2013 |date=23 November 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222144133/http://www.hindustantimes.com/photos/entertainment/rough-n-tough-deepika-padukone-in-uniform/photo-yIFQ9OLxuFGsGEJk7bEiUI.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SLAMtheTour 20Sep2014 (199) (15143666038) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|alt=A shot of Deepika Padukone dancing on stage|Padukone performing at the  \"SLAM! The Tour\" concert in 2014]]\n\nPadukone took part in the opening ceremony of the [[2010 Indian Premier League|third season of the Indian Premier League]] at the [[DY Patil Stadium]] in [[Navi Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite web |title=IPL 3 kicks off with grand opening ceremony |url=http://sports.ndtv.com/cricket/news/134698-ipl-3-kicks-off-with-grand-opening-ceremony |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=24 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006100537/http://sports.ndtv.com/cricket/news/134698-ipl-3-kicks-off-with-grand-opening-ceremony |archivedate=6 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Three years later, she performed alongside Shah Rukh Khan, [[Katrina Kaif]], and [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] for the [[2013 Indian Premier League|sixth edition]] of the Indian Premier League.<ref>{{cite web |title=IPL 2013: Shah Rukh Khan, Katrina Kaif, Deepika Padukone, Pitbull showcase diverse culture |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/ipl-2013-shah-rukh-khan-katrina-kaif-deepika-padukone-pitbull-showcase-diverse-culture-349474 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=24 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713121133/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/ipl-2013-shah-rukh-khan-katrina-kaif-deepika-padukone-pitbull-showcase-diverse-culture-349474 |archivedate=13 July 2014 |df=}}</ref> In 2014, she participated in a concert tour across North America, entitled \"SLAM! The Tour\", in which she performed alongside her co-stars from ''Happy New Year''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone take America by storm |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/shah-rukh-khan-deepika-padukone-slam-american-fans-houston-new-jersey/1/384742.html |work=India Today |date=24 September 2014 |accessdate=26 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140926201737/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/shah-rukh-khan-deepika-padukone-slam-american-fans-houston-new-jersey/1/384742.html |archivedate=26 September 2014 |df=}}</ref> Padukone has also been involved with the [[Olympic Gold Quest]] team, established by her father and [[Geet Sethi]] to support Indian athletes at the Olympic Games, along with sports personalities such as [[Leander Paes]] and [[Viswanathan Anand]] and several other actors.<ref name=\"Nehwal2012\">{{cite book |last=Nehwal |first=Saina |title=Playing to Win |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tBSi3rdUPO0C&pg=PT41 |date=15 December 2012 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |isbn=978-81-8475-915-0 |page=41 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101113850/http://books.google.com/books?id=tBSi3rdUPO0C&pg=PT41 |archivedate=1 November 2013 |df=}}</ref> In 2013, she launched her own line of clothing for women, in association with the retail chain [[PVH (company)|Van Heusen]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone makes her debut as fashion designer |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-makes-her-debut-as-fashion-designer/1177826/ |accessdate=4 October 2013 |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=3 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140213011332/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-makes-her-debut-as-fashion-designer/1177826 |archivedate=13 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> Two years later, Padukone collaborated with the fashion portal [[Myntra]] to launch another line under her brand \"All About You\".<ref>{{cite news |author=Anshul |title=Myntra launches Deepika Padukone brand \u2018All About You\u2019; prices start Rs 1,500 |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/industry/companies/myntra-launches-deepika-padukone-brand-all-about-you-prices-start-rs-1500/154226/ |accessdate=11 October 2016 |work=The Financial Express |date=20 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011224233/http://www.financialexpress.com/industry/companies/myntra-launches-deepika-padukone-brand-all-about-you-prices-start-rs-1500/154226/ |archivedate=11 October 2016 |df=}}</ref> In 2019, she was appointed as the chairperson of the [[Mumbai Academy of the Moving Image]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone is the new MAMI chairperson |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-is-the-new-mami-chairperson/articleshow/67750989.cms |accessdate=30 January 2019 |newspaper=Mumbai Mirror |date=30 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130110026/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-is-the-new-mami-chairperson/articleshow/67750989.cms |archive-date=30 January 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Through her own company, Ka Enterprises, Padukone invested in Drum Foods International, a [[fast-moving consumer goods]] company, and Blu Smart, an [[electric vehicle|electric taxi]] startup.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone invests in maker of Epigamia yogurt |url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-invests-in-maker-of-epigamia-yogurt-1557771851043.html |accessdate=16 May 2019 |work=Mint |date=14 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517231717/https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-invests-in-maker-of-epigamia-yogurt-1557771851043.html |archive-date=17 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Sriram, M.|title=Deepika Padukone\u2019s family office invests in e-taxi startup Blu Smart|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-s-family-office-invests-in-blu-smart-1569243127845.html|accessdate=24 September 2019|work=Mint|date=23 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924101621/https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-s-family-office-invests-in-blu-smart-1569243127845.html|archive-date=24 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPadukone has also been outspoken on issues such as feminism and has said, \"New feminism isn't about being aggressive; it's about reaching the top yet being soft. It's about being you \u2014 feminine, strong and full of will power.\u201d<ref name=\"Sinha2011\">{{cite book |last=Sinha |first=Dheeraj |title=Consumer India: Inside the Indian Mind and Wallet |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Uw-XCvE9G4YC&pg=PA129 |date=14 February 2011 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=978-0-470-82632-4 |page=129}}</ref> In a 2015 interview, Padukone spoke about her personal experience of overcoming depression, and in October that year she formed a foundation to create awareness on mental health in India, named [[The Live Love Laugh Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Awaasthi, Kavita |title=Deepika Padukone on suffering from depression: It was a struggle to wake up |date=17 January 2015 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid/deepika-padukone-on-suffering-from-depression-it-was-a-struggle-to-wake-up/article1-1306957.aspx |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150118035439/http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid/deepika-padukone-on-suffering-from-depression-it-was-a-struggle-to-wake-up/article1-1306957.aspx |archivedate=18 January 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone launches her foundation 'Live, Love and Laugh' on World Mental Health Day |date=10 October 2015 |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-launches-her-foundation-live-love-and-laugh-on-world-mental-health-day-2133489 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=28 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022163008/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-launches-her-foundation-live-love-and-laugh-on-world-mental-health-day-2133489 |archivedate=22 October 2015 |df=}}</ref> The following year, she launched a campaign named More Than Just Sad to assist general physicians in their treatment of patients suffering from depression or anxiety.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone\u2019s foundation launches awareness programme on mental health |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukones-foundation-launches-awareness-programme-on-mental-health-2811187/#sthash.A7hGmE4o.dpuf |date=20 May 2016 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=22 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160521215431/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukones-foundation-launches-awareness-programme-on-mental-health-2811187/ |archivedate=21 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> Also in 2016, the foundation teamed with Facebook and the [[AASRA]] organisation to launch multilingual tools and educational resources in Facebook's networking site to support people with suicidal tendencies.<ref>{{cite news |last=Alawadhi |first=Neha |title=Facebook partners with Deepika Padukone's Foundation; launches suicide prevention tools in India |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/52749651.cms |date=14 June 2016 |work=The Economic Times |accessdate=15 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911230551/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/52749651.cms |archivedate=11 September 2016 |df=}}</ref> Padukone became the brand ambassador for the NGO [[Indian Psychiatric Society]] and on her foundation's first anniversary, the two organisations collaborated to launch the video and poster campaign #DobaraPoocho dedicated to victims and survivors of depression.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone named Indian Psychiatric Society's brand ambassador |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-named-Indian-Psychiatric-Societys-brand-ambassador/articleshow/53856784.cms |accessdate=5 November 2016 |work=The Times of India |date=25 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829212121/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-named-Indian-Psychiatric-Societys-brand-ambassador/articleshow/53856784.cms |archivedate=29 August 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Stigma key reason why mental health issues not being addressed: Deepika |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/stigma-key-reason-why-mental-health-issues-not-being-addressed-deepika/story-IhbNNQwyGfdPqwTFNsQEvM.html |accessdate=5 November 2016 |work=Hindustan Times |date=10 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106061008/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/stigma-key-reason-why-mental-health-issues-not-being-addressed-deepika/story-IhbNNQwyGfdPqwTFNsQEvM.html |archivedate=6 November 2016 |df=}}</ref> The [[World Economic Forum]] presented her with the Crystal Award in 2020 for creating awareness on mental health.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone feted with Crystal Award at WEF; stresses on importance of mental health, quotes Martin Luther King |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/deepika-padukone-feted-with-crystal-award-at-wef-stresses-on-importance-of-mental-health-quotes-martin-luther-king/articleshow/73471900.cms |accessdate=21 January 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, Padukone lent her support to students who were brutalised during the [[2020 JNU Attack]] due to their [[Citizenship Amendment Act protests|protests]] against the [[Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2019|Citizenship Amendment Act]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018We are not scared\u2019: Why Deepika Padukone\u2019s JNU visit matters |url=https://scroll.in/reel/949118/why-deepika-padukones-jnu-visit-matters |date=8 January 2020 |website=Scroll.in |accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref> Members of the ruling [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] criticised her decision and asked people to boycott her film ''Chhapaak''.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Deepika Padukone Was Patriot Earlier, Now...\": Kanhaiya Kumar On Criticism |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/jawaharlal-nehru-university-jnu-deepika-padukone-was-patriot-earlier-now-kanhaiya-kumar-on-criticism-2161458 |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=NDTV |date=9 January 2020}}</ref> Many others praised her for standing up against a crackdown on dissent, as mainstream Bollywood actors avoid making political statements fearing backlash and consequences on their film.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bollywood A-lister backs protesting students, faces boycott calls |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-student-protests/bollywood-a-lister-backs-protesting-students-faces-boycott-calls-idUSKBN1Z71CU |accessdate=8 January 2020 |website=Reuters |date=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== In the media ==\nThe journalist [[Vir Sanghvi]], in 2013, described Padukone as \"strong, someone who makes up her own mind, [and] has motivation within herself.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Sanghvi |first=Vir |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shah-rukh-khan-and-deepika-padukone-in-conversation-with-vir-sanghvi/story-IVIPeV2PyW34oFg2UpCZoJ.html |title=Shah Rukh Khan and Deepika Padukone in conversation with Vir Sanghvi |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=17 August 2013 |date=4 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201125703/http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shah-rukh-khan-and-deepika-padukone-in-conversation-with-vir-sanghvi/story-IVIPeV2PyW34oFg2UpCZoJ.html |archivedate=1 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> She is particularly known in the media as a professional, disciplined performer, whose \"work takes precedence over everything else.\"<ref name=\"making of deepika\" /> A reviewer for Rediff.com described her personality as \"simple,\" \"grounded,\" and \"accessible,\" and wrote, \"She takes criticism in her stride, acknowledges her limitations and strives to work hard at getting better. She handles praise with equal composure.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-10-reasons-why-we-love-deepika-padukone/20130805.htm#10 |title=10 reasons we love Deepika Padukone |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=12 August 2013 |date=5 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130812060241/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-10-reasons-why-we-love-deepika-padukone/20130805.htm |archivedate=12 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> Ayan Mukerji (the director of ''Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani'') considers her to be \"a woman who will flirt with you but you will love to take her home to meet your mom as well.\"<ref name=\"making of deepika\" /> Padukone has maintained a Twitter account since 2010, and launched an official Facebook page in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-07/news-interviews/36950476_1_facebook-page-deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-race |title=Deepika Padukone races from 2.6 to 5 million |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=7 February 2013 |work=The Times of India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055931/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-07/news-interviews/36950476_1_facebook-page-deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-race |archive-date=23 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She is the most followed Asian woman on Twitter.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone becomes the most followed woman on Twitter in Asia! |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-becomes-the-most-followed-woman-on-twitter-in-asia-2260199 |accessdate=11 October 2016 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=30 September 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005023708/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-becomes-the-most-followed-woman-on-twitter-in-asia-2260199 |archivedate=5 October 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/deepika-padukone-ahead-of-amitabh-salman-khan-on-facebook/story-8rCxIBo9ZxN4etbgJi1rPN.html |title=Deepika Padukone ahead of Amitabh, Salman Khan on Facebook |work=Hindustan Times |date=26 March 2014 |accessdate=28 March 2014 |last=Baksi |first=Dibyojyoti |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201124048/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/deepika-padukone-ahead-of-amitabh-salman-khan-on-facebook/story-8rCxIBo9ZxN4etbgJi1rPN.html |archivedate=1 February 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n[[File:Deepika p Lux-Award 2016.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|alt=A shot of Deepika Padukone posing for the camera|Padukone at an event for [[Lux (soap)|Lux]] in 2016]]\nPadukone is considered among the most popular and high-profile celebrities in India.<ref name=\"heroine\" /><ref name=\"high\" /> Analysing her career, [[Reuters]] published that after making a successful debut with ''Om Shanti Om'', she featured in a series of films for which critics labelled her as \"wooden\" and \"mocked her accent.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Jamkhandikar |first=Shilpa |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2013/06/12/deepika-padukone-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-idINDEE95B0CM20130612 |title=Deepika Padukone breaks free of Brad Pitt syndrome |agency=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=30 August 2013 |date=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130827144604/http://in.reuters.com/article/2013/06/12/deepika-padukone-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-idINDEE95B0CM20130612 |archivedate=27 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> ''The Indian Express'' added, \"Not too long ago after a few unwise script calls and the public blow up of her high profile relationship with Ranbir Kapoor, Deepika was written off. Credit to her much touted professionalism, dedication, discipline and perseverance that she bounced back.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Harneet |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |title=Post Chennai Express, Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani Deepika Padukone is number 1 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=30 August 2013 |date=16 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205203526/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |archivedate=5 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> Following the success of ''Cocktail'', ''Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani'', and ''Chennai Express'', several media publications began crediting her as the most successful contemporary actress in India.<ref name=\"top\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1130822/jsp/t2/story_17256831.jsp |title=Heroine no. 1 \u2013 Deepika leads the Bolly girl gang |newspaper=The Telegraph |accessdate=30 August 2013 |date=22 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002122212/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1130822/jsp/t2/story_17256831.jsp |archivedate=2 October 2013 |df=}}<br />{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Harneet |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |title=Post Chennai Express, Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani Deepika Padukone is number 1 |newspaper=The Indian Express |accessdate=7 October 2013 |date=16 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205203526/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |archivedate=5 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> ''[[India Today]]'' featured her among the nation's 50 most powerful people in 2017 and 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/india-today-top-50-powerful-indians-mukesh-ambani-ratan-tata-kumar-mangalam-birla-gautam-adani-anand-mahindra-srk-amitabh-bacchan/1/928939.html |title=50 power people |work=India Today |date=14 April 2017 |accessdate=21 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417122537/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/india-today-top-50-powerful-indians-mukesh-ambani-ratan-tata-kumar-mangalam-birla-gautam-adani-anand-mahindra-srk-amitabh-bacchan/1/928939.html |archivedate=17 April 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/the-most-powerful-people-of-india-2019-full-list-1574021-2019-07-26 |title=The most powerful people of India 2019 |work=India Today |date=26 July 2019 |accessdate=30 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730004608/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/the-most-powerful-people-of-india-2019-full-list-1574021-2019-07-26 |archive-date=30 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The global edition of ''Forbes'' ranked her as the tenth highest-paid actress in the world in 2016 and in 2018, the magazine ranked her as the highest-earning woman celebrity in India.<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/23/the-worlds-highest-paid-actresses-2016-jennifer-lawrence-banks-46-million-payday-ahead-of-melissa-mccarthy/ |title=The World's Highest-Paid Actresses 2016: Jennifer Lawrence Banks $46 Million Payday Ahead Of Melissa McCarthy |work=Forbes |date=23 August 2016 |accessdate=23 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823191155/http://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/23/the-worlds-highest-paid-actresses-2016-jennifer-lawrence-banks-46-million-payday-ahead-of-melissa-mccarthy/ |archivedate=23 August 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/emjl45efgmh/10-deepika-padukone/ |title=Deepika Padukone |work=Forbes |accessdate=23 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823235831/http://www.forbes.com/pictures/emjl45efgmh/10-deepika-padukone/ |archivedate=23 August 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Panchal |first1=Salil |last2=Gangal |first2=Neeraj |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2018-celebrity-100/salman-khan-tops-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list-for-third-time-in-a-row/51955/1 |title=Salman Khan tops Forbes India Celebrity 100 list for third time in a row |work=Forbes |accessdate=2 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205064716/http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2018-celebrity-100/salman-khan-tops-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list-for-third-time-in-a-row/51955/1 |archive-date=5 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> From 2014\u20132016 and in 2018, she was the highest ranked woman on the Indian edition of ''[[Forbes]]''{{'}} \"[[Celebrity 100]]\" (a list based on the income and popularity of celebrities), peaking at the fourth position in 2018 with an estimated annual earning of over {{INRConvert|1.12|b}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2016/deepika-padukone/1587/11 |title=Deepika Padukone |work=[[Forbes India]] |accessdate=26 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224132532/http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2016/deepika-padukone/1587/11 |archivedate=24 December 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Salman Khan beats Shah Rukh Khan; tops the \u20182016 Forbes India Celebrity 100 List\u2019 - Bollywood Hungama |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/salman-khan-beats-shah-rukh-khan-tops-2016-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list/ |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=25 December 2016 |date=23 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224143231/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/salman-khan-beats-shah-rukh-khan-tops-2016-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list/ |archivedate=24 December 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2018-celebrity-100/1735/all |title=2018 Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes India |accessdate=5 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205064833/http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2018-celebrity-100/1735/all |archive-date=5 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in 2018, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine named Padukone one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]], ''Variety'' featured her in their listing of the 50 most impactful women in the world, and the market research firm [[YouGov]] named her the world's thirteenth most admired woman.<ref>{{cite news |last=Diesel |first=Vin |url=http://time.com/collection/most-influential-people-2018/5217557/deepika-padukone/ |title=Deepika Padukone |work=Time |accessdate=21 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420220932/http://time.com/collection/most-influential-people-2018/5217557/deepika-padukone/|archive-date=20 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/gallery/international-womens-impact-report-2018/#!33/deepika-padukone-3 |title=Deepika Padukone |work=Variety |accessdate=28 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322020424/http://variety.com/gallery/international-womens-impact-report-2018/#!33/deepika-padukone-3|archive-date=22 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://yougov.co.uk/news/2018/04/11/worlds-most-admired-2018/ |title=World\u2019s most admired 2018 |publisher=[[YouGov]] |accessdate=28 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612141722/https://yougov.co.uk/news/2018/04/11/worlds-most-admired-2018/ |archive-date=12 June 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nPadukone is considered a sex symbol and style icon in India \u2013 the media cites her figure, height {{height|m=1.74}}, smile, and eyes as her distinctive physical features.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://idiva.com/photogallery-entertainment/50-most-beautiful-indian-faces/11401/21 |title=50 Most Beautiful Indian Faces |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=9 March 2012 |publisher=iDiva |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBO91br?url=http://idiva.com/photogallery-entertainment/50-most-beautiful-indian-faces/11401/21 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The actress ranks high on various listings of the most attractive Indian celebrities.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/554302/style-icon-deepika-padukone/ |title=Style icon: Deepika Padukone |work=[[The Express Tribune]] |date=24 May 2013 |accessdate=19 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608023546/http://tribune.com.pk/story/554302/style-icon-deepika-padukone/ |archivedate=8 June 2013 |df=}}</ref> In 2008, she topped ''[[Maxim (India)|Indian ''Maxim'']]''{{'}}s \"Hot 100\" list,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-08-24/news-interviews/27910255_1_sexiest-woman-deepika-padukone-platform |title=Deepika is the world's sexiest woman! |work=The Times of India |date=24 August 2008 |accessdate=4 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194527/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-08-24/news-interviews/27910255_1_sexiest-woman-deepika-padukone-platform |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> and in 2012, she was named \"India's Most Beautiful Woman\" by the Indian edition of ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine.<ref name=\"people most beautiful\">{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/deepika-padukone-named-india-most-beautiful-woman/1/9386.html#photo1 |title=Deepika named India's Most Beautiful Woman |work=India Today |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=3 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCXdOMt?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/deepika-padukone-named-india-most-beautiful-woman/1/9386.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Padukone has frequently featured in ''The Times of India''{{'}}s listing of the \"Most Desirable Woman\", topping the list in 2012 and 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-2013s-Most-desirable-woman/articleshow/35726757.cms? |title=Deepika Padukone: 2013\u2019s Most desirable woman |work=The Times of India |date=30 May 2014 |accessdate=31 May 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140531081711/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-2013s-Most-desirable-woman/articleshow/35726757.cms |archivedate=31 May 2014 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-29/news-interviews/38903243_1_entrant-desirable-women-desirable-men |title=Times top 50 Most Desirable Women of 2012 |work=The Times of India |date=29 April 2013 |accessdate=19 July 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019103638/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-29/news-interviews/38903243_1_entrant-desirable-women-desirable-men |archive-date=19 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Priyanka-Chopra-The-Most-Desirable-woman-of-2015/articleshow/52187930.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra: The Most Desirable woman of 2015 |newspaper=The Times of India |accessdate=10 May 2016 |date=10 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160511112201/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Priyanka-Chopra-The-Most-Desirable-woman-of-2015/articleshow/52187930.cms |archivedate=11 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> In 2010 and 2014, she was named the \"World's Sexiest Woman\" by the Indian edition of ''[[FHM (India)|FHM]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=KBR |first=Upala |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-displaces-katrina-kaif-in-fhm-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2014-1999264 |title=Deepika Padukone displaces Katrina Kaif in FHM 100 Sexiest Women in the World 2014 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=5 July 2014 |date=3 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707022951/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-displaces-katrina-kaif-in-fhm-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2014-1999264 |archivedate=7 July 2014 |df=}}</ref> and she was selected by the UK magazine ''[[Eastern Eye]]'' as the \"Sexiest Asian Woman\" in 2016 and 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/deepika-padukone-is-the-sexiest-asian-women/20161209.htm |title=Deepika Padukone is Asia's sexiest woman! |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=8 February 2017 |date=9 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112005154/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/deepika-padukone-is-the-sexiest-asian-women/20161209.htm |archivedate=12 January 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/50-sexiest-asian-women-deepika-padukone-priyanka-chopra-5480941/ |title=50 Sexiest Asian Women: Deepika tops the list, Priyanka is in second position |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=8 December 2018 |date=6 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207135508/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/50-sexiest-asian-women-deepika-padukone-priyanka-chopra-5480941/ |archive-date=7 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Taking note of her dress sense, ''Filmfare'' credited her as one of the \"few actresses who experiments with colours, cuts and silhouettes.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Tandan |first=Raedita |url=http://www.filmfare.com/features/poll-most-fashionable-star-3034.html |title=Poll: Most Fashionable Star |work=Filmfare |accessdate=4 August 2013 |date=3 May 2008 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBG075Y?url=http://www.filmfare.com/features/poll-most-fashionable-star-3034.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In the fitness book ''The Four-Week Countdown Diet'', the actress was cited by Namita Jain as \"the ultimate role model for a healthy, fit and active lifestyle.\"<ref name=\"Jain2011\">{{cite book |last=Jain |first=Namita |title=The Four-Week Countdown Diet |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-Ru_R9r07RgC&pg=PR9 |date=1 January 2011 |publisher=Penguin Books India |isbn=978-0-14-306781-8 |page=9 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131028162350/http://books.google.com/books?id=-Ru_R9r07RgC&pg=PR9 |archivedate=28 October 2013 |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone is an active celebrity endorser for several brands and products, including [[Tissot]], [[Maybelline]], [[Coca-Cola]], and [[L'Oreal Paris]], among others.<ref>{{cite web |title=Deepika Padukone brand ambassador for Tissot |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report_deepika-padukone-brand-ambassador-for-tissot_1139085 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=9 March 2013}}<br />{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone is Sony brand ambassador |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/62603/deepika-padukone-sony-brand-ambassador.html |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=9 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927121724/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/62603/deepika-padukone-sony-brand-ambassador.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=}}<br />{{cite video |title=Nescafe announces Deepika Padukone as brand ambassador |url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/news/nescafe-announces-deepika-padukone-as-brand-ambassador/150166 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=9 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928210902/http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/news/nescafe-announces-deepika-padukone-as-brand-ambassador/150166 |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}<br />{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone lives her DDLJ moment in Chennai Express |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-lives-her-ddlj-moment-in-chennai-express-1849731 |accessdate=22 January 2014 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=18 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202203154/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-lives-her-ddlj-moment-in-chennai-express-1849731 |archivedate=2 February 2014 |df=}}<br />{{cite web |last=Singh |first=Aarti K. |title=All at 20! May be she is born with it |date=3 August 2006 |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/all-at-20-may-be-she-is-born-with-it/17520-8.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=30 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007061205/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/all-at-20-may-be-she-is-born-with-it/17520-8.html |archivedate=7 October 2014}}<br />{{cite book |last=Kapoor |first=Jagdeep |title=Twenty Four Brand Mantras: Finding a Place in the Minds and Hearts of Consumers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fmmkwDy9_QIC&pg=PA68 |date=9 February 2009 |publisher=SAGE Publications |isbn=978-81-7829-943-3 |page=68 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504103925/https://books.google.com/books?id=fmmkwDy9_QIC&pg=PA68 |archivedate=4 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> In 2014, ''Business Standard'' reported that Padukone earned {{INRConvert|50|m}} to {{INRConvert|60|m}} per endorsement deal and [[TAM Media Research|TAM AdEX]] named Padukone the most visible face on television in India that year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pinto |first1=Viveat Susan |title=Deepika: Leading lady in brand fees |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/deepika-leading-lady-in-brand-fees-114030700027_1.html |accessdate=5 March 2017 |work=Business Standard |date=11 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704181135/http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/deepika-leading-lady-in-brand-fees-114030700027_1.html |archivedate=4 July 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone is leading the advertisement space |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-is-leading-the-advertisement-space-2045937 |accessdate=5 March 2017 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=21 December 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306032102/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-is-leading-the-advertisement-space-2045937 |archivedate=6 March 2017 |df=}}</ref> [[Duff & Phelps]] estimated her brand value to be US$102.5 million, in 2018, the second highest of Indian celebrities.<ref>{{cite news |last=Laghate |first=Gaurav |title=Virat Kohli tops powerful celebrity brands list with a brand value of $170.9 million |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/advertising/virat-kohli-tops-powerful-celebrity-brands-list-with-a-brand-value-of-170-9-million/articleshow/67469396.cms |accessdate=26 January 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=10 January 2019}}</ref> In 2020, she became the first Indian actor to campaign for the fashion company [[Louis Vuitton]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Tewari |first=Saumya |title=Deepika Padukone becomes first Indian actor to feature in Louis Vuitton campaign |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/deepika-padukone-becomes-first-indian-actor-to-feature-in-louis-vuitton-campaign-11579781913267.html |accessdate=24 January 2020 |work=Mint |date=23 January 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone}}\nPadukone has been the recipient of three [[Filmfare Awards]]: Best Female Debut for ''Om Shanti Om'' (2007), and two Best Actress awards for ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' (2013) and  ''Piku'' (2015).<ref name=\"heroine\" /><ref name=\"ff13\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=25em}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite news |author1=Ajwani, Deepak |author2=Paul, Cuckoo |title=Deepika Padukone: Living a Fairytale |url=http://forbesindia.com/article/2013-celebrity-100/deepika-padukone-living-a-fairytale/36753/0 |work=Forbes |date=26 December 2013}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=2138653}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes person|deepika_padukone|Deepika Padukone}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards received by Deepika Padukone\n| list =\n{{FilmfareAwardBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestActress}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{StarGuildAwardBestActress}}\n{{StardustAwardFemaleActor}}\n{{ZeeCineAwardBestActorFemale}}\n{{Zee Cine Award for Best Female Debut}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Padukone, Deepika}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Hindi cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Kannada cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Female models from Bangalore]]\n[[Category:Indian female badminton players]]\n[[Category:Indian feminists]]\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Indian Hindus]]\n[[Category:Indian women columnists]]\n[[Category:Indira Gandhi National Open University alumni]]\n[[Category:Konkani people]]\n[[Category:Mental health activists]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:Filmfare Awards winners]]\n[[Category:Zee Cine Awards winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-semi-protected|small=yes}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Deepika Padukone\n| image              = Deepika Padukone Cannes 2018 (cropped).jpg\n| alt                = Deepika Padukone is seen smiling at the camera\n| caption            = Padukone at the [[2018 Cannes Film Festival]]\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age |df=yes|1986|1|5}}\n| birth_place        = [[Copenhagen]], Denmark\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actress|film producer}}\n| yearsactive        = 2005\u2013present\n| father             = [[Prakash Padukone]]\n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Ranveer Singh]]|2018}}\n| works              = [[Deepika Padukone filmography|Full list]]\n| awards             = [[List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone|Full list]]\n| website            = {{URL|deepikapadukone.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Deepika Padukone''' ({{IPA-hns|d\u032ai\u02d0p\u026aka\u02d0 p\u0259\u0256\u028ako\u02d0\u0273e\u02d0|pron}} or {{IPA-hns|pa\u02d0\u0256\u028ako\u02d0\u0273|}}; born 5 January 1986) is an Indian film actress and producer. One of the highest-paid actresses in India, [[List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone|her accolades]] include three [[Filmfare Awards]]. She features in listings of the nation's most popular personalities, and ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' named her one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]] in 2018.\n\nPadukone, the daughter of the badminton player [[Prakash Padukone]], was born in [[Copenhagen]] and raised in [[Bangalore]]. As a teenager, she played badminton in national level championships but left her career in the sport to become a fashion model. She soon received offers for film roles and made her acting debut in 2006 as the title character of the [[Kannada film]] ''[[Aishwarya (film)|Aishwarya]]''. Padukone then played a dual role opposite [[Shah Rukh Khan]] in her first Bollywood release, the romance ''[[Om Shanti Om]]'' (2007), which won her the [[Filmfare Award for Best Female Debut]]. Padukone received praise for her starring role in the romance ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' (2009), but this was followed by a brief setback. \n\nThe romantic comedy ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' (2012) marked a turning point in her career, and she gained further success with starring roles in the romantic comedies ''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]'' and ''[[Chennai Express]]'' (both 2013), the heist comedy ''[[Happy New Year (2014 film)|Happy New Year]]'' (2014), [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]'s period dramas ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' (2015) and ''[[Padmaavat]]'' (2018), and the [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]] action film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' (2017). She also received critical acclaim for playing a character based on [[Juliet]] in Bhansali's tragic romance ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' (2013) and a headstrong architect in the comedy-drama ''[[Piku]]'' (2015), winning two [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Filmfare Awards for Best Actress]]. She formed her own company Ka Productions in 2018, under which she produced ''[[Chhapaak]]'' (2020), in which she also starred as an [[acid attack]] survivor. \n\nPadukone is the chairperson of the [[Mumbai Academy of the Moving Image]] and is the founder of [[the Live Love Laugh Foundation]], which creates awareness on mental health in India. Vocal about issues such as [[feminism]] and depression, she also participates in stage shows, has written columns for a newspaper, designed her own line of clothing for women, and is a prominent celebrity endorser for brands and products. Padukone is married to her frequent co-star [[Ranveer Singh]].\n\n== Early life and modelling career ==\nPadukone was born on 5 January 1986 in [[Copenhagen]], Denmark to [[Konkani Language|Konkani]]-speaking parents.<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Celebrity/Deepika-Padukone/894255-Profile.aspx |title=Biography: Deepika Padukone |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=23 July 2012 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141231022055/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Celebrity/Deepika-Padukone/894255-Profile.aspx |archivedate=31 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Baksi |first=Dibyojyoti |title=Shah Rukh Khan made Deepika Padukone learn Tamil |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/shah-rukh-khan-made-deepika-padukone-learn-tamil/story-cdrZkwDuAQGCilR51uF7wI.html |accessdate=18 August 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=13 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304081932/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/shah-rukh-khan-made-deepika-padukone-learn-tamil/story-cdrZkwDuAQGCilR51uF7wI.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> Her father, [[Prakash Padukone]], is a former professional badminton player and her mother, Ujjala, is a travel agent.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-182121908.html |title=She's the model of success |work=[[The Star (South Africa)|The Star]] |date=4 August 2008 |accessdate=29 August 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140610213030/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-182121908.html |archivedate=10 June 2014 |df=dmy-all }}{{subscription required|via=Highbeam}}</ref> Her younger sister, Anisha, is a golfer.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kaura |first=Neha |title=Deepika\u2019s link-ups don\u2019t bother us, says sister |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepikas-link-ups-dont-bother-us-says-sister/articleshow/13994578.cms |accessdate=2 July 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=11 June 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616173634/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepikas-link-ups-dont-bother-us-says-sister/articleshow/13994578.cms |archivedate=16 June 2012 |df=}}</ref> Her paternal grandfather, Ramesh, was a secretary of the Mysore Badminton Association.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/an-exciting-tournament/article3185184.ece |title=An exciting tournament |newspaper=The Hindu |date=5 January 2006 |accessdate=3 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085559/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/an-exciting-tournament/article3185184.ece |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> The family relocated to [[Bangalore]], India when Padukone was a year old.<ref name=\"toi interview\">{{cite news |last=Gupta |first=Priya |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Ranbir-and-I-are-still-friends-Deepika-Padukone/articleshow/16782698.cms |title=Ranbir and I are still friends: Deepika Padukone |accessdate=29 August 2013 |date=13 October 2012 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014233537/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Ranbir-and-I-are-still-friends-Deepika-Padukone/articleshow/16782698.cms |archivedate=14 October 2012 |df=}}</ref> She was educated at Bangalore's [[Sophia High School]] and completed her pre-university education at [[Mount Carmel College, Bangalore|Mount Carmel College]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Just How educated are our Bollywood heroines?: Deepika Padukone |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm#3 |publisher=[[Rediff.com]] |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130805134000/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-just-how-educated-are-bollywood-heroines/20120118.htm |archivedate=5 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> She subsequently enrolled at the [[Indira Gandhi National Open University]] for a Bachelor of Arts degree in sociology but later quit it due to scheduling conflicts with her modelling career.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Deepika-Padukone-has-not-put-studies-on-back-burner/articleshow/2661901.cms |work=The Times of India |title=Deepika Padukone has not put studies on back-burner |accessdate=6 August 2013 |date=30 December 2007 |archivedate=18 July 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150718235820/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Deepika-Padukone-has-not-put-studies-on-back-burner/articleshow/2661901.cms |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone has said that she was socially awkward as a child and did not have many friends.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> The focus of her life was badminton, which she played competitively from a young age. Describing her daily routine in a 2012 interview, Padukone said, \"I would wake up at five in the morning, go for physical training, go to school, again go for playing badminton, finish my homework, and go to sleep.\"<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> Padukone continued to pursue a career in badminton throughout her school years and played the sport in national level championships. She also played baseball in a few state level tournaments.<ref>{{cite news |last=Banerjee |first=Soumyadipta |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-was-a-state-level-baseball-player-deepika-padukone-1349480 |title=I was a state level baseball player: Deepika Padukone |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=18 February 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222022814/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-i-was-a-state-level-baseball-player-deepika-padukone-1349480 |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> While concentrating on her education and sporting career, Padukone also worked as a child model, first appearing in a couple of advertising campaigns at the age of eight.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/mp/2004/08/11/stories/2004081101100100.htm |title=The long and short of the ramp |work=[[The Hindu]] |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=11 August 2004 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911085352/https://www.thehindu.com/mp/2004/08/11/stories/2004081101100100.htm |archive-date=11 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the [[Education in India|tenth grade]], she changed focus and decided to become a fashion model. She later explained, \"I realised that I was playing the game only because it ran in the family. So, I asked my father if I could give up the game and he wasn't upset at all.\"<ref name=\"model\">{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/613309.cms |title=Smash hit on the ramp |work=The Times of India |first=Asha |last=Chowdary |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=13 April 2004 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025015245/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/613309.cms |archivedate=25 October 2012 |df=}}</ref> In 2004, she began a full-time career as a model under the tutelage of [[Prasad Bidapa]].<ref name=\"model\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Malani |first=Gaurav |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-not-a-part-of-race/articleshow/10971364.cms |title=Deepika Padukone not a part of race |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=7 December 2011 |newspaper=[[The Times of India]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085559/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-not-a-part-of-race/articleshow/10971364.cms |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}<br />{{cite news |last=Saran |first=Rhea |title=Venus Rising? |url=http://www.verveonline.com/30/people/verve/venus/excerpt.shtml |accessdate=7 August 2013 |work=[[Verve (Indian magazine)|Verve]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131018010159/http://verveonline.com/30/people/verve/venus/excerpt.shtml |archivedate=18 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\nEarly in her career, Padukone gained recognition with a television commercial for the soap [[Liril]] and modelled for various other brands and products.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gahlaut |first=Kanika |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-in-new-liril-soap-ad/1/196716.html |title=Making a splash |work=[[India Today]] |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=12 April 2004 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBsSbRF?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-in-new-liril-soap-ad/1/196716.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Deepika Padukone: Biography |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity-profile/Deepika-Padukone.htm |publisher=[[Zee News]] |accessdate=7 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130906020146/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/celebrity-profile/Deepika-Padukone.htm |archivedate=6 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> In 2005, she made her [[runway (fashion)|runway]] debut at the [[Lakme Fashion Week]] for designer [[Suneet Varma]] and won the \"Model of the Year\" award at the [[Kingfisher (beer)|Kingfisher]] Fashion Awards.<ref>{{cite web |last=Menon |first=Sita |url=http://www.rediff.com/getahead/2005/apr/21fwdeep.htm |title=Go white this summer |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=21 April 2005 |publisher=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928093037/http://www.rediff.com/getahead/2005/apr/21fwdeep.htm |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Chowdhury |first=Smita R. |title=Glamour, glitz & grace |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050405/asp/calcutta/story_4572605.asp |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]] |date=5 May 2005 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927205701/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1050405/asp/calcutta/story_4572605.asp |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> Padukone's fame increased when she appeared in a highly popular print campaign for the 2006 [[Kingfisher Calendar]];<ref name=\"meet\" /> the designer [[Wendell Rodricks]] commented, \"Since [[Aishwarya Rai]], we haven't had a girl as beautiful and fresh.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=http://m.indiatoday.in/story/young-achievers-deepika-padukone-ms-dhoni-to-rabbi-shergill/1/181846.html |title=Young achievers: Deepika Padukone to Aditya Mittal, MS Dhoni to Rabbi Shergill |work=India Today |accessdate=3 August 2013 |date=20 February 2006 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBwTlZD?url=http://m.indiatoday.in/story/young-achievers-deepika-padukone-ms-dhoni-to-rabbi-shergill/1/181846.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Rodricks had spotted her at a Ganjam jewellery class he was teaching and signed her up with the Matrix agency.<ref>{{cite book |last=Vasudev |first=Shefalee |title=Powder Room |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DzdfsXQEtqoC&pg=PT61 |publisher=Random House India |isbn=978-81-8400-297-3 |page=61 |year=2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131231234025/http://books.google.com/books?id=DzdfsXQEtqoC&pg=PT61 |archivedate=31 December 2013 |df=}}</ref> At the age of 21, Padukone relocated to [[Mumbai]] and stayed at her aunt's home.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> That year, she gained wider recognition by featuring in the music video for [[Himesh Reshammiya]]'s song \"Naam Hai Tera\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Iyer |first=Meena |title=Deepika Padukone in awe of beauty pageant winners |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-in-awe-of-beauty-pageant-winners/articleshow/10767352.cms |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=17 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085600/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-in-awe-of-beauty-pageant-winners/articleshow/10767352.cms |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nPadukone soon began to receive offers for film roles.<ref>{{cite web |title=The hottest heroine in Kannada cinema |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/24sld1.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=24 August 2006 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928092027/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/aug/24sld1.htm |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> Believing herself to be too inexperienced as an actor, she instead enrolled for a course at [[Anupam Kher]]'s film academy.<ref>{{cite news |title=On course: Deepika Padukone joins Anupam Kher's Film Academy |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/badminton-star-prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-shifted-to-mumbai/1/193374.html |work=India Today |date=11 July 2005 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwC0HxiV?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/badminton-star-prakash-padukone-daughter-deepika-shifted-to-mumbai/1/193374.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Following much media speculation, the director [[Farah Khan]], who had noticed her in Reshammiya's music video, made the decision to cast her for a role in ''[[Happy New Year (2014 film)|Happy New Year]]''.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /><ref name=\"meet\" /> Fashion designer [[Wendell Rodricks]] also takes credit in helping her get the role. Farah Khan was looking for a model to star in her next film, and got in touch with [[Malaika Arora]]. Rodricks, for whom Padukone had been modelling for roughly two years then, recommended her to Arora, a close friend of his, who in turn recommended her to Khan in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/malaika-arora-deepika-padukone-om-shanti-om-wendell-rodricks-1039745-2017-09-07|title=Throwback Thursday: Did you know Malaika Arora helped Deepika Padukone bag her first film Om Shanti Om?|date=Sep 7, 2017|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-05-22}}</ref>\n\n== Acting career ==\n{{See also|Deepika Padukone filmography}}\n\n=== Film breakthrough and career struggles (2006\u20132011) ===\nPadukone announced in 2006 that she would make her film debut with ''[[Aishwarya (film)|Aishwarya]]'', a [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada film]] directed by [[Indrajit Lankesh]].<ref name=\"meet\">{{cite web |last=Vijayasarathy |first=R.G. |title=Meet Deepika Padukone |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/14sd1.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=14 March 2006 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055752/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/14sd1.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> The romantic comedy was a remake of the [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Telugu film]] ''[[Manmadhudu]]'', and she was cast in the title role opposite the actor [[Upendra (actor)|Upendra]]. The film proved to be a commercial success.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kumar |first=S.S |title=Ramya in a rush |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/ramya-in-a-rush/article3230859.ece |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=The Hindu |date=29 September 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107085559/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/ramya-in-a-rush/article3230859.ece |archive-date=7 November 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> RG Vijayasarathy of [[Rediff.com]] was appreciative of Padukone's screen presence but added that \"she needs to work on her emotional scenes.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Vijayasarathy |first=R.G. |title=Deepika's Aishwarya is a must watch |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/15aish.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=15 September 2006 |accessdate=3 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055429/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2006/sep/15aish.htm |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> By the end of 2006, Farah Khan's ''Happy New Year'' was shelved, and Khan had instead cast Padukone for the melodrama ''[[Om Shanti Om]]'' (2007).<ref>{{cite web |title='I was pulling SRK's hair out!' |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/10fchat.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=10 December 2007 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928093128/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2007/dec/10fchat.htm |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> Set against the backdrop of the [[Bollywood|Hindi film industry]], the film tells the story of a struggling actor in the 1970s who dies soon after witnessing the murder of the woman he loved and is reincarnated to avenge her death. [[Shah Rukh Khan]] starred as the protagonist, and Padukone featured in dual roles of a leading actress of the 1970s, and later, an aspiring actress.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ray |first=Sarit |title=I'm a shy person: Deepika |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-11-02/news-interviews/27986233_1_dream-debut-modelling-deepika-padukone |accessdate=3 August 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=2 November 2007 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194317/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2007-11-02/news-interviews/27986233_1_dream-debut-modelling-deepika-padukone |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> In preparation for her role, Padukone watched several films of actresses [[Helen (actress)|Helen]] and [[Hema Malini]] to study their body language.<ref>{{cite news |last=Thakur |first=Shweta |title=I saw Hema Malini films for '70s look: Deepika |date=17 November 2007 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-saw-hema-malini-films-for-70s-look-deepika/story-mGPqGR1oyShb3ElcJ7qpDO.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130102931/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/i-saw-hema-malini-films-for-70s-look-deepika/story-mGPqGR1oyShb3ElcJ7qpDO.html |archivedate=30 January 2016 |df=}}</ref> Her voice was dubbed by the voice artist [[Mona Ghosh Shetty]].<ref name=\"mona dub\">{{cite web |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-01-03/news-interviews/45834895_1_deepika-padukone-dramatic-prowess-and-zest-kochadaiiyaan |title=Why is Deepika's Hindi in Kochadaiiyaan dubbed? |work=The Times of India |date=2 January 2013 |accessdate=3 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105062349/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2014-01-03/news-interviews/45834895_1_deepika-padukone-dramatic-prowess-and-zest-kochadaiiyaan |archive-date=5 January 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> For one of the songs in the film, \"Dhoom Taana,\u201d Padukone drew upon Indian classical dance, and according to [[Dorling Kindersley]], \"mesmeriz[ed] audiences\" by using ''[[List of mudras (dance)|hasta mudras]]'' (hand gestures).<ref>{{cite book |title=The Book of Dance |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EzKmKyugOjkC&pg=PA113 |date=3 September 2012 |publisher=Dorling Kindersley Limited |isbn=978-1-4093-2237-5 |page=113 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131013030643/http://books.google.com/books?id=EzKmKyugOjkC&pg=PA113 |archivedate=13 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> ''Om Shanti Om'' was a commercial success, and emerged as the [[List of Bollywood films of 2007|highest-grossing film of the year]], with a global revenue of {{INRConvert|1.49|b}}.<ref name=\"top\">{{cite web |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=3997&nCat= |title=Top All Time Worldwide Grossers Updated |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |accessdate=13 October 2013 |date=11 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131105215110/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/arounddetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=4409&nCat= |archivedate=5 November 2013}}</ref> [[Taran Adarsh]] of the entertainment portal [[Bollywood Hungama]] opined that she had \"all it takes to be a top star\", and she was awarded with the [[Filmfare Best Female Debut Award]] and received her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] nomination.<ref>{{cite web |last=Adarsh |first=Taran |title=Movie Review: Om Shanti Om |date=7 November 2007 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54373 |publisher=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |accessdate=18 December 2007 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBYXxYy?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/criticreview/id/54373 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"heroine\">{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/top-actresses-of-bollywood-ever/9/7051.html#photo35 |title=Top heroines of Bollywood |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=10 May 2013 |work=India Today |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwC4LXB6?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/top-actresses-of-bollywood-ever/9/7051.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Bollywood Hungama reported that the success of ''Om Shanti Om'' proved a [[breakthrough role|breakthrough]] for her.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Exploring the Box Office journey of Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2013 Part 1 |date=2 August 2013 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBdY9Zu?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Deepika Padukone at an event.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|alt=Deepika Padukone is sitting on a chair and smiling at the camera|Padukone at a promotional event for ''[[Lafangey Parindey]]'' in 2010]]\n\nPadukone next played the role of one of star [[Ranbir Kapoor]]'s love interests in [[Yash Raj Films]]' romantic comedy ''[[Bachna Ae Haseeno]]'' (2008). The film was a financial success,<ref>{{cite web |title=Bachna Ae Haseeno scores at box office |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/18box.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=20 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150517150653/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/aug/18box.htm |archivedate=17 May 2015 |df=}}</ref> but [[Namrata Joshi]] of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' wrote that Padukone's performance was disappointing; \"She is mannequin-like and utterly lacks fire and zing.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Joshi |first=Namrata |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?238292 |title=Movie Review: Bachna Ae Haseeno |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=1 September 2008 |work=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927152352/http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?238292 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Her first release of 2009 came alongside [[Akshay Kumar]] in [[Nikhil Advani]]'s [[Kung fu film|kung fu]] comedy ''[[Chandni Chowk To China]]'', in which she portrayed dual roles of Indian-Chinese twin sisters. Produced by [[Warner Bros.]], it had one of the widest international releases given to an Indian film.<ref>{{cite news |last=Anderson |first=Jason |title=Chandni Chowk to China: Kung fusion hustle |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2009/01/16/chandni_chowk_to_china_kung_fusion_hustle.html |work=[[Toronto Star]] |date=16 January 2009 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012104208/http://www.thestar.com/entertainment/2009/01/16/chandni_chowk_to_china_kung_fusion_hustle.html |archivedate=12 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> Padukone learned [[jujutsu]] and performed her own stunts.<ref>{{cite web |title=Deepika's unbelievable stunt! |url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2008/nov/26slid1-deepika-unbelievable-stunt.htm?zcc=rl |publisher=Rediff.com |date=26 November 2008 |accessdate=3 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611083353/http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2008/nov/26slid1-deepika-unbelievable-stunt.htm?zcc=rl |archivedate=11 June 2014 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lalwani |first=Vickeya |title=Yes, I'm dating Ranbir: Deepika |date=15 March 2008 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-03-15/news-interviews/27772143_1_action-film-deepika-ranbir-yash-raj |work=The Times of India |accessdate=3 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012195823/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-03-15/news-interviews/27772143_1_action-film-deepika-ranbir-yash-raj |archive-date=12 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Despite the hype, ''Chandni Chowk To China'' was a financial failure, failing to recoup its {{INRConvert|800|m}} budget.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=348&catName=TGlmZXRpbWUgV29ybGR3aWRlIEluIFVTICQ= |title=Top Lifetime Grossers Worldwide (US $) |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=11 November 2010 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602093609/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=312&catName=TGlmZXRpbWU%3D |archivedate=2 June 2013 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Sharma |first=Amit |last2=Verma Ambwani |first2=Meenakshi |title=Chandni Chowk to China crosses Rs 33 cr at local box office |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-01-20/news/27650181_1_domestic-box-office-bollywood-film-kinng |work=[[The Economic Times]] |date=20 January 2009 |accessdate=6 August 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305091941/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2009-01-20/news/27650181_1_domestic-box-office-bollywood-film-kinng |archivedate=5 March 2016 |df= }}</ref> Bollywood Hungama reported that the success of ''Om Shanti Om'' proved a [[breakthrough role|breakthrough]] for Padukone.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Exploring the Box Office journey of Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2013 Part 1 |date=2 August 2013 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBdY9Zu?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5321 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Following an [[item number]] (for a song called \"Love Mera Hit Hit\") in the drama ''[[Billu]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://entertainment.in.msn.com/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=3034274&page=4 |title=Item Number in 'Billoo Barber' |publisher=[[MSN]] |date=6 January 2009 |accessdate=2 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314143005/http://entertainment.in.msn.com/gallery.aspx?cp-documentid=3034274&page=4 |archivedate=14 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> she appeared alongside [[Saif Ali Khan]] in the romantic drama ''[[Love Aaj Kal]]'' from the writer-director [[Imtiaz Ali (director)|Imtiaz Ali]]. The film documented the changing value of relationships among the youth and had Padukone play the part of Meera Pandit, a head-strong [[career woman]]. With a worldwide gross of {{INRConvert|1.2|b}}, ''Love Aaj Kal'' proved to be the [[List of Bollywood films of 2009|third highest-grossing film of 2009]].<ref name=\"top\" /> Aniruddha Guha of ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' said that Padukone \"delivers the best of her four performances so far\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Guha |first=Aniruddha |title=Review: Love Aaj Kal is the perfect date movie |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/review-review-love-aaj-kal-is-the-perfect-date-movie-1278796 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=31 July 2009 |accessdate=16 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140106100802/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/review-review-love-aaj-kal-is-the-perfect-date-movie-1278796 |archivedate=6 January 2014 |df=}}</ref> At the [[55th Filmfare Awards]] Padukone received a nomination for Best Actress.<ref name=\"bollywoodhungama1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/725/ |title=Nominations for 55th Idea Filmfare Awards 2009 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=27 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141020180943/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/725/ |archivedate=20 October 2014 |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone had five film releases in 2010. Her first role was in the psychological thriller ''[[Karthik Calling Karthik]]'', where Padukone was cast as the supportive girlfriend of a depressed man (played by [[Farhan Akhtar]]). Derek Elley of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' found the film to be \"thinly plotted\" but considered \"the uncomplicated ingenuousness of Padukone\" to be the film's highlight.<ref>{{cite news |last=Elley |first=Derek |title=Review: \"Karthik Calling Karthik\" |url=https://variety.com/2010/film/reviews/karthik-calling-karthik-1117942367/ |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=8 March 2010 |accessdate=16 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130605055907/http://variety.com/2010/film/reviews/karthik-calling-karthik-1117942367/ |archivedate=5 June 2013 |df=}}</ref> Commercially, the film performed poorly.<ref name=\"bo2010\">{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=318&catName=MjAxMA== |title=Box Office 2010 |publisher=Box office India |accessdate=14 May 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014062657/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=318&catName=MjAxMA%3D%3D |archivedate=14 October 2013 |url-status=dead |df=}}</ref> Her most financially profitable film that year was [[Sajid Khan]]'s {{INRConvert|1.15|b}}-grossing comedy film ''[[Housefull (2010 film)|Housefull]]'' in which she featured alongside an [[ensemble cast]] headlined by Akshay Kumar.<ref name=\"top\" /> [[Raja Sen]] described the film as a \"festival of bad acting\" and attributed Padukone's poor performance to her \"plasticky expressions.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Gags that'll make you gag |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-housefull-is-painful/20100430.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |date=30 April 2010 |accessdate=14 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012003148/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-housefull-is-painful/20100430.htm |archivedate=12 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> \n\n[[Pradeep Sarkar]]'s drama ''[[Lafangey Parindey]]'' (2010) starred Padukone as a blind girl determined to win a skating competition. In preparation, she observed the interactions of blind people and rehearsed scenes while blindfolded.<ref>{{cite news |title=To play a blind dancer was very challenging: Deepika Padukone |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/to-play-a-blind-dancer-was-very-challenging-deepika-padukone/1/106251.html |accessdate=3 September 2013 |work=India Today |date=22 July 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwC8bHIt?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/to-play-a-blind-dancer-was-very-challenging-deepika-padukone/1/106251.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Writing for ''[[The Hindu]]'', Sudhish Kamath was particularly impressed by the \"considerable restraint\" with which she played her part.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/article600437.ece |title=Lafangey Parindey Movie Review |author=Kamath, Sudhish |work=The Hindu |accessdate=28 April 2011 |date=28 August 2010 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220131856/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/article600437.ece |archivedate=20 December 2013 |df=}}</ref> Her next role was opposite [[Imran Khan (Bollywood actor)|Imran Khan]] in the romantic comedy ''[[Break Ke Baad]]''. [[CNN-IBN]]'s [[Rajeev Masand]] found the film to be \"watchable largely for the performance of its leading lady.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Masand |first=Rajeev |title=Masand: Break Ke Baad is an engaging film |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-break-ke-baad-is-an-engaging-film/135956-8-66.html |publisher=[[CNN-IBN]] |date=16 December 2010 |accessdate=8 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009233651/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/masand-break-ke-baad-is-an-engaging-film/135956-8-66.html |archivedate=9 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> Padukone's final release of 2010 was [[Ashutosh Gowarikar]]'s [[Historical drama film|period film]] ''[[Khelein Hum Jee Jaan Sey]]'' opposite [[Abhishek Bachchan]]. Based on the book ''[[Do and Die]]'', the film is a retelling of the 1930 [[Chittagong armoury raid]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/first-look-deepika-in-khelein-hum-jee-jaan-sey/20100519.htm |title=First look: Deepika in ''Khelein Hum Jee Jaan Sey'' |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=27 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012033209/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/first-look-deepika-in-khelein-hum-jee-jaan-sey/20100519.htm |archivedate=12 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> Bachchan featured as the revolutionary leader [[Surya Sen]] and Padukone played [[Kalpana Dutta]], his confidante.<ref>{{cite news |last=Mukherjee |first=Roshni |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-02/news-interviews/28264661_1_period-thriller-deepika-padukone-kalpana-dutta |title=Working with Ashu sir is an achievement: Deepika |work=The Times of India |date=2 December 2010 |accessdate=10 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012042232/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-12-02/news-interviews/28264661_1_period-thriller-deepika-padukone-kalpana-dutta |archive-date=12 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> Padukone said that she was unable to research her role as there was very little information on Dutta and relied on Gowarikar's direction.<ref>{{cite web |title=`Khelein Hum` no less glamorous than any of my films: Deepika |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/khelein-hum-no-less-glamorous-than-any-of-my-films-deepika_76567.html |publisher=Zee News |date=29 November 2010 |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131003203240/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/bollywood/khelein-hum-no-less-glamorous-than-any-of-my-films-deepika_76567.html |archivedate=3 October 2013 |df=}}</ref> It did not perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bad times continue at the box office |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/bad-times-continue-at-the-box-office/20101213.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025121346/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/bad-times-continue-at-the-box-office/20101213.htm |archivedate=25 October 2012 |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone began 2011 with an item number in [[Rohan Sippy]]'s ''[[Dum Maaro Dum (film)|Dum Maaro Dum]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-04/news-interviews/28359126_1_deepika-padukone-lyrics-rohan-sippy |title=Deepika's Dum Maro Dum with a twist |work=The Times of India |accessdate=27 April 2011 |date=4 February 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120523184302/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-02-04/news-interviews/28359126_1_deepika-padukone-lyrics-rohan-sippy |archive-date=23 May 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> She referred to it as \"the wildest song any actress has done;\" the song's sexual content attracted controversy including a court case for indecency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Sahgal |first=Geety |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/its-the-wildest-song-any-actress-has-done-deepika/777015/ |title=It's the wildest song any actress has done: Deepika |newspaper=[[The Indian Express]] |accessdate=27 April 2011 |date=16 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222155407/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/its-the-wildest-song-any-actress-has-done-deepika/777015/ |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/case-against-dum-maaro-dum-for-indecency-news-national-leswuobjjgf.html |title=Case against 'Dum Maaro Dum' for indecency |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=27 April 2011 |date=18 April 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110419180348/http://www.sify.com/movies/case-against-dum-maaro-dum-for-indecency-news-national-leswuobjjgf.html |archivedate=19 April 2011 |df=}}</ref> Her next film was [[Prakash Jha]]'s socio-political drama ''[[Aarakshan]]'', which dealt with [[Reservation in India|caste-based reservations in India]]. Trade journalists had high expectations for the film which ultimately flopped at the box office.<ref>{{cite web |title=Will Aarakshan draw in the crowds? |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/will-aarakshan-draw-in-the-crowds/20110801.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203184214/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/will-aarakshan-draw-in-the-crowds/20110801.htm |archivedate=3 February 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=It's raining flops at the box office |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/raining-flops-at-box-office/20110919.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=4 April 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120429131112/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/raining-flops-at-box-office/20110919.htm |archivedate=29 April 2012 |df=}}</ref> Critical reaction was largely negative, though [[Pratim D. Gupta]] mentioned Padukone as the most \"refreshing thing\" about it.<ref>{{cite news |title=Aarakshan loses plot after second half |date=12 August 2011 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/aarakshan-loses-plot-after-second-half/story-MxH4SLWdr8jzU3Jr2lUFUP.html |accessdate=13 August 2012 |work=Hindustan Times |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203133341/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/aarakshan-loses-plot-after-second-half/story-MxH4SLWdr8jzU3Jr2lUFUP.html |archivedate=3 February 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Gupta, Pratim D. |title=Aarakshan&nbsp;\u2013 Film Review |date=13 August 2011 |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1110813/jsp/entertainment/story_14372488.jsp |accessdate=13 August 2012 |work=The Telegraph |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121102175641/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1110813/jsp/entertainment/story_14372488.jsp |archivedate=2 November 2012 |df=}}</ref> Her final appearance that year was in Rohit Dhawan's comedy-drama ''[[Desi Boyz]]'' alongside Akshay Kumar, [[John Abraham (actor)|John Abraham]] and [[Chitrangada Singh]], a role that failed to propel her career forward.<ref>{{cite web |title=Review: Desi Boyz |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-desi-boyz-676 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=12 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130917011435/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/review-desi-boyz-676 |archivedate=17 September 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Tuteja |first=Joginder |title=Exploring the Box Office journey of Deepika Padukone \u2013 Part III |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5360 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=12 August 2013 |accessdate=12 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130814144827/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/5360 |archivedate=14 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> The series of poorly received films led critics to perceive that Padukone had \"[lost] her sparkle.\"<ref name=\"making of deepika\">{{cite news |last=Pal |first=Chandrima |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-17/news-interviews/40009313_1_deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-deepika-imtiaz-ali |title=The making of Deepika Padukone |accessdate=27 July 2013 |date=17 June 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627020227/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-17/news-interviews/40009313_1_deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-deepika-imtiaz-ali |archive-date=27 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Establishing as a leading lady (2012\u20132015) ===\nPadukone has said that her starring role in the 2012 [[Homi Adajania]]-directed romantic comedy ''[[Cocktail (2012 film)|Cocktail]]'' marked a significant turning point in her career.<ref>{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Harneet |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-ranbir-kapoor-excites-me-as-an-actor-costar/1126038/0 |title=Deepika Padukone: Ranbir Kapoor excites me as an actor, co-star |work=The Indian Express |date=7 June 2013 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152538/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-ranbir-kapoor-excites-me-as-an-actor-costar/1126038/0 |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> Raja Sen of Rediff.com opined that she had successfully proved to be a \"stunning girl who can also act.\"<ref name=\"report card 2012\">{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-hows-these-bollywood-actresses-fared-in-2012/20130102.htm#3 |title=Report Card, 2012: How Kat, Kareena, Deepika performed |accessdate=27 July 2013 |date=2 January 2013 |publisher=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130508185019/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-hows-these-bollywood-actresses-fared-in-2012/20130102.htm |archivedate=8 May 2013 |df=}}</ref> Set in London, ''Cocktail'' tells the story of a man's relationship with two temperamentally different women{{mdash}}an impulsive party girl (Veronica, played by Padukone) and a submissive [[girl next door]] (Meera, played by [[Diana Penty]]). During the script narration, the producer Dinesh Vijan offered Padukone the choice of which woman to play; she decided on Veronica to expand her horizons as an actress.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/veronica-is-no-meera-deepika-padukone/story-QfD3KilX3eevBOtuKJkznO.html |title=Veronica is no Meera: Deepika |work=Hindustan Times |date=25 May 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808003227/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/veronica-is-no-meera-deepika-padukone/story-QfD3KilX3eevBOtuKJkznO.html |archivedate=8 August 2016 |df=}}</ref> Portraying the role was a creative and physical challenge for her, and to achieve the physical requirements of her character she exercised extensively and followed a rigorous diet.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/playing-veronica-in-cocktail-was-challenging-deepika-padukone/970790/0 |title=Playing Veronica in 'Cocktail' was challenging: Deepika Padukone |work=The Indian Express |date=5 May 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=http://archive.wikiwix.com/cache/20130811102927/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/playing-veronica-in-cocktail-was-challenging-deepika-padukone/970790/0 |archivedate=11 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/cocktail-deepika-padukone-daina-penty-saif-ali-khan/1/207582.html |title=Was conscious about my look in Cocktail: Deepika |work=India Today |date=11 May 2012 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCBnq5n?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/cocktail-deepika-padukone-daina-penty-saif-ali-khan/1/207582.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Critics were divided in their opinion of the film, but particularly praised Padukone's performance;<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-verdict-cocktail-works-but-in-bits/story-cFNQiVGyPXFUTKmsSUSBEN.html |title=Critics verdict: Cocktail works, but in bits |work=Hindustan Times |date=13 July 2013 |accessdate=7 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304122353/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-verdict-cocktail-works-but-in-bits/story-cFNQiVGyPXFUTKmsSUSBEN.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> Devesh Sharma of ''[[Filmfare]]'' credited her as the \"soul of the film\" and wrote that she \"excels in every scene, whether as a material girl who enjoys sex, drugs and rock and roll or as the jealousy ridden girl out to destroy herself.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Sharma |first=Devesh |title=Movie Review: Cocktail |url=http://www.filmfare.com/reviews/movie-review-cocktail-840.html |work=[[Filmfare]] |date=13 May 2012 |accessdate=29 June 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwAglv9h?url=http://www.filmfare.com/reviews/movie-review-cocktail-840.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> ''Cocktail'' earned Padukone Best Actress nominations at several award ceremonies, including Filmfare, [[Screen Award|Screen]], and [[IIFA Awards|IIFA]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/1856 |title=Deepika Padukone&nbsp;\u2014 Awards |accessdate=5 September 2013 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCqDjGs?url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/celebritymicro/awards/id/1856 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The film proved to be a box office success as well.<ref>{{cite web |title=Box Office Earnings 10/08/12 \u2013 16/08/12 |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=earnings |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=9 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825191030/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/cpages.php?pageName=earnings |archivedate=25 August 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Ranveer-Deepika at Ram Leela screening.jpg|thumb|left|upright=1|alt=Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone smiling for the camera|Padukone and [[Ranveer Singh]] at an event for ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'' in 2013. She was awarded her first [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress]] for her performance in the film.]]\n\nIn 2013, Padukone had established herself as a leading actress of Hindi cinema by featuring in four of the [[List of Bollywood films of 2013|top-grossing productions of the year]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone races to the top as top actress in Bollywood |last=Tanwar |first=Sarita |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-races-to-the-top-as-top-actress-in-bollywood-1858364 |accessdate=8 July 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131220024053/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-races-to-the-top-as-top-actress-in-bollywood-1858364 |archivedate=20 December 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"top2\">{{cite news |last=Goyal |first=Divya |title=Deepika Padukone lucky fourth time with 'Ram-Leela' |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-lucky-fourth-time-with-ramleela/1196368/ |accessdate=4 December 2013 |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=18 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152120/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-lucky-fourth-time-with-ramleela/1196368/ |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> She collaborated with Saif Ali Khan for the fourth time in [[Abbas-Mustan]]'s ''[[Race 2]]'', an ensemble action thriller that served as a sequel to ''[[Race (2008 film)|Race]]'' (2008). The film received predominantly negative reviews,<ref>{{cite news |title=Critics report: Race 2 not worth it |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-report-race-2-not-worth-it/story-QhSKezAX1YGfNcpJEyKCTJ.html |accessdate=9 March 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=25 January 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304081019/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/critics-report-race-2-not-worth-it/story-QhSKezAX1YGfNcpJEyKCTJ.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> but with a total collection of {{INRConvert|1.62|b}}, it proved to be a commercial success.<ref name=\"worldwide10\">{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |title=Worldwide Top Ten 2013 |publisher=Box Office India |accessdate=12 December 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104212753/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/boxnewsdetail.php?page=shownews&articleid=6308&nCat= |archivedate=4 January 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"cloud9\">{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone on cloud 9, Chennai Express, Ram-Leela, Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani, Race 2 big hits of 2013 |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/happy-birthday-deepika-padukone-on-cloud-9-chennai-express-ramleela-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-race-2-big-hits-of-2013/1215689?rhheader |accessdate=26 January 2014 |newspaper=The Financial Express |date=5 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201194525/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/happy-birthday-deepika-padukone-on-cloud-9-chennai-express-ramleela-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-race-2-big-hits-of-2013/1215689?rhheader |archivedate=1 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> [[Ayan Mukerji]]'s romantic comedy ''[[Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani]]'' was Padukone's next film release. Co-starring opposite Ranbir Kapoor, she was cast as Naina Talwar, a \"shy wallflower,\" which marked a departure from the glamorous characters that she had a reputation for portraying.<ref name=\"party girl\">{{cite news |last=KBR |first=Upala |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-party-girl-deepika-padukone-gets-serious-1819664 |title=Party girl Deepika Padukone gets serious |accessdate=17 August 2013 |date=7 April 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141014003716/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-party-girl-deepika-padukone-gets-serious-1819664 |archivedate=14 October 2014 |df=}}</ref> Raja Sen thought that the film \"lacked a good story\" but added that Padukone \"acts within herself and eschews exaggeration, and the results are impressive&nbsp;... This may be her most self-aware performance so far\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Sen |first=Raja |title=Review: Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani disappoints |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-disappoints/20130531.htm |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=31 May 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606072818/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/review-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-disappoints/20130531.htm |archivedate=6 June 2013 |df=}}</ref> The pairing of Padukone with her former boyfriend was anticipated,<ref>{{cite news |title=Younger generation should learn from Ranbir & Deepika: Ayan |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-01/news-interviews/39674323_1_ayan-mukerji-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone |author=Risbood, Vaibhavi |work=The Times of India |date=1 June 2013 |accessdate=12 July 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618173542/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-01/news-interviews/39674323_1_ayan-mukerji-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone |archive-date=18 June 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the film emerged as a major commercial success.<ref name=\"worldwide10\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani is Ranbir Kapoor, Deepika Padukone's biggest hit |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-is-ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-s-biggest-hit/1127672/ |accessdate=1 July 2013 |work=The Indian Express |date=1 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152212/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-is-ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-s-biggest-hit/1127672/ |archivedate=22 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> Her next appearance was opposite Shah Rukh Khan in [[Rohit Shetty]]'s action-comedy film ''[[Chennai Express]]'', as a [[Tamil people|Tamil girl]] on the run from her father (a local [[boss (crime)|don]]), which required that she adopt a Tamil accent. Critical opinion on her accent was mixed,<ref>{{cite news |title=Not spoofing South India in Chennai Express: Deepika Padukone |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/not-spoofing-south-india-in-chennai-express-says-deepika-padukone/1/298317.html |accessdate=13 August 2013 |work=India Today |date=6 August 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCFXjFR?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/not-spoofing-south-india-in-chennai-express-says-deepika-padukone/1/298317.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> but her performance received praise;<ref name=\"high\">{{cite news |last=Uniyal |first=Parmita |title=Deepika Padukone rides on a high graph express |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-gets-critical-acclaim-rides-on-a-high-graph-express/article1-1107578.aspx |accessdate=13 August 2013 |work=Hindustan Times |date=13 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101105157/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-gets-critical-acclaim-rides-on-a-high-graph-express/article1-1107578.aspx |archivedate=1 January 2014 |df=}}</ref> film critic Aseem Chhabra wrote, \"Padukone is delightful in the film{{mdash}}beautiful, smiling, and often a lot more playful and funny than Khan.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Chhabra |first=Aseem |title=Aseem Chhabra's Chennai Express Review: Mindless but entertaining |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/aseem-chhabras-chennai-express-review-mindless-but-entertaining/20130809.htm |publisher=Rediff |date=9 August 2013 |accessdate=10 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130811184158/http://www.rediff.com/movies/review/aseem-chhabras-chennai-express-review-mindless-but-entertaining/20130809.htm |archivedate=11 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> ''Chennai Express'' earned  over {{INRConvert|3.95|b}} to emerge as one of the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|highest-grossing Indian films]].<ref name=\"box office\">{{cite web |title=Top Worldwide Grossers All Time |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/worldwide-total-gross.php |publisher=Box Office India |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180107113404/http://boxofficeindia.com/worldwide-total-gross.php |archivedate=7 January 2018 |accessdate=5 February 2018 |url-status=live |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone next played opposite [[Ranveer Singh]] in ''[[Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela]]'', an adaptation of the [[Shakespearean tragedy]] of ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'' from director [[Sanjay Leela Bhansali]]. Her role was Leela, a [[Gujarati people|Gujarati girl]] based on the character of [[Juliet]].<ref>{{cite news |title=First look Ram Leela: Meet Romeo Ranveer and Juliet Deepika |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |work=India Today |accessdate=16 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCOFmHR?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/first-poster-of-ram-leela-ranveer-singh-deepika-padukone/1/247370.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Initially titled ''Ram-Leela'', the film's title was changed after a court case was registered against Bhansali, Padukone, and Singh for \"offending the religious sentiments\" of the Hindu community by showcasing sex and violence under a title that referred to the life of [[Rama]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Sura |first=Ajay |title=Controversy over 'Ram Leela': HC stays arrest of Bhansali, Ranveer and Deepika |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-11-14/india/44073111_1_ram-leela-ranveer-singh-delhi-high-court |accessdate=16 November 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=14 November 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131117095053/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-11-14/india/44073111_1_ram-leela-ranveer-singh-delhi-high-court |archive-date=17 November 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' released among protests across several states in India, but was generally well received by critics.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ram-Leela faces protest in several states |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-ram-leela-faces-protest-in-several-states-1919790 |accessdate=16 November 2013 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131118080509/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-ram-leela-faces-protest-in-several-states-1919790 |archivedate=18 November 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Uniyal |first=Parmita |title=Movie review: Bhansali's Ram-leela is his best ever, say critics |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/story-cdj9US9WMi2M58gcg56YNI.html |accessdate=15 November 2013 |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=15 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304070929/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/movie-review-bhansali-s-ram-leela-is-his-best-ever-say-critics/story-cdj9US9WMi2M58gcg56YNI.html |archivedate=4 March 2016 |df=}}</ref> Meena Iyer of ''The Times of India'' mentioned Padukone as \"breathtaking\", and writing for ''[[Deccan Chronicle]]'', [[Khalid Mohamed]] concluded that \"it's Deepika Padukone whom the film belongs to. Looking drop dead gorgeous and going at her part with a wallop, she's the prime asset of ''Ram-Leela''.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Iyer |first=Meena |title=Ram-Leela |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/Ram-Leela/movie-review/25770699.cms |accessdate=15 November 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=14 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131115000038/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/hindi/ram-leela/movie-review/25770699.cms |archivedate=15 November 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mohamed |first=Khalid |title='Ram-Leela' Review: The good, the bard and the beautiful |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131115/entertainment-movie-reviews/article/ram-leela-review-good-bard-and-beautiful |accessdate=16 November 2013 |work=Deccan Chronicle |date=16 November 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131116102722/http://deccanchronicle.com/131115/entertainment-movie-reviews/article/ram-leela-review-good-bard-and-beautiful |archivedate=16 November 2013 |df=}}</ref> Her performances in ''Chennai Express'' and ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' won her several awards,<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika is toast of this award season |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/deepika-padukone-is-toast-of-this-award-season/1/343781.html |accessdate=16 February 2014 |work=India Today |date=17 February 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140216064856/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/deepika-padukone-is-toast-of-this-award-season/1/343781.html |archivedate=16 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> including the [[Screen Award for Best Actress]] for both films and the Filmfare Award for Best Actress for the latter.<ref>{{cite web |title=Winners of 20th Annual Life OK Screen Awards |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6026 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |date=14 January 2014 |accessdate=17 February 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116181505/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/6026 |archivedate=16 January 2014 |df=}}</ref><ref name=\"ff13\">{{cite web |title=Filmfare Awards 2014: Deepika Padukone wins Best Actress award, Farhan Akhtar Best Actor |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-2014-deepika-padukone-wins-best-actress-award-farhan-akhtar-best-actor/447639-8-66.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |date=25 January 2014 |accessdate=25 January 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140125110704/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/filmfare-awards-2014-deepika-padukone-wins-best-actress-award-farhan-akhtar-best-actor/447639-8-66.html |archivedate=25 January 2014 |df=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Padukone featured opposite [[Rajinikanth]] in the [[Tamil cinema|Tamil film]] ''[[Kochadaiiyaan]]'', a period drama that was shot using [[motion capture]] technology.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/kochadaiiyaan-released-nationwide-rajinikanth-turns-movemaking-pioneer-in-india/1253639 |title='Kochadaiiyaan' released nationwide, Rajinikanth turns moviemaking pioneer in India |work=[[The Financial Express (India)|The Financial Express]] |date=23 March 2014 |agency=Press Trust of India |accessdate=23 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140523230850/http://www.financialexpress.com/news/kochadaiiyaan-released-nationwide-rajinikanth-turns-movemaking-pioneer-in-india/1253639 |archivedate=23 May 2014 |df=}}</ref> She was paid {{INRConvert|30|m}} for two days worth of work in it.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/deepika-padukone-films-rajinikanth-s-kochadaiiyaan-for-two-days-only_143262.html |title=Deepika Padukone shoots Rajinikanth\u2019s `Kochadaiiyaan` for two days only! |publisher=Zee News |date=23 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926173744/http://zeenews.india.com/entertainment/movies/deepika-padukone-films-rajinikanth-s-kochadaiiyaan-for-two-days-only_143262.html |archivedate=26 September 2013 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-gets-3-cr-for-2-day-shoot-in-Rajnis-film/articleshow/22508894.cms |title=Deepika gets 3 cr for 2 day shoot in Rajni\u2019s film? |work=The Times of India |date=12 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130912235545/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-gets-3-cr-for-2-day-shoot-in-Rajnis-film/articleshow/22508894.cms |archivedate=12 September 2013 |df=}}</ref> In Homi Adajania's praised satire ''[[Finding Fanny]]'', Padukone played a young widow who takes a road trip with her dysfunctional friends (played by [[Arjun Kapoor]], [[Naseeruddin Shah]], [[Dimple Kapadia]] and [[Pankaj Kapur]]) in search of a woman named Fanny.<ref>{{cite news |last=Mehta |first=Ankita |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/finding-fanny-movie-review-must-watch-film-brilliant-performances-608764 |title='Finding Fanny' Movie Review: Must Watch Film with Brilliant Performances |date=10 September 2014 |work=[[International Business Times]] |accessdate=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140911015405/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/finding-fanny-movie-review-must-watch-film-brilliant-performances-608764 |archivedate=11 September 2014 |df=}}</ref> The film was screened at the [[19th Busan International Film Festival]];<ref>{{cite news |last=Vyavahare |first=Renuka |title=Finding Fanny selected for Busan Film Festival |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Finding-Fanny-selected-for-Busan-Film-Festival/articleshow/41878021.cms |accessdate=12 September 2014 |work=The Times of India |date=6 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140909044509/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Finding-Fanny-selected-for-Busan-Film-Festival/articleshow/41878021.cms |archivedate=9 September 2014 |df=}}</ref> critic Anuj Kumar of ''[[The Hindu]]'' wrote that Padukone successfully \"takes off the fineries of Bollywood and you can sense the freedom from baggage in her performance\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Kumar |first=Anuj |title=Finding fanny: Lost and found |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/finding-fanny-review/article6404665.ece |work=The Hindu |accessdate=29 November 2014 |date=12 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141205215445/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/finding-fanny-review/article6404665.ece |archivedate=5 December 2014 |df=}}</ref> Later that year, she starred opposite Shah Rukh Khan for the third time in Farah Khan's renewal of ''Happy New Year''. She played a bar dancer who trains a group of underachievers for a dance competition. Sanjukta Sharma of ''[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]'' found her role to be of minimal importance that required her only to be \"a pretty thing to be laughed at and pitied\", but the film became one of her most successful, earning over {{INRConvert|3.4|b}} worldwide.<ref name=\"box office\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Sharma |first=Sanjukta |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/RbQFYNOCmIXFirlKS1t0kI/Film-Review--Happy-New-Year.html |title=Film Review Happy New Year |date=4 September 2013 |accessdate=24 October 2014 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024170656/http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/RbQFYNOCmIXFirlKS1t0kI/Film-Review--Happy-New-Year.html |archivedate=24 October 2014 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Deepika Padukone promoting Bajirao Mastani (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|alt=A headshot shot of Deepika Padukone|Padukone at an event for ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'' in 2015]]\n\nFollowing an appearance in Homi Adajania's online video on [[Feminism in India|feminism]], entitled ''My Choice'',<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone: Bollywood actress urges women to own their 'choice' over marriage, sex and sexuality |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/deepika-padukone-bollywood-actress-urges-women-to-own-their-choice-over-marriage-sex-and-sexuality-10145843.html |work=[[The Independent]] |date=31 March 2015 |accessdate=1 April 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150331183715/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/deepika-padukone-bollywood-actress-urges-women-to-own-their-choice-over-marriage-sex-and-sexuality-10145843.html |archivedate=31 March 2015 |df=}}</ref> Padukone took on the role of a headstrong [[Bengali people|Bengali]] architect who cares for her hypochondriac father (played by Amitabh Bachchan), in [[Shoojit Sircar]]'s comedy-drama ''[[Piku]]'' (2015). She was drawn to the depiction of a realistic father-daughter bond, which she thought was rare in Hindi cinema.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ratnam |first=Dhamini |title=Objectifying me, that is not done: Deepika Padukone |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |work=Mint |date=27 December 2014 |accessdate=25 January 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509232711/http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |archivedate=9 May 2016}}</ref> Reviews for the film were positive;<ref>{{cite web |last=Mehta |first=Ankita |title='Piku' Review Roundup: A Film that's all Heart |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/piku-review-roundup-simple-classy-charming-film-631700 |work=International Business Times |date=7 May 2015 |accessdate=10 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509200624/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/piku-review-roundup-simple-classy-charming-film-631700 |archivedate=9 May 2015 |df=}}</ref> Tanmaya Nanda of ''[[Business Standard]]'' praised the film's feminist tone, and wrote that Padukone proves \"what she is capable of when given something more to do than look pretty and be the crazy-dance girl at parties\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Nanda |first=Tanmaya |title=Film Review: Piku is a delightfully brilliant film |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |work=[[Business Standard]] |date=8 May 2015 |accessdate=9 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160509232711/http://www.business-standard.com/article/specials/film-review-piku-is-a-quietly-brilliant-film-115050800287_1.html |archivedate=9 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> NDTV's Saibal Chatterjee opined that she \"holds ''Piku'' together with a restrained star turn\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Chatterjee |first=Saibal |title=Piku Movie Review |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/piku-movie-review-1124 |publisher=NDTV |date=8 May 2015 |accessdate=10 May 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150510190128/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie-reviews/piku-movie-review-1124 |archivedate=10 May 2015 |df=}}</ref> With a worldwide gross of over {{INRConvert|1.40|b}}, ''Piku'' emerged as a box office hit, and garnered Padukone several awards, including second Best Actress awards at Filmfare and Screen.<ref name=\"filmfare16\">{{cite news |title=Victory dance for Team 'Bajirao Mastani' at the Filmfare Awards |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Victory-dance-for-Team-Bajirao-Mastani-at-the-Filmfare-Awards/articleshow/50604444.cms |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=The Times of India |date=17 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160121183819/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Victory-dance-for-Team-Bajirao-Mastani-at-the-Filmfare-Awards/articleshow/50604444.cms |archivedate=21 January 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ghosh |first=Raya |title=Screen Awards 2016: Complete List of Winners |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/screen-awards-2016-complete-list-of-winners-1263815 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=9 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160110051251/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/screen-awards-2016-complete-list-of-winners-1263815 |archivedate=10 January 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n\nLater in 2015, Padukone played the part of a businessperson who helps Ranbir Kapoor's character overcome his conflicts in Imtiaz Ali's romantic drama ''[[Tamasha (2015 film)|Tamasha]]''. Despite poor financial returns, Sukanya Verma of Rediff.com named Padukone's performance as the best by an actress that year, writing that she \"is so potent in ''Tamasha'', it's almost as if you can hear her heartbeat across the screen\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Khuranaa |first=Amann |title=Deepika Padukone reacts to Tamasha's box-office failure |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-reacts-to-Tamashas-box-office-failure/articleshow/50186402.cms |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=The Times of India |date=15 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151218163236/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-reacts-to-Tamashas-box-office-failure/articleshow/50186402.cms |archivedate=18 December 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Verma |first=Sukanya |title=Sukanya Verma's Best Actresses of 2015 |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sukanya-vermas-best-actresses-of-2015/20151224.htm |date=24 December 2015 |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=24 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123175703/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/sukanya-vermas-best-actresses-of-2015/20151224.htm |archivedate=23 January 2016 |df=}}</ref> In her final release of 2015, Padukone reunited with Sanjay Leela Bhansali and Ranveer Singh in ''[[Bajirao Mastani]]'', a historical drama about a tragic extramarital affair. Singh was cast as the [[maratha]] general [[Bajirao I]], while [[Priyanka Chopra]] and Padukone featured as his first and second wife, respectively. To play the warrior-princess [[Mastani]], Padukone learnt sword-fighting, horse-riding, and the martial art form of [[kalaripayattu]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Awaasthi |first=Kavita |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-learn-sword-fighting-for-bajirao-mastani/story-KUjvxij1mi4pBQyOLkzWrM.html |title=Deepika Padukone to learn sword-fighting for Bajirao Mastani |work=Hindutan Times |date=23 January 2015 |accessdate=19 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222163238/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-learn-sword-fighting-for-bajirao-mastani/story-KUjvxij1mi4pBQyOLkzWrM.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref> With a revenue of over {{INRConvert|3.5|b}}, ''Bajirao Mastani'' proved to be the [[List of Bollywood films of 2015|fourth highest-grossing Bollywood film of the year]].<ref name=\"box office\" /> [[Anupama Chopra]] found Padukone \"riveting\", but [[Subhash K. Jha]] thought that she was \"way too subtle and silken, and not steely enough\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Chopra |first=Anupama |title=Bajirao Mastani review by Anupama Chopra: Soaring, searing, sumptuous |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/bajirao-mastani-review-by-anupama-chopra-soaring-searing-sumptuous/story-gZmskukJnTmbRtcS15D3XK.html |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=Hindustan Times |date=22 December 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116085552/http://www.hindustantimes.com/movie-reviews/bajirao-mastani-review-by-anupama-chopra-soaring-searing-sumptuous/story-gZmskukJnTmbRtcS15D3XK.html |archivedate=16 January 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Jha |first=Subhash K. |title=Subhash K Jha speaks about Bajirao Mastani |date=19 December 2015 |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9439 |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=24 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119175354/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movies/features/type/view/id/9439 |archivedate=19 January 2016 |df=}}</ref> The film was showcased at the [[International Film Festival of India]];<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/IP_press_release_2016_Final.pdf |title=Indian Panorama Selections for 47th International Film Festival of India, 2016: Press Release|access-date=25 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112080152/http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/IP_press_release_2016_Final.pdf |archivedate=12 November 2016}}</ref> at the [[61st Filmfare Awards]], ''Bajirao Mastani'' was named [[Filmfare Award for Best Film|Best Film]] and Padukone received her second Best Actress nomination in that year.<ref name=\"filmfare16\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Nominations for the 61st Britannia Filmfare Awards |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11809.html |accessdate=24 January 2016 |work=Filmfare |date=11 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6gO32fdDO?url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/nominations-for-the-61st-britannia-filmfare-awards-11809.html |archivedate=30 March 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n\n=== Professional expansion (2017\u2013present) ===\nThe action film ''[[XXX: Return of Xander Cage]]'' (2017), in which Padukone played the lead female role of Serena Unger, opposite [[Vin Diesel]], marked her first project in [[Cinema of the United States|Hollywood]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Goyal |first=Divya |title=Deepika Padukone Wraps xXx 3 Shoot and in Such Style |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/hollywood/deepika-padukone-wraps-xxx-3-shoot-and-in-such-style-1405905 |publisher=NDTV |date=13 May 2016 |accessdate=14 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160513123136/http://movies.ndtv.com/hollywood/deepika-padukone-wraps-xxx-3-shoot-and-in-such-style-1405905 |archivedate=13 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> Critical reception of the film was mixed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/xxx_return_of_xander_cage |title=xXx: Return of Xander Cage (2017) |publisher=Rotten Tomatoes |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119223913/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/xxx_return_of_xander_cage |archivedate=19 January 2017 |df=}}</ref> Tirdad Derakhshani of ''[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]'' termed the film a \"repetitious heap of remarkably tedious CGI-enhanced action scenes\" and thought that Padukone's talent was wasted in it.<ref>{{cite news |last=Derakhshani |first=Tirdad |url=http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/Vin-Diesels-xXx.html |title=Vin Diesel\u2019s \u2018xXx: Return of Xander Cage\u2019: Abysmal, unwatchable, embarrassing |work=[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]] |date=20 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170123172631/http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/movies/Vin-Diesels-xXx.html |archive-date=23 January 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> Conversely, Frank Scheck of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' believed that she had successfully \"outclassed\" Diesel to \"practically [steal] the film\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Scheck |first=Frank |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/xxx-return-xander-review-965998 |title='xXx: Return of Xander Cage': Film Review |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=19 January 2017 |accessdate=20 January 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120024920/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/xxx-return-xander-review-965998 |archivedate=20 January 2017 |df=}}</ref> The film earned over US$345 million worldwide, a majority of which came from the Chinese box office.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=xxx3.htm |title=xXx: Return of Xander Cage |publisher=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=8 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170329021315/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=xxx3.htm |archivedate=29 March 2017 |df=}}</ref> Padukone received three nominations at the [[Teen Choice Awards]] and followed it with an item number in the romantic drama ''[[Raabta (film)|Raabta]]''.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominees |title=Teen Choice Awards 2017: See the First Wave of Nominations |last=Ceron |first=Ella |work=[[Teen Vogue]] |date=19 June 2017 |accessdate=20 June 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6rLtVsNex?url=http://www.teenvogue.com/story/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominees |archivedate=20 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Shcherbakova |first=Lisa |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7865210/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominations-second-wave |title=Selena Gomez Leads Second Wave of Teen Choice Awards 2017 Nominations |work=Billboard |date=12 July 2017|access-date=14 July 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170714060829/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7865210/teen-choice-awards-2017-nominations-second-wave |archivedate=14 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Watch: Deepika Padukone takes flexibility to a new level for dance number in 'Raabta' |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-watch-deepika-padukone-takes-flexibility-to-a-new-level-for-dance-number-in-raabta-2218761 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=1 June 2016 |accessdate=2 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160602145415/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-watch-deepika-padukone-takes-flexibility-to-a-new-level-for-dance-number-in-raabta-2218761 |archivedate=2 June 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Deepika Padukone at Chhapaak premiere.jpg|thumb|upright|left|Padukone at the premiere of ''[[Chhapaak]]'' (2020), which marked her first production venture]]\n\nIn 2018, Padukone portrayed [[Rani Padmini|Rani Padmavati]], a [[Rajput]] queen who commits ''[[jauhar]]'' (self-immolation) to protect herself from the [[Muslim]] invader [[Alauddin Khalji|Alauddin Khilji]], in the period drama ''[[Padmaavat]]''; it marked her third collaboration with Bhansali and Singh.<ref>{{cite news |title=It's official! Sanjay Leela Bhansali's Padmavati to release in 2017 |url=http://www.filmfare.com/news/its-official-sanjay-leela-bhansalis-padmavati-to-release-in-2017_-16000.html |work=Filmfare |date=10 October 2016 |accessdate=10 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011140218/http://www.filmfare.com/news/its-official-sanjay-leela-bhansalis-padmavati-to-release-in-2017_-16000.html |archivedate=11 October 2016 |df=}}</ref> She was challenged by the need to convey her character's courage through silence and considered it to be the most emotionally exhausting role of her career.<ref name=\"filmfare17\">{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Raghuvendra |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/the-empress-strikes-back-25241.html |title=Deepika Padukone chats with Filmfare about Padmavati, Ranveer Singh & more in her exclusive interview |date=24 November 2017 |work=Filmfare |accessdate=25 January 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180125193654/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/the-empress-strikes-back-25241.html |archivedate=25 January 2018}}</ref> She read history books on the era and researched the various historical depictions of Padmavati.<ref name=\"filmfare17\" /> [[Saffron terror|Right-wing Hindu groups]] speculated that the film portrayed a romantic liaison between Padmavati and Khilji; they protested violently and placed a bounty to behead Padukone and Bhansali.<ref>{{cite news |last=Ray |first=Saptarshi |title=Bounty placed on Bollywood actress' head after Hindu-Muslim film outrage |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=17 November 2017 |accessdate=2 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171118052745/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/11/17/bounty-placed-bollywood-actress-head-hindu-muslim-film-outrage/ |archivedate=18 November 2017}}</ref> Following a deferment in release, the film was cleared for exhibition after several modifications were made to it.<ref>{{cite news |title=Padmavati release deferred after protests, Sanjay Leela Bhansali film not to come out on Dec 1 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/padmavati-release-postponed-not-to-come-out-on-december-1/story-AAMT5dPtRloBAmSdqR4NRL.html |accessdate=19 November 2017 |work=Hindustan Times |date=19 November 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171119113357/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/padmavati-release-postponed-not-to-come-out-on-december-1/story-AAMT5dPtRloBAmSdqR4NRL.html |archivedate=19 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855 |title=Censor Board Wants \"Padmavati\" Renamed \"Padmavat\", 5 Changes To Film |publisher=NDTV |date=30 December 2017 |accessdate=30 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171230133652/https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/film-padmavati-to-get-ua-certificate-title-may-be-changed-to-padmavat-1793855 |archivedate=30 December 2017}}</ref> [[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' criticised the film's glorification of ''jauhar'', but credited Padukone for managing to \"eke something out of the stereotype-ridden writing\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Vetticad |first=Anna MM |title=Padmaavat movie review: Bhansali couches regressive, opportunistic messaging in exhausting visual splendour |url=http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/padmaavat-padmavati-padmavat-movie-review-bhansali-couches-regressive-opportunistic-messaging-in-exhausting-visual-splendour-4317153.html |website=[[Firstpost]] |date=24 January 2018 |accessdate=24 January 2018 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180124090649/http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/padmaavat-padmavati-padmavat-movie-review-bhansali-couches-regressive-opportunistic-messaging-in-exhausting-visual-splendour-4317153.html |archivedate=24 January 2018}}</ref> With an estimated budget of {{INRConvert|2|b}}, ''Padmaavat'' is [[List of most expensive Indian films#Hindi|one of the most expensive Hindi films]], and with earnings of {{INRConvert|5.45|b}}, it is Padukone's highest-grossing release and one of Indian cinema's biggest grossers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469 |title=Padmavati Being Aimed For A February Release |publisher=Box Office India |date=8 December 2017 |accessdate=8 December 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171208231459/http://www.boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3469 |archivedate=8 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881 |title=Worldwide Alltime : Padmaavat 7th \u2013 Baaghi 2 22nd |accessdate=26 April 2018 |date=26 April 2018 |publisher=Box Office India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180426213042/https://boxofficeindia.com/report-details.php?articleid=3881 |archive-date=26 April 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> She received another Best Actress nomination at Filmfare.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |title=Nominations for the 64th Vimal Filmfare Awards 2019 |work=Filmfare |date=12 March 2019 |access-date=13 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190316052927/https://www.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-64th-vimal-filmfare-awards-2019_-32898-1.html |archive-date=16 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFollowing the success of ''Padmaavat'', Padukone took some time off work to focus on her home and family.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chaurasia |first=Ankita |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-karan-johar-was-only-joking-when-he-said-ill-make-a-good-producer/articleshow/72985903.cms|title=Deepika Padukone: Karan Johar was only joking when he said I'll make a good producer |work=Mumbai Mirror |date=27 December 2019 |access-date=9 January 2020 }}</ref> In 2018, she formed her own company, named Ka Productions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bhattacharya |first=Roshmilla |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-turns-producer-for-meghna-gulzars-next-directorial/articleshow/66077252.cms |title=Deepika Padukone turns producer for Meghna Gulzar's next directorial |work=Mumbai Mirror |date=5 October 2018 |access-date=5 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005052344/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-turns-producer-for-meghna-gulzars-next-directorial/articleshow/66077252.cms |archive-date=5 October 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Her first production venture came with ''[[Chhapaak]]'' (2020), a drama by [[Meghna Gulzar]], in which she starred as an [[acid attack]] survivor (based on [[Laxmi Agarwal]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/deepikas-next-chhapaak-is-a-story-of-undying-human-spirit/articleshow/68549587.cms|title=Deepika\u2019s next 'Chhapaak' is a story of undying human spirit|newspaper=The Times Of India|date=25 March 2019|accessdate=25 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190325025119/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/deepikas-next-chhapaak-is-a-story-of-undying-human-spirit/articleshow/68549587.cms|archive-date=25 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> She found it taxing to film in extreme heat wearing prosthetic makeup on her face, and considered it to be the most physically challenging role of her career.<ref>{{cite web |last=Ghosh |first=Devarsi |url=https://scroll.in/reel/948467/deepika-padukone-on-chhapaak-this-was-my-most-physically-challenging-film|title=Deepika Padukone on \u2018Chhapaak\u2019: \u2018This was my most physically challenging film\u2019 |website=[[Scroll.in]] |date=4 January 2020 |access-date=5 January 2020 }}</ref> Shubhra Gupta of ''[[The Indian Express]]'' credited her for \"not just putting the focus on the ravaged-skin-with a missing ear-and-nostril, but reflecting a mix of pain, anger, resignation, and finally, arriving at some kind of resolution\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Gupta |first=Shubhra |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/chhapaak-movie-review-rating-deepika-padukone-6207416/|title=Chhapaak movie review: Deepika Padukone delivers a solid, realised performance |work=The Indian Express |date=9 January 2020 |access-date=9 January 2020 }}</ref> Teo Bugbee of ''[[The New York Times]]'' added that \"Padukone is by turns inquisitive, watchful and serene but never maudlin\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Bugbee |first=Teo |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/10/movies/chhapaak-review.html|title=Chhapaak Review: Life and Activism After an Acid Attack |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=10 January 2020 |access-date=10 January 2020 }}</ref> It did not perform well commercially.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jha|first=Subhash K.|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/features/much-lauded-deepika-padukone-starrer-chhapaak-crashes-box-office-trade-experts-analyse/|title=The much lauded Deepika Padukone starrer Chhapaak crashes at the box office, trade experts analyse|website=Bollywood Hungama|date=18 January 2020|accessdate=18 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nPadukone's next production venture will be ''[[83 (film)|83]]'', a sports film about India's victory at the [[1983 Cricket World Cup]], starring Ranveer Singh as [[Kapil Dev]], in which she will also take on the role of Dev's wife, Romi.<ref>{{cite web |author=Mishra, Shambhavi |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/deepika-padukone-wants-to-spend-time-with-kapil-dev-s-wife-romi-for-83-prep-details-here/434039 |title=Deepika Padukone wants to spend time with Kapil Dev\u2019s wife Romi for \u201883 prep - details here |website=Times Now |date=10 June 2019 |access-date=10 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190610061110/https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/deepika-padukone-wants-to-spend-time-with-kapil-dev-s-wife-romi-for-83-prep-details-here/434039 |archive-date=10 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She has committed to star alongside [[Siddhant Chaturvedi]] and [[Ananya Panday]] in [[Shakun Batra]]'s as-yet untitled romantic drama, and to portray [[Draupadi]] in a retelling of the ''[[Mahabharata]]'' from her character's perspective, which she will also be producing.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-teams-up-with-ananya-panday-sidhant-chaturvedi-for-shakun-batra-s-relationship-drama/story-ruLfnemT6A88Xju7a79kqO.html |title=Deepika Padukone teams up with Ananya Panday, Sidhant Chaturvedi for Shakun Batra\u2019s relationship drama |work=Hindustan Times |date=19 December 2019 |access-date=19 December 2019 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-play-draupadi-in-next-this-perspective-on-mahabharata-will-be-interesting-significant/story-SAaHdtLN7UwlIlUYWruyWN.html |title=Deepika Padukone to play Draupadi in next: \u2018This perspective on Mahabharata will be interesting, significant\u2019 |work=Hindustan Times |date=25 October 2019 |access-date=25 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191025041303/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-to-play-draupadi-in-next-this-perspective-on-mahabharata-will-be-interesting-significant/story-SAaHdtLN7UwlIlUYWruyWN.html |archive-date=25 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Padukone will also produce and star in a remake of the American comedy film ''[[The Intern (2015 film)|The Intern]]'', co-starring [[Rishi Kapoor]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Ramachandran|first=Naman|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/asia/deepika-padukone-rishi-kapoor-bollywood-remake-the-intern-1203481933/|title=Deepika Padukone and Rishi Kapoor to star in Bollywood Remake of \u2018The Intern\u2019|work=Variety|date=27 January 2020|accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life  ==\n[[File:Deepika Padukone and Ranveer Singh reception.jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|Singh and Padukone at their wedding reception in 2018]]\nPadukone shares a close bond with her family, and visits them regularly in her hometown of Bangalore.<ref>{{cite news |author=Muthanna, Anjali |title=Deepika makes time for family in Bangalore |date=25 May 2013 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-25/news-interviews/39520879_1_deepika-padukone-bangalore-girl-yjhd |work=The Times of India |accessdate=25 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194307/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-25/news-interviews/39520879_1_deepika-padukone-bangalore-girl-yjhd |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She lives in [[Prabhadevi]], a neighbourhood in Mumbai, and has admitted to missing the presence of her parents there.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone's South Indian home |date=7 November 2011 |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2505006891.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=4 September 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410000136/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2505006891.html |archivedate=10 April 2016 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Ahmed, Afsana |title=I want to be the first girl Ranbir Kapoor directs: Deepika Padukone |date=23 June 2013 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-want-to-be-the-first-girl-ranbir-kapoor-directs-deepika-padukone/story-YHxXvKq8N4PFSgD1glVKEP.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=4 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203134412/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/i-want-to-be-the-first-girl-ranbir-kapoor-directs-deepika-padukone/story-YHxXvKq8N4PFSgD1glVKEP.html |archivedate=3 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> A practicing [[Hindu]], Padukone considers religion to be an important aspect of her life and makes frequent visits to [[Hindu temple|temples]] and other religious shrines.<ref>{{cite news |author=Batra, Ankur |title=Deepika Padukone on a religious trip |date=8 September 2011 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-08/news-interviews/30123474_1_deepika-padukone-golden-temple-morning-walkers |work=The Times of India |accessdate=25 May 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194315/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-08/news-interviews/30123474_1_deepika-padukone-golden-temple-morning-walkers |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nWhile filming ''Bachna Ae Haseeno'' in 2008, Padukone began a romantic relationship with co-star Ranbir Kapoor.<ref>{{cite web |title=I've been dating Deepika for few weeks: Ranbir Kapoor |date=17 March 2008 |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/i-ve-been-dating-deepika-for-a-few-weeks-ranbir-kapoor-news-bollywood-kkftL3hfdja.html |accessdate=17 March 2008 |publisher=[[Sify]] |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101231090325/http://www.sify.com/movies/i-ve-been-dating-deepika-for-a-few-weeks-ranbir-kapoor-news-bollywood-kkftL3hfdja.html |archivedate=31 December 2010 |df=}}</ref> She spoke openly about the relationship and sported a tattoo of his initials on the nape of her neck.<ref>{{cite news |last=Behrawala |first=Krutika |title=Tattoo Tales |date=17 August 2012 |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/tattoo-tales/987803/ |accessdate=4 September 2013 |work=The Indian Express |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208095326/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/tattoo-tales/987803 |archivedate=8 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> She has said that the relationship had a profound effect on her, transforming her into a more confident and social person.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> The Indian media speculated on an engagement, and reported that this had occurred in November 2008, although Padukone had stated that she had no plans to marry within the next five years.<ref>{{cite book |title=Drum |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_OosAQAAIAAJ |year=2008 |publisher=Drum Publications (East Africa) |page=98 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131114120425/http://books.google.com/books?id=_OosAQAAIAAJ |archivedate=14 November 2013 |df=}}</ref> The couple broke up a year later;<ref>{{cite news |author=Lalwani, Vickey |title=Deepika-Ranbir call it quits! |date=3 November 2009 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-03/news-interviews/28091798_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-nihar-pandya |work=The Times of India |accessdate=10 December 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025161535/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-11-03/news-interviews/28091798_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-nihar-pandya |archive-date=25 October 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> she professed in an interview to feeling betrayed for a long time.<ref name=\"toi interview\" /> In a 2010 interview, Padukone accused him of infidelity, and Kapoor later admitted to it.<ref>{{cite news |title=He cheated on me: Deepika |date=28 September 2010 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/he-cheated-on-me-deepika/story-Yb1QlWYJgHy9rIyGhoaWJP.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=4 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151117032126/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/he-cheated-on-me-deepika/story-Yb1QlWYJgHy9rIyGhoaWJP.html |archivedate=17 November 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Punoose, Rukhmini |title=Deepika on a dream run |url=http://www.verveonline.com/89/people/deepika.shtml |work=Verve |accessdate=4 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBCdTkQ?url=http://www.verveonline.com/89/people/deepika.shtml |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Yes, I cheated: Ranbir |date=30 September 2011 |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-30/news-interviews/30229828_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-relationship |work=The Times of India |accessdate=4 September 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203192202/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-09-30/news-interviews/30229828_1_ranbir-kapoor-deepika-padukone-relationship |archive-date=3 December 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> They reconciled their friendship while working on ''Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani''.<ref>{{cite news |title='Ranbir and I have become a lot closer now' \u2013 Deepika Padukone |last=Tandon |first=Raedita |date=28 June 2013 |url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/ranbir-and-i-have-become-a-lot-closer-now-deepika-padukone-3546.html |work=Filmfare |accessdate=4 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwAucO9G?url=http://www.filmfare.com/interviews/ranbir-and-i-have-become-a-lot-closer-now-deepika-padukone-3546.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\nPadukone subsequently became reticent to discuss her personal life, but in 2017, she fondly spoke of her relationship with her frequent co-star [[Ranveer Singh]], whom she began dating in 2012.<ref name=\"filmfare17\" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Choudhary|first=Anuradha|title=Exclusive and explosive: Deepika Padukone\u2019s first interview after marriage |url=https://www.filmfare.com/interviews/exclusive-and-explosive-deepika-padukones-first-interview-after-marriage-31906.html |work=Filmfare |date=28 December 2018 |accessdate=8 January 2020 }}</ref> In November 2018, the couple married in traditional Konkani and Sindhi ceremonies at [[Lake Como]], Italy.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone, Ranveer Singh are married now, wedding ceremony ends in Italy |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-are-married-now-wedding-ceremony-ends-in-italy/story-OrrIJnMvTwI1wSwl7JbWqM.html |work=Hindustan Times |date=14 November 2018 |accessdate=14 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114143025/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/deepika-padukone-ranveer-singh-are-married-now-wedding-ceremony-ends-in-italy/story-OrrIJnMvTwI1wSwl7JbWqM.html |archive-date=14 November 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n== Off-screen work ==\n\nIn addition to acting, Padukone has written opinion columns and has been involved with women's health and fitness magazines. She has also supported charitable organisations, and has performed for stage shows. In 2009, she was hired by ''Hindustan Times'' to write weekly columns for their lifestyle section; through these columns she interacted with her fans and passed details of her personal and professional life.<ref>{{cite news |last=Padukone |first=Deepika |title=My nervous excitement |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/my-nervous-excitement/story-cd9szDgxJirCJBRYiRSANO.html |work=Hindustan Times |date=27 July 2009 |accessdate=7 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222115730/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/my-nervous-excitement/story-cd9szDgxJirCJBRYiRSANO.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Padukone |first=Deepika |title=Our love stays: Deepika |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/our-love-stays-deepika/story-g90A33jkUB0aliIisrjLmJ.html |work=Hindustan Times |date=12 October 2009 |accessdate=7 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222091753/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/our-love-stays-deepika/story-g90A33jkUB0aliIisrjLmJ.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref> That year, she participated in the [[World 10K Bangalore]] marathon, which raised {{INRConvert|13.1|m}} in support of 81&nbsp;NGOs.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika for charity |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-07-22/people/28169980_1_charity-event-bangaloreans |accessdate=24 June 2013 |newspaper=The Times of India |date=22 July 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928200019/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-07-22/people/28169980_1_charity-event-bangaloreans |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone raises Rs 1.3 crore for several charities |url=http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2009/jul/090709-Bollywood-Bengaluru-Deepika-Padukone-marathon-1-crore-charity.htm |accessdate=24 June 2013 |newspaper=[[Mid Day]] |date=9 July 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911085117/http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2009/jul/090709-Bollywood-Bengaluru-Deepika-Padukone-marathon-1-crore-charity.htm |archive-date=11 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In 2010, Padukone adopted the [[Maharashtra|Maharashtrian]] village of [[Ambegaon]] as part of NDTV's Greenathon Campaign, to provide the village with a regular supply of electricity.<ref>{{cite news |last=Joshi |first=Tushar |title=Deepika adopts a Ambegaon village |url=http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/mar/100310-Deepika-Padukone-Ambegaon-village-Greenathon-campaign.htm |accessdate=21 April 2013 |newspaper=Mid Day |date=10 March 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180911085232/http://archive.mid-day.com/entertainment/2010/mar/100310-Deepika-Padukone-Ambegaon-village-Greenathon-campaign.htm |archive-date=11 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> She visited Indian ''[[jawans]]'' (troops) in [[Jammu]], for an [[Independence Day (India)|Independence Day]] special episode of NDTV's reality show ''Jai Jawaan''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone in uniform |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/photos/entertainment/rough-n-tough-deepika-padukone-in-uniform/photo-yIFQ9OLxuFGsGEJk7bEiUI.html |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=24 June 2013 |date=23 November 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222144133/http://www.hindustantimes.com/photos/entertainment/rough-n-tough-deepika-padukone-in-uniform/photo-yIFQ9OLxuFGsGEJk7bEiUI.html |archivedate=22 December 2015 |df=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:SLAMtheTour 20Sep2014 (199) (15143666038) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|alt=A shot of Deepika Padukone dancing on stage|Padukone performing at the  \"SLAM! The Tour\" concert in 2014]]\n\nPadukone took part in the opening ceremony of the [[2010 Indian Premier League|third season of the Indian Premier League]] at the [[DY Patil Stadium]] in [[Navi Mumbai]].<ref>{{cite web |title=IPL 3 kicks off with grand opening ceremony |url=http://sports.ndtv.com/cricket/news/134698-ipl-3-kicks-off-with-grand-opening-ceremony |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=24 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006100537/http://sports.ndtv.com/cricket/news/134698-ipl-3-kicks-off-with-grand-opening-ceremony |archivedate=6 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Three years later, she performed alongside Shah Rukh Khan, [[Katrina Kaif]], and [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] for the [[2013 Indian Premier League|sixth edition]] of the Indian Premier League.<ref>{{cite web |title=IPL 2013: Shah Rukh Khan, Katrina Kaif, Deepika Padukone, Pitbull showcase diverse culture |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/ipl-2013-shah-rukh-khan-katrina-kaif-deepika-padukone-pitbull-showcase-diverse-culture-349474 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=24 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713121133/http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/ipl-2013-shah-rukh-khan-katrina-kaif-deepika-padukone-pitbull-showcase-diverse-culture-349474 |archivedate=13 July 2014 |df=}}</ref> In 2014, she participated in a concert tour across North America, entitled \"SLAM! The Tour\", in which she performed alongside her co-stars from ''Happy New Year''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone take America by storm |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/shah-rukh-khan-deepika-padukone-slam-american-fans-houston-new-jersey/1/384742.html |work=India Today |date=24 September 2014 |accessdate=26 September 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140926201737/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/shah-rukh-khan-deepika-padukone-slam-american-fans-houston-new-jersey/1/384742.html |archivedate=26 September 2014 |df=}}</ref> Padukone has also been involved with the [[Olympic Gold Quest]] team, established by her father and [[Geet Sethi]] to support Indian athletes at the Olympic Games, along with sports personalities such as [[Leander Paes]] and [[Viswanathan Anand]] and several other actors.<ref name=\"Nehwal2012\">{{cite book |last=Nehwal |first=Saina |title=Playing to Win |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tBSi3rdUPO0C&pg=PT41 |date=15 December 2012 |publisher=Penguin Books Limited |isbn=978-81-8475-915-0 |page=41 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131101113850/http://books.google.com/books?id=tBSi3rdUPO0C&pg=PT41 |archivedate=1 November 2013 |df=}}</ref> In 2013, she launched her own line of clothing for women, in association with the retail chain [[PVH (company)|Van Heusen]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone makes her debut as fashion designer |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-makes-her-debut-as-fashion-designer/1177826/ |accessdate=4 October 2013 |newspaper=The Indian Express |date=3 October 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140213011332/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/deepika-padukone-makes-her-debut-as-fashion-designer/1177826 |archivedate=13 February 2014 |df=}}</ref> Two years later, Padukone collaborated with the fashion portal [[Myntra]] to launch another line under her brand \"All About You\".<ref>{{cite news |author=Anshul |title=Myntra launches Deepika Padukone brand \u2018All About You\u2019; prices start Rs 1,500 |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/industry/companies/myntra-launches-deepika-padukone-brand-all-about-you-prices-start-rs-1500/154226/ |accessdate=11 October 2016 |work=The Financial Express |date=20 October 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011224233/http://www.financialexpress.com/industry/companies/myntra-launches-deepika-padukone-brand-all-about-you-prices-start-rs-1500/154226/ |archivedate=11 October 2016 |df=}}</ref> In 2019, she was appointed as the chairperson of the [[Mumbai Academy of the Moving Image]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone is the new MAMI chairperson |url=https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-is-the-new-mami-chairperson/articleshow/67750989.cms |accessdate=30 January 2019 |newspaper=Mumbai Mirror |date=30 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190130110026/https://mumbaimirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukone-is-the-new-mami-chairperson/articleshow/67750989.cms |archive-date=30 January 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Through her own company, Ka Enterprises, Padukone invested in Drum Foods International, a [[fast-moving consumer goods]] company, and Blu Smart, an [[electric vehicle|electric taxi]] startup.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone invests in maker of Epigamia yogurt |url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-invests-in-maker-of-epigamia-yogurt-1557771851043.html |accessdate=16 May 2019 |work=Mint |date=14 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517231717/https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-invests-in-maker-of-epigamia-yogurt-1557771851043.html |archive-date=17 May 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Sriram, M.|title=Deepika Padukone\u2019s family office invests in e-taxi startup Blu Smart|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-s-family-office-invests-in-blu-smart-1569243127845.html|accessdate=24 September 2019|work=Mint|date=23 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924101621/https://www.livemint.com/companies/start-ups/deepika-padukone-s-family-office-invests-in-blu-smart-1569243127845.html|archive-date=24 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nPadukone has also been outspoken on issues such as feminism and has said, \"New feminism isn't about being aggressive; it's about reaching the top yet being soft. It's about being you \u2014 feminine, strong and full of will power.\u201d<ref name=\"Sinha2011\">{{cite book |last=Sinha |first=Dheeraj |title=Consumer India: Inside the Indian Mind and Wallet |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Uw-XCvE9G4YC&pg=PA129 |date=14 February 2011 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=978-0-470-82632-4 |page=129}}</ref> In a 2015 interview, Padukone spoke about her personal experience of overcoming depression, and in October that year she formed a foundation to create awareness on mental health in India, named [[The Live Love Laugh Foundation]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Awaasthi, Kavita |title=Deepika Padukone on suffering from depression: It was a struggle to wake up |date=17 January 2015 |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid/deepika-padukone-on-suffering-from-depression-it-was-a-struggle-to-wake-up/article1-1306957.aspx |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=18 January 2015 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150118035439/http://www.hindustantimes.com/tabloid/deepika-padukone-on-suffering-from-depression-it-was-a-struggle-to-wake-up/article1-1306957.aspx |archivedate=18 January 2015 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone launches her foundation 'Live, Love and Laugh' on World Mental Health Day |date=10 October 2015 |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-launches-her-foundation-live-love-and-laugh-on-world-mental-health-day-2133489 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=28 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022163008/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-launches-her-foundation-live-love-and-laugh-on-world-mental-health-day-2133489 |archivedate=22 October 2015 |df=}}</ref> The following year, she launched a campaign named More Than Just Sad to assist general physicians in their treatment of patients suffering from depression or anxiety.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone\u2019s foundation launches awareness programme on mental health |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukones-foundation-launches-awareness-programme-on-mental-health-2811187/#sthash.A7hGmE4o.dpuf |date=20 May 2016 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=22 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160521215431/http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/deepika-padukones-foundation-launches-awareness-programme-on-mental-health-2811187/ |archivedate=21 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> Also in 2016, the foundation teamed with Facebook and the [[AASRA]] organisation to launch multilingual tools and educational resources in Facebook's networking site to support people with suicidal tendencies.<ref>{{cite news |last=Alawadhi |first=Neha |title=Facebook partners with Deepika Padukone's Foundation; launches suicide prevention tools in India |url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/52749651.cms |date=14 June 2016 |work=The Economic Times |accessdate=15 June 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160911230551/http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/articleshow/52749651.cms |archivedate=11 September 2016 |df=}}</ref> Padukone became the brand ambassador for the NGO [[Indian Psychiatric Society]] and on her foundation's first anniversary, the two organisations collaborated to launch the video and poster campaign #DobaraPoocho dedicated to victims and survivors of depression.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone named Indian Psychiatric Society's brand ambassador |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-named-Indian-Psychiatric-Societys-brand-ambassador/articleshow/53856784.cms |accessdate=5 November 2016 |work=The Times of India |date=25 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160829212121/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Deepika-Padukone-named-Indian-Psychiatric-Societys-brand-ambassador/articleshow/53856784.cms |archivedate=29 August 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Stigma key reason why mental health issues not being addressed: Deepika |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/stigma-key-reason-why-mental-health-issues-not-being-addressed-deepika/story-IhbNNQwyGfdPqwTFNsQEvM.html |accessdate=5 November 2016 |work=Hindustan Times |date=10 October 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161106061008/http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/stigma-key-reason-why-mental-health-issues-not-being-addressed-deepika/story-IhbNNQwyGfdPqwTFNsQEvM.html |archivedate=6 November 2016 |df=}}</ref> The [[World Economic Forum]] presented her with the Crystal Award in 2020 for creating awareness on mental health.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone feted with Crystal Award at WEF; stresses on importance of mental health, quotes Martin Luther King |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/deepika-padukone-feted-with-crystal-award-at-wef-stresses-on-importance-of-mental-health-quotes-martin-luther-king/articleshow/73471900.cms |accessdate=21 January 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=21 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, Padukone lent her support to students who were brutalised during the [[2020 JNU Attack]] due to their [[Citizenship Amendment Act protests|protests]] against the [[Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2019|Citizenship Amendment Act]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018We are not scared\u2019: Why Deepika Padukone\u2019s JNU visit matters |url=https://scroll.in/reel/949118/why-deepika-padukones-jnu-visit-matters |date=8 January 2020 |website=Scroll.in |accessdate=8 January 2020}}</ref> Members of the ruling [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] criticised her decision and asked people to boycott her film ''Chhapaak''.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Deepika Padukone Was Patriot Earlier, Now...\": Kanhaiya Kumar On Criticism |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/jawaharlal-nehru-university-jnu-deepika-padukone-was-patriot-earlier-now-kanhaiya-kumar-on-criticism-2161458 |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=NDTV |date=9 January 2020}}</ref> Many others praised her for standing up against a crackdown on dissent, as mainstream Bollywood actors avoid making political statements fearing backlash and consequences on their film.<ref>{{cite web |title=Bollywood A-lister backs protesting students, faces boycott calls |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-india-student-protests/bollywood-a-lister-backs-protesting-students-faces-boycott-calls-idUSKBN1Z71CU |accessdate=8 January 2020 |website=Reuters |date=8 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n== In the media ==\nThe journalist [[Vir Sanghvi]], in 2013, described Padukone as \"strong, someone who makes up her own mind, [and] has motivation within herself.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Sanghvi |first=Vir |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shah-rukh-khan-and-deepika-padukone-in-conversation-with-vir-sanghvi/story-IVIPeV2PyW34oFg2UpCZoJ.html |title=Shah Rukh Khan and Deepika Padukone in conversation with Vir Sanghvi |work=Hindustan Times |accessdate=17 August 2013 |date=4 September 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201125703/http://www.hindustantimes.com/brunch/shah-rukh-khan-and-deepika-padukone-in-conversation-with-vir-sanghvi/story-IVIPeV2PyW34oFg2UpCZoJ.html |archivedate=1 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> She is particularly known in the media as a professional, disciplined performer, whose \"work takes precedence over everything else.\"<ref name=\"making of deepika\" /> A reviewer for Rediff.com described her personality as \"simple,\" \"grounded,\" and \"accessible,\" and wrote, \"She takes criticism in her stride, acknowledges her limitations and strives to work hard at getting better. She handles praise with equal composure.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-10-reasons-why-we-love-deepika-padukone/20130805.htm#10 |title=10 reasons we love Deepika Padukone |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=12 August 2013 |date=5 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130812060241/http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-1-10-reasons-why-we-love-deepika-padukone/20130805.htm |archivedate=12 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> Ayan Mukerji (the director of ''Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani'') considers her to be \"a woman who will flirt with you but you will love to take her home to meet your mom as well.\"<ref name=\"making of deepika\" /> Padukone has maintained a Twitter account since 2010, and launched an official Facebook page in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-07/news-interviews/36950476_1_facebook-page-deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-race |title=Deepika Padukone races from 2.6 to 5 million |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=7 February 2013 |work=The Times of India |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023055931/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-02-07/news-interviews/36950476_1_facebook-page-deepika-padukone-cocktail-and-race |archive-date=23 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> She is the most followed Asian woman on Twitter.<ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone becomes the most followed woman on Twitter in Asia! |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-becomes-the-most-followed-woman-on-twitter-in-asia-2260199 |accessdate=11 October 2016 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=30 September 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005023708/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-becomes-the-most-followed-woman-on-twitter-in-asia-2260199 |archivedate=5 October 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/deepika-padukone-ahead-of-amitabh-salman-khan-on-facebook/story-8rCxIBo9ZxN4etbgJi1rPN.html |title=Deepika Padukone ahead of Amitabh, Salman Khan on Facebook |work=Hindustan Times |date=26 March 2014 |accessdate=28 March 2014 |last=Baksi |first=Dibyojyoti |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160201124048/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/deepika-padukone-ahead-of-amitabh-salman-khan-on-facebook/story-8rCxIBo9ZxN4etbgJi1rPN.html |archivedate=1 February 2016 |df=}}</ref>\n[[File:Deepika p Lux-Award 2016.jpg|thumb|upright=0.9|alt=A shot of Deepika Padukone posing for the camera|Padukone at an event for [[Lux (soap)|Lux]] in 2016]]\nPadukone is considered among the most popular and high-profile celebrities in India.<ref name=\"heroine\" /><ref name=\"high\" /> Analysing her career, [[Reuters]] published that after making a successful debut with ''Om Shanti Om'', she featured in a series of films for which critics labelled her as \"wooden\" and \"mocked her accent.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Jamkhandikar |first=Shilpa |url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2013/06/12/deepika-padukone-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-idINDEE95B0CM20130612 |title=Deepika Padukone breaks free of Brad Pitt syndrome |agency=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=30 August 2013 |date=12 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130827144604/http://in.reuters.com/article/2013/06/12/deepika-padukone-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-idINDEE95B0CM20130612 |archivedate=27 August 2013 |df=}}</ref> ''The Indian Express'' added, \"Not too long ago after a few unwise script calls and the public blow up of her high profile relationship with Ranbir Kapoor, Deepika was written off. Credit to her much touted professionalism, dedication, discipline and perseverance that she bounced back.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Harneet |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |title=Post Chennai Express, Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani Deepika Padukone is number 1 |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=30 August 2013 |date=16 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205203526/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |archivedate=5 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> Following the success of ''Cocktail'', ''Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani'', and ''Chennai Express'', several media publications began crediting her as the most successful contemporary actress in India.<ref name=\"top\" /><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1130822/jsp/t2/story_17256831.jsp |title=Heroine no. 1 \u2013 Deepika leads the Bolly girl gang |newspaper=The Telegraph |accessdate=30 August 2013 |date=22 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131002122212/http://www.telegraphindia.com/1130822/jsp/t2/story_17256831.jsp |archivedate=2 October 2013 |df=}}<br />{{cite news |last=Singh |first=Harneet |url=http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |title=Post Chennai Express, Yeh Jawaani Hai Deewani Deepika Padukone is number 1 |newspaper=The Indian Express |accessdate=7 October 2013 |date=16 August 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205203526/http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/post-chennai-express-yeh-jawaani-hai-deewani-deepika-padukone-is-number-1/1155960/0 |archivedate=5 February 2016 |df=}}</ref> ''[[India Today]]'' featured her among the nation's 50 most powerful people in 2017 and 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/india-today-top-50-powerful-indians-mukesh-ambani-ratan-tata-kumar-mangalam-birla-gautam-adani-anand-mahindra-srk-amitabh-bacchan/1/928939.html |title=50 power people |work=India Today |date=14 April 2017 |accessdate=21 April 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417122537/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/india-today-top-50-powerful-indians-mukesh-ambani-ratan-tata-kumar-mangalam-birla-gautam-adani-anand-mahindra-srk-amitabh-bacchan/1/928939.html |archivedate=17 April 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/the-most-powerful-people-of-india-2019-full-list-1574021-2019-07-26 |title=The most powerful people of India 2019 |work=India Today |date=26 July 2019 |accessdate=30 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190730004608/https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/the-most-powerful-people-of-india-2019-full-list-1574021-2019-07-26 |archive-date=30 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The global edition of ''Forbes'' ranked her as the tenth highest-paid actress in the world in 2016 and in 2018, the magazine ranked her as the highest-earning woman celebrity in India.<ref name=\"forbes\">{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/23/the-worlds-highest-paid-actresses-2016-jennifer-lawrence-banks-46-million-payday-ahead-of-melissa-mccarthy/ |title=The World's Highest-Paid Actresses 2016: Jennifer Lawrence Banks $46 Million Payday Ahead Of Melissa McCarthy |work=Forbes |date=23 August 2016 |accessdate=23 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823191155/http://www.forbes.com/sites/natalierobehmed/2016/08/23/the-worlds-highest-paid-actresses-2016-jennifer-lawrence-banks-46-million-payday-ahead-of-melissa-mccarthy/ |archivedate=23 August 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/emjl45efgmh/10-deepika-padukone/ |title=Deepika Padukone |work=Forbes |accessdate=23 August 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160823235831/http://www.forbes.com/pictures/emjl45efgmh/10-deepika-padukone/ |archivedate=23 August 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Panchal |first1=Salil |last2=Gangal |first2=Neeraj |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2018-celebrity-100/salman-khan-tops-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list-for-third-time-in-a-row/51955/1 |title=Salman Khan tops Forbes India Celebrity 100 list for third time in a row |work=Forbes |accessdate=2 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205064716/http://www.forbesindia.com/article/2018-celebrity-100/salman-khan-tops-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list-for-third-time-in-a-row/51955/1 |archive-date=5 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> From 2014\u20132016 and in 2018, she was the highest ranked woman on the Indian edition of ''[[Forbes]]''{{'}} \"[[Celebrity 100]]\" (a list based on the income and popularity of celebrities), peaking at the fourth position in 2018 with an estimated annual earning of over {{INRConvert|1.12|b}}.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2016/deepika-padukone/1587/11 |title=Deepika Padukone |work=[[Forbes India]] |accessdate=26 January 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224132532/http://www.forbesindia.com/celebprofile2016/deepika-padukone/1587/11 |archivedate=24 December 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Salman Khan beats Shah Rukh Khan; tops the \u20182016 Forbes India Celebrity 100 List\u2019 - Bollywood Hungama |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/salman-khan-beats-shah-rukh-khan-tops-2016-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list/ |publisher=Bollywood Hungama |accessdate=25 December 2016 |date=23 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224143231/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/bollywood/salman-khan-beats-shah-rukh-khan-tops-2016-forbes-india-celebrity-100-list/ |archivedate=24 December 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2018-celebrity-100/1735/all |title=2018 Celebrity 100 |work=Forbes India |accessdate=5 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205064833/http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2018-celebrity-100/1735/all |archive-date=5 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Also in 2018, ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine named Padukone one of the [[Time 100|100 most influential people in the world]], ''Variety'' featured her in their listing of the 50 most impactful women in the world, and the market research firm [[YouGov]] named her the world's thirteenth most admired woman.<ref>{{cite news |last=Diesel |first=Vin |url=http://time.com/collection/most-influential-people-2018/5217557/deepika-padukone/ |title=Deepika Padukone |work=Time |accessdate=21 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180420220932/http://time.com/collection/most-influential-people-2018/5217557/deepika-padukone/|archive-date=20 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://variety.com/gallery/international-womens-impact-report-2018/#!33/deepika-padukone-3 |title=Deepika Padukone |work=Variety |accessdate=28 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180322020424/http://variety.com/gallery/international-womens-impact-report-2018/#!33/deepika-padukone-3|archive-date=22 March 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://yougov.co.uk/news/2018/04/11/worlds-most-admired-2018/ |title=World\u2019s most admired 2018 |publisher=[[YouGov]] |accessdate=28 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612141722/https://yougov.co.uk/news/2018/04/11/worlds-most-admired-2018/ |archive-date=12 June 2018 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nPadukone is considered a sex symbol and style icon in India \u2013 the media cites her figure, height {{height|m=1.74}}, smile, and eyes as her distinctive physical features.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://idiva.com/photogallery-entertainment/50-most-beautiful-indian-faces/11401/21 |title=50 Most Beautiful Indian Faces |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=9 March 2012 |publisher=iDiva |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBO91br?url=http://idiva.com/photogallery-entertainment/50-most-beautiful-indian-faces/11401/21 |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> The actress ranks high on various listings of the most attractive Indian celebrities.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/554302/style-icon-deepika-padukone/ |title=Style icon: Deepika Padukone |work=[[The Express Tribune]] |date=24 May 2013 |accessdate=19 July 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130608023546/http://tribune.com.pk/story/554302/style-icon-deepika-padukone/ |archivedate=8 June 2013 |df=}}</ref> In 2008, she topped ''[[Maxim (India)|Indian ''Maxim'']]''{{'}}s \"Hot 100\" list,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-08-24/news-interviews/27910255_1_sexiest-woman-deepika-padukone-platform |title=Deepika is the world's sexiest woman! |work=The Times of India |date=24 August 2008 |accessdate=4 August 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928194527/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2008-08-24/news-interviews/27910255_1_sexiest-woman-deepika-padukone-platform |archive-date=28 September 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref> and in 2012, she was named \"India's Most Beautiful Woman\" by the Indian edition of ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine.<ref name=\"people most beautiful\">{{cite web |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/deepika-padukone-named-india-most-beautiful-woman/1/9386.html#photo1 |title=Deepika named India's Most Beautiful Woman |work=India Today |accessdate=19 July 2013 |date=3 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwCXdOMt?url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/gallery/deepika-padukone-named-india-most-beautiful-woman/1/9386.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Padukone has frequently featured in ''The Times of India''{{'}}s listing of the \"Most Desirable Woman\", topping the list in 2012 and 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-2013s-Most-desirable-woman/articleshow/35726757.cms? |title=Deepika Padukone: 2013\u2019s Most desirable woman |work=The Times of India |date=30 May 2014 |accessdate=31 May 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140531081711/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news-interviews/Deepika-Padukone-2013s-Most-desirable-woman/articleshow/35726757.cms |archivedate=31 May 2014 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-29/news-interviews/38903243_1_entrant-desirable-women-desirable-men |title=Times top 50 Most Desirable Women of 2012 |work=The Times of India |date=29 April 2013 |accessdate=19 July 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019103638/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-29/news-interviews/38903243_1_entrant-desirable-women-desirable-men |archive-date=19 October 2013 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Priyanka-Chopra-The-Most-Desirable-woman-of-2015/articleshow/52187930.cms |title=Priyanka Chopra: The Most Desirable woman of 2015 |newspaper=The Times of India |accessdate=10 May 2016 |date=10 May 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160511112201/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Priyanka-Chopra-The-Most-Desirable-woman-of-2015/articleshow/52187930.cms |archivedate=11 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> In 2010 and 2014, she was named the \"World's Sexiest Woman\" by the Indian edition of ''[[FHM (India)|FHM]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=KBR |first=Upala |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-displaces-katrina-kaif-in-fhm-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2014-1999264 |title=Deepika Padukone displaces Katrina Kaif in FHM 100 Sexiest Women in the World 2014 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=5 July 2014 |date=3 July 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707022951/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-displaces-katrina-kaif-in-fhm-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2014-1999264 |archivedate=7 July 2014 |df=}}</ref> and she was selected by the UK magazine ''[[Eastern Eye]]'' as the \"Sexiest Asian Woman\" in 2016 and 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/deepika-padukone-is-the-sexiest-asian-women/20161209.htm |title=Deepika Padukone is Asia's sexiest woman! |publisher=Rediff.com |accessdate=8 February 2017 |date=9 December 2016 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170112005154/http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/deepika-padukone-is-the-sexiest-asian-women/20161209.htm |archivedate=12 January 2017 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/50-sexiest-asian-women-deepika-padukone-priyanka-chopra-5480941/ |title=50 Sexiest Asian Women: Deepika tops the list, Priyanka is in second position |work=The Indian Express |accessdate=8 December 2018 |date=6 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207135508/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/50-sexiest-asian-women-deepika-padukone-priyanka-chopra-5480941/ |archive-date=7 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Taking note of her dress sense, ''Filmfare'' credited her as one of the \"few actresses who experiments with colours, cuts and silhouettes.\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Tandan |first=Raedita |url=http://www.filmfare.com/features/poll-most-fashionable-star-3034.html |title=Poll: Most Fashionable Star |work=Filmfare |accessdate=4 August 2013 |date=3 May 2008 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6JwBG075Y?url=http://www.filmfare.com/features/poll-most-fashionable-star-3034.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> In the fitness book ''The Four-Week Countdown Diet'', the actress was cited by Namita Jain as \"the ultimate role model for a healthy, fit and active lifestyle.\"<ref name=\"Jain2011\">{{cite book |last=Jain |first=Namita |title=The Four-Week Countdown Diet |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-Ru_R9r07RgC&pg=PR9 |date=1 January 2011 |publisher=Penguin Books India |isbn=978-0-14-306781-8 |page=9 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131028162350/http://books.google.com/books?id=-Ru_R9r07RgC&pg=PR9 |archivedate=28 October 2013 |df=}}</ref>\n\nPadukone is an active celebrity endorser for several brands and products, including [[Tissot]], [[Maybelline]], [[Coca-Cola]], and [[L'Oreal Paris]], among others.<ref>{{cite web |title=Deepika Padukone brand ambassador for Tissot |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/money/report_deepika-padukone-brand-ambassador-for-tissot_1139085 |work=Daily News and Analysis |accessdate=9 March 2013}}<br />{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone is Sony brand ambassador |url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/62603/deepika-padukone-sony-brand-ambassador.html |work=[[Deccan Herald]] |accessdate=9 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927121724/http://www.deccanherald.com/content/62603/deepika-padukone-sony-brand-ambassador.html |archivedate=27 September 2013 |df=}}<br />{{cite video |title=Nescafe announces Deepika Padukone as brand ambassador |url=http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/news/nescafe-announces-deepika-padukone-as-brand-ambassador/150166 |publisher=NDTV |accessdate=9 March 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928210902/http://www.ndtv.com/video/player/news/nescafe-announces-deepika-padukone-as-brand-ambassador/150166 |archivedate=28 September 2013 |df=}}<br />{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone lives her DDLJ moment in Chennai Express |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-lives-her-ddlj-moment-in-chennai-express-1849731 |accessdate=22 January 2014 |newspaper=Daily News and Analysis |date=18 June 2013 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202203154/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-lives-her-ddlj-moment-in-chennai-express-1849731 |archivedate=2 February 2014 |df=}}<br />{{cite web |last=Singh |first=Aarti K. |title=All at 20! May be she is born with it |date=3 August 2006 |url=http://ibnlive.in.com/news/all-at-20-may-be-she-is-born-with-it/17520-8.html |publisher=CNN-IBN |accessdate=30 September 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007061205/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/all-at-20-may-be-she-is-born-with-it/17520-8.html |archivedate=7 October 2014}}<br />{{cite book |last=Kapoor |first=Jagdeep |title=Twenty Four Brand Mantras: Finding a Place in the Minds and Hearts of Consumers |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fmmkwDy9_QIC&pg=PA68 |date=9 February 2009 |publisher=SAGE Publications |isbn=978-81-7829-943-3 |page=68 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160504103925/https://books.google.com/books?id=fmmkwDy9_QIC&pg=PA68 |archivedate=4 May 2016 |df=}}</ref> In 2014, ''Business Standard'' reported that Padukone earned {{INRConvert|50|m}} to {{INRConvert|60|m}} per endorsement deal and [[TAM Media Research|TAM AdEX]] named Padukone the most visible face on television in India that year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pinto |first1=Viveat Susan |title=Deepika: Leading lady in brand fees |url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/deepika-leading-lady-in-brand-fees-114030700027_1.html |accessdate=5 March 2017 |work=Business Standard |date=11 March 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160704181135/http://www.business-standard.com/article/management/deepika-leading-lady-in-brand-fees-114030700027_1.html |archivedate=4 July 2016 |df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Deepika Padukone is leading the advertisement space |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-is-leading-the-advertisement-space-2045937 |accessdate=5 March 2017 |work=Daily News and Analysis |date=21 December 2014 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306032102/http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-deepika-padukone-is-leading-the-advertisement-space-2045937 |archivedate=6 March 2017 |df=}}</ref> [[Duff & Phelps]] estimated her brand value to be US$102.5 million, in 2018, the second highest of Indian celebrities.<ref>{{cite news |last=Laghate |first=Gaurav |title=Virat Kohli tops powerful celebrity brands list with a brand value of $170.9 million |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/services/advertising/virat-kohli-tops-powerful-celebrity-brands-list-with-a-brand-value-of-170-9-million/articleshow/67469396.cms |accessdate=26 January 2020 |work=The Economic Times |date=10 January 2019}}</ref> In 2020, she became the first Indian actor to campaign for the fashion company [[Louis Vuitton]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Tewari |first=Saumya |title=Deepika Padukone becomes first Indian actor to feature in Louis Vuitton campaign |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/deepika-padukone-becomes-first-indian-actor-to-feature-in-louis-vuitton-campaign-11579781913267.html |accessdate=24 January 2020 |work=Mint |date=23 January 2020 }}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Deepika Padukone}}\nPadukone has been the recipient of three [[Filmfare Awards]]: Best Female Debut for ''Om Shanti Om'' (2007), and two Best Actress awards for ''Goliyon Ki Raasleela Ram-Leela'' (2013) and  ''Piku'' (2015).<ref name=\"heroine\" /><ref name=\"ff13\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=25em}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{cite news |author1=Ajwani, Deepak |author2=Paul, Cuckoo |title=Deepika Padukone: Living a Fairytale |url=http://forbesindia.com/article/2013-celebrity-100/deepika-padukone-living-a-fairytale/36753/0 |work=Forbes |date=26 December 2013}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=2138653}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes person|deepika_padukone|Deepika Padukone}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards received by Deepika Padukone\n| list =\n{{FilmfareAwardBestActress}}\n{{FilmfareAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestActress}}\n{{IIFAAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestActress}}\n{{ScreenAwardBestFemaleDebut}}\n{{StarGuildAwardBestActress}}\n{{StardustAwardFemaleActor}}\n{{ZeeCineAwardBestActorFemale}}\n{{Zee Cine Award for Best Female Debut}}\n}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pa